title: harvey wallbanger cake(to be prepared in baking ring)
directions: Evenly
grease baking ring or spray with vegetable oil. In
a large
mixing bowl combine all ingredients;
beat for 4 minutes on
medium
speed
with electric mixer.
Remove 1 1/2 cups batter, reserve for cupcakes.
Pour remaining cake batter into
prepared baking rings.
Microwave on 2/3 power (Medium-high)
for 2 minutes, 1/2 power (Medium) for 20 to 30 minutes, or
until wooden
pick
inserted
in
center comes out clean. Rotate
once during
cooking time, if necessary.
Batter will run
over
sides of
pan
slightly.
Let
stand in pan for 10 minutes.
Turn out on plate and glaze while warm.

title: shredded beef
directions: Wrap in foil; bake in a pan, to catch juice, for 24 hours at 200`.
Shred beef with a fork.

title: grandma's coleslaw
directions: Pour boiling water over cabbage.
Add salt and knead well to soften cabbage.
Add carrot, lemon juice and dill.
Stir and add mayonnaise; mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream shortening and sugar; add eggs, syrup, and honey. Add all spices. Add flour, alternating with buttermilk. Stir in nuts and raisins. Batter will be very thick. Drop onto greased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; put in casserole dish.
Sprinkle Ritz cracker crumbs on top with melted stick of butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: burger bundles
directions: Mix beef with milk.
Divide into 10 patties.
On waxed paper, flatten each patty to form a 6-inch circle.
Put equal amounts of stuffing on each of 5 patties.
Place another pattie on top and seal.

title: asparagus and peas casserole(servings:  12)
directions: Arrange asparagus on bottom of flat casserole or oblong Pyrex dish.
Mix chestnuts, soup and peas and pour over asparagus. Cover with cheese.
In small skillet, melt margarine.
Carefully place bread strips (a few at a time) in margarine to absorb and then arrange bread on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: southwestern roll-ups
directions: Spread dressing and salsa on each tortilla; sprinkle with cheese.
Top with lettuce and meat; roll up.
For hot roll-ups; prepare as directed, except omit lettuce.
Wrap each tortilla in paper towel.
Microwave on High 1 minute or until thoroughly heated.

title: onion-baked pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine soup mix with the bread crumbs. Dip pork chops in egg, then soup mixture, coating well.
Place in lightly greased large shallow baking pan and if desired, drizzle with melted butter.
Bake, turning once, 1 hour or until tender. Yields 8 servings.

title: oven baked chicken
directions: Dip chicken in milk and roll in corn flakes.
Layer in greased baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: poppy seed crescents
directions: Combine 1 cup flour, whole wheat flour, yeast and salt in large mixing bowl, stirring well.
Combine skim milk, water, cottage cheese, honey and margarine in a small saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until oleo melts; stir occasionally.
Cool to 120° to 130°.
Gradually add liquid mixture to flour mixture, beating well at high speed of electric mixer.
Beat an additional 3 minutes at medium speed.
Gradually add remaining 2 1/4 cups flour to make a firm dough.

title: beet pickles
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients 20 minutes, then add remaining and simmer five minutes more.
Add more juice if needed.

title: chicken ham casserole
directions: Place chicken, salt, pepper, onion and celery tops in pressure cooker and cook until tender.
Cut chicken into large pieces. Strain liquid and save.
In skillet, cook butter, mushrooms and onion, then add next 6 ingredients to make sauce (the sauce and the chicken may be combined the day before).
Arrange noodles, ham, almonds and chicken mixture in layers in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish. Break bread.
Put in bottom of dish.
Brown sausage and drain. Spoon over bread.
Sprinkle cheese over sausage.
Beat eggs, salt, pepper and milk together.
Pour over cheese, sausage and bread. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: poppy seed cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, egg and vanilla until creamy.
Add pecans and poppy seed.
Stir in flour and chill dough.
Shape into 2 or 3 rolls.
Sprinkle each roll with sugar.
Wrap in plastic wrap and freeze overnight.
Slice while frozen.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: glazed walnuts
directions: Combine apricot preserves, sugar and soy sauce in a small saucepan.
Heat over medium heat and stir constantly until preserves melt.
Stir in walnuts; spread out onto lightly oiled baking sheet.
Bake in preheated 275° oven for 20 minutes or until walnuts feel dry to the touch.
Remove walnuts onto waxed paper and cool completely.
Store in airtight container.

title: banana macadamia nut bread or muffins
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl, combine the first 8 ingredients.
Beat at low speed, scraping bowl often until well mixed.
Add bananas and orange juice.
Continue beating until all mixed.
By hand, stir in coconut and nuts.
Batter will be thick. Spread into 3 greased mini loaf pans or 1 greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake 60 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan(s).

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix sugar, butter and peanut butter until smooth.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Chill.
Dip each ball in melted chocolate.

title: arva's oatmeal macaroons
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix margarine, sugars, vanilla and eggs.
Beat well.
Sift together flour, soda and cinnamon and add to first mixture.
Mix well.
Fold in quick oatmeal and nuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls on a very, very lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove immediately to rack to cool.
(Do not overbake or cookies will be hard.)

title: macaroni cheese
directions: Boil noodles.
Drain.
Add butter.
Grate cheese.
Layer cheese and noodles in pan.
Beat egg and milk.
Pour over macaroni and cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until hot. Makes 6 servings.

title: avocado pie
directions: Blend avocado, milk and juice; spread fast.
Top with cream and nuts.

title: beef & cheese bake
directions: In 10 inch skillet, cook ground beef and onion until meat is browned and onion is tender;
drain excess fat.
Stir in soup, 1/2 cup milk and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Meanwhile cook macaroni according to package directions;
drain.
Return to pan along with butter, 1/3 cup milk, cheese and green pepper.
Heat and stir until butter and cheese are melted.
Transfer meat mixture to a 10 x 6 x 2 inch baking dish.
Spoon macaroni mixture on top.
Cover and bake in a 350 degree oven for 25 minutes.
Uncover and bake 5 - 10 minutes more.

title: broccoli and beef
directions: Carefully slice beef into thin pieces across the grain. Marinate beef in soy sauce, wine and salt.
Place oil in wok and heat to smoking point.
Quickly stir-fry beef about 3 minutes. Remove beef. Add broccoli to wok with water and sugar.
Turn heat to medium-high. Cover and cook 6 minutes.
Lift cover.
Stir occasionally. Serve with beef.

title: crack salad
directions: Mix.
Put vegetables in jar.
Mix the liquid cold.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter; blend in flour and cheeses.
Add milk; cook and stir until boiling.
Gently stir in broccoli.
Place in 1-quart casserole; top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: vegetable dip(makes 1 cup.)
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill.
Serve with sliced fresh vegetables.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Slice zucchini.
Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: vegetarian chili with rice
directions: In a large saucepan, combine kidney beans, Northern beans, undrained tomatoes, tomato sauce, green pepper, onion, chili powder, sugar, basil, garlic and 1 cup water.
Bring to boiling. Reduce heat; simmer, covered, for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Top each serving of chili with 1/2 cup hot rice. Makes 4 servings.
Contains 316 calories.

title: corn chowder
directions: Put in a large kettle with just enough water to cover and cook slowly until everything is tender, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: seafood dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, then chill.

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place breast in baking pan.
Combine all other ingredients for sauce.
Pour sauce over chicken; bake for 1 1/4 hours, basting every 15 minutes, until chicken is tender and nicely browned.

title: chocolate surprise
directions: Make cake according to directions on box; let cool.
Prepare pudding as directed on boxes.
Crumble half of cake in bottom of a large bowl; cover with half of pudding mixture, half of candy and half of the Cool Whip.
Repeat for another layer and top off with the Kit-Kat candies.

title: baby food cake
directions: Cream sugar and eggs together.
Mix in other ingredients.
Bake in preheated oven for 1 hour at 350°.
Use tube pan.

title: rice casserole
directions: Wash rice under running water. Slightly brown in butter on stovetop. Add mushrooms, onion soup and beef bouillon soup. Bake covered 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: holiday punch
directions: Add gelatin to 2 cups boiling water in large bowl.
Stir to dissolve.
Add frozen juices; stir well to blend.
Add 6 cups cold water and pineapple juice; mix well.
Pour over ice in punch bowl. Add ginger ale just before serving.
Garnish with orange slices. Yields 50 servings.

title: apple pie
directions: Cook
apples,
water and 1/2 cup sugar until apples are tender.
Combine cornstarch, apple juice, orange juice and 1/2 cup sugar
and	mix well.
Add to apples and cook until clear. Bake in uncooked crust
with lattice topping at 350° or 400°. Can add cinnamon, if desired.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Whip cream cheese slowly. Add cream. Beat until thick. Fold in remaining ingredients. Spoon into paper-lined muffin tins and freeze. Serve frozen.

title: hot spiced cranberry punch
directions: Boil cranberries in 3 quarts water for 5 minutes or until cranberries pop.
Strain into large pot and discard berries.
Add juice of oranges and lemons, sugar and spices.
Bring back to boil and serve.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix onion with sherry for 20 minutes.
Blend cheese, mayonnaise, beef and olives well.
Add onion mixture.
Serve with crackers.

title: polish stew
directions: Brown potatoes, onion and garlic in small amount of cooking oil.
Completely cook potatoes.
Add sauerkraut, tomatoes and sausage.
(Cut sausage into serving sizes.) Simmer for 30 minutes on low.
Serve.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, beat eggs, cream, salt, pepper and nutmeg with eggbeater or whisk.
With a fork, prick sides and bottom of shell every 1/2-inch to avoid shrinking or bubbling.
Make 2 to 3 layers of cheese and bacon in bottom of pie shell.
Pour egg and cream mix over this.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown and puffy.
Let cool and slice.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles.
Brown hamburger and sausage; drain. Simmer sauce, hamburger and sausage and pepperoni together for an hour or so.
Coat bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with a thin layer of sauce, one layer of noodles, 1/2 of Ricotta cheese, 1/3 of meat sauce, one layer of Mozzarella cheese.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add oil.
Add to dry mixture. Place in covered dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Take out what you need.
Put rest back in refrigerator.
Will keep for several days. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: cole slaw
directions: Finely chop cabbage and carrots.
Combine sugar, salt, pepper, milk, mayonnaise, buttermilk, vinegar and lemon juice.
Beat until smooth.
Add cabbage and carrots; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate approximately 2 hours before serving.
Refrigeration is necessary to enhance the flavor.

title: mexican meat cups
directions: Roll or pat each biscuit to 3 1/2 to 4-inch circle; turn muffin pans upside down.
Fit biscuits over well-greased backs of muffin tins.
Bake in a 400° oven for 8 or 9 minutes.
Cool and remove cups.
Brown meat, drain.
Add taco seasoning and water; heat to boiling and thick.
Put meat into biscuit cups and add sour cream, salsa, Cheddar cheese, lettuce and tomatoes.

title: pecan balls
directions: Make into small balls and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Cool 5 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Cool 5 minutes more and roll in powdered sugar again.

title: barley casserole
directions: Brown meat in cooking oil.
Mix other ingredients and add to meat.
Place in a casserole dish and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cook in low oven about 1 1/2 hours.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: asparagus spears rolled in ham
directions: Marinate asparagus spears in oil, vinegar, salt, pepper and basil for two hours.
Drain thoroughly.
Cut ham in half crosswise and wrap around asparagus spear, securing with toothpick.
(These may be prepared ahead of time and kept refrigerated until serving time.)

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt oleo in a 9 x 13-inch pan, then add soups, rice and water.
Set chicken on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll crescent roll dough.
Place in a lightly greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan, pressing edges and perforations together to line bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes or until browned.
Cool.

title: fancy chicken salad
directions: Blend curry and soy sauce with mayonnaise.
Toss together chicken, water chestnuts, grapes, pineapple and celery.
Stir in dressing, then nuts.
For attractive presentation, garnish with additional grapes and nuts.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Let cream cheese stand at room temperature until softened. In a medium sized mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Beat in sweetened condensed milk.
Add lemon juice and vanilla; stir until well mixed.
Pour filling into crust.
Chill several hours and then top with cherry pie filling.
Makes 1 pie.

title: old fashioned chicken dressing
directions: Mix ingredients in large bowl.
Stir until mushy, then pour around chicken and bake in slow oven at 350° until golden brown.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix in pint jar, salad dressing and dry ingredients.
Add vinegar and shake well.
Use for all mixed salads.

title: bread bowl
directions: Cut circle from center of bread, keeping sides intact; trim inside of bread to form bowl.
Set aside.
Cut bread removed from center into bite size pieces.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and dill dip.
Refrigerate dip overnight.
Just before serving, fill hollow portion of bread bowl.
Place bread bowl on serving platter and surround it with cut bread pieces.
Use bread as dippers.
This dip is also good with assorted raw vegetables.

title: rene's lemonade
directions: Put water in cup.
Put spoon of lemonade mix in cup.
Stir it. Drink it.

title: bermuda fruitcake
directions: Cream butter and add sugar; beat well.
Add flour (reserving 2 tablespoons) and buttermilk alternately by spoonfuls, stirring steadily.
Beat well.

title: bibb lettuce and fruit
directions: Follow package directions on dressing, using juice from mandarin oranges for the water and substitute tarragon vinegar for white vinegar.
Mix well and refrigerate.
Combine lettuce, chopped onion, oranges, strawberries and tomatoes.
Add dressing to lettuce and fruit when serving.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Oven temperature to 350°.
Oil or grease the pan, a Bundt or tube pan or smaller ones.

title: tea punch
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill and serve over ice.

title: delicious chicken breast
directions: Salt and pepper breast; wrap each with slice of bacon.
Place chicken in casserole dish.
Combine mushroom soup and sour cream. Pour over chicken.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours.
Do not bake at any higher temperature.
Serve over rice.
(Skin chicken breast before cooking.)

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour peaches over first mixture, juice and all.
Mix together sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle on top of peaches.
Mix together sour cream and egg yolks.
Pour over everything.
Bake for 20 more minutes.

title: like kentucky fried dressing
directions: Mix all together and keep in refrigerator.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar in warm water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and let stand in refrigerator at least 6 hours or overnight.
Dough will keep in refrigerator several days.

title: onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Add remaining ingredients, pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat sugars and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add and beat in egg and vanilla.
Combine flour, soda, salt and spices.
Add this to the margarine mixture.
Mix in well. Stir in oats, pecans and drained raisins.
Drop by rounded teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes for chewy cookie, 10 to 11 minutes for crisp cookie.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes approximately 4 1/2 dozen.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Mix in a bowl the soups, sour cream and chilies.
Fold in chicken and olives.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spread enough sauce to keep tortillas from sticking.
For each tortilla, spread 1 spoonful sauce and cheese.
Roll up and place in pan.
Spread remaining sauce over tortillas.
Add cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind and mix altogether.

title: breakfast blizzard
directions: In blender, combine all ingredients; blend until smooth, about 45 seconds.
Pour into 12-ounce glass and enjoy.

title: lemon angel squares
directions: Bake and cool cake as directed on package.
Pour boiling water on gelatin; stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Refrigerate until thickened, but not set.
Add enough cold water to lemonade concentrate to make 2 cups.
Stir into gelatin; beat until foamy. Beat whipping cream in chilled bowl until stiff.
Fold into gelatin.

title: beef curry
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Put potatoes and carrots in beef mixture with one cup of water.
Cook together with salt and pepper.
Thicken flour with water.
Add curry powder to this. Serve over rice.

title: burnt sugar cake
directions: Note:
Burnt sugar is made by heating white sugar in skillet until it melts and becomes liquid.

title: red potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes with peeling.
When cool, dice and mix with remaining ingredients.

title: ham and cheese crescent buns
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 8 muffin cups.
Combine first 4 ingredients and set aside.
Separate rolls into 8 triangles. Spoon ham mixture on dough and top with 1/4 teaspoon butter. Wrap dough around mixture and press edges together.
Place in muffin pan.
Bake for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: walnut-raisin bread
directions: Day Before:
Add vinegar to milk; let stand.
Start heating oven to 350°.
Grease well and lightly flour 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda and sugar.
Then stir in egg, molasses and milk mixture all at once. Fold in oats, raisins and walnuts.
Turn at once into prepared pan.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack; wrap in Saran or foil and store overnight.
Serve, sliced, with cheese.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: taco soup
directions: Do not drain juice from beans, corn, or tomatoes.

Combine browned ground meat, onion, kidney beans, ranch style beans, pinto beans, navy beans, and corn. Simmer 30 minutes. Add taco seasoning, Ranch dressing mix and water. Stir well and simmer until heated through.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Peel and slice sweet potatoes and layer in baking dish. Sprinkle with cinnamon and pour apple juice over potatoes.
Bake until potatoes are tender in 375° oven.

title: tangy mustard cauliflower
directions: Place cauliflower and water in glass bowl.
Cover.
Microwave for 9 minutes on High.
Drain.
Combine mayonnaise, onion, mustard and salt.
Spoon over cauliflower, then sprinkle with cheese. Microwave on Medium-high for 2 minutes.
Let stand 2 minutes before serving.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl, tossing to coat. Cover and refrigerate 8 hours.
Yield:
6 cups.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except mushrooms.
Set aside. Wash and stem mushrooms, then stuff.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. May be prepared and frozen.
Bake while still frozen.

title: layer salad
directions: Layer vegetables in oblong dish.
Break up green peas; do not thaw.
Cover vegetables with the cup of Miracle Whip.
Spread. Sprinkle Cheddar and bacon bits on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix cocoa, flour, salt and sugar thoroughly.
Then add water a little at a time to make a thick smooth paste.
Add rest of water. Place over medium heat and cook until thick gravy.
Serve over biscuits or pancakes.

title: applesauce cake(my favorite)
directions: Heat applesauce in large pan; add margarine and sugar.
Let melt; set aside to cool.
Sift flour with spices and salt into large bowl; stir in soda to applesauce mixture.
Add mixture to sifted ingredients.
Mix thoroughly with spoon.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° in large tube or pound cake pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let cool in pan before remaining.
After cooling, add rum or wine, if desired.
Cake is better if stored for a while. Makes a good holiday cake.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Melt margarine, beat eggs and combine with sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° until brown; reduce heat to 350°.
Cook until firm in middle.

title: so easy meal in one
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Form into patties and brown on each side in a small amount of oil.
Place the patties in a greased baking dish, then pour the soup and water over the patties.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: creamed corn
directions: Add all ingredients to 5-quart crock-pot.
Cook on low for 5 hours or so; high for 3 hours.

title: lasagna in a bun
directions: Cook ground beef until brown; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce. Cook, covered, over low heat 5 minutes.
Uncover.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes longer, stirring frequently.
In a bowl, combine egg and cheeses.

title: cornbread skillet casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; set aside.
Brown ground beef; drain and set aside.
Pour half of first ingredients into pan. Sprinkle evenly with beef.
Top with cheese, onion, and pepper. Pour remaining batter over top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 - 50 minutes.

title: all-round icing
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water.
Cook to soft boil stage. Pour slowly over beaten egg whites, beating constantly.
Add vanilla.
Beat until almost cold and stiff enough to hold its shape.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Alternate with buttermilk.
Mix well.
Add hot water.
Bake at 350°.
Makes 36 cupcakes or 3 large layers.

title: inez watson's green tomato pickles
directions: Mix vinegar, salt, sugar and hot pepper.
Combine and heat. Add tomatoes, onion and bell pepper.
Bring to a boil, but don't let boil.
Pack in hot jars and seal.
Let ripen for 4 to 6 weeks. Delicious, especially with fish.

title: recipe for happiness
directions: Sprinkle generously with kindness and plenty of faith.
Mix well.
Very good when served over a period of a lifetime and served to everyone you meet.

title: frankfurter bake
directions: Cook
noodles
and
drain.
Stir in cheese, milk, oleo, flour and
salt.	Pour
in
greased baking dish.	In bowl, mix hot dogs, brown sugar, mayo and mustard.
Spoon over noodles. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: zesty refreshing fruit punch
directions: Combine juices and Seven-Up in a punch bowl.
Add sherbet and sliced oranges.
Add ice cubes just before serving and stir.

title: super bean soup
directions: Open all 6 cans.
Empty into 2-quart kettle.
Heat to boiling. Serve. Delicious quick meal with fresh bread.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Bring to boil the first 4 ingredients and cool.
Mix sugar and flour; pour first mixture over this and beat.
Add eggs, buttermilk and soda to other mixture and beat.
Pour into long baking pan. Cook at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Fix gelatin as per directions on envelope.
Combine all other ingredients.
Mix well.

title: cheesy bacon bites
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, bacon pieces, onion and black pepper together; set aside.
Divide crescent rolls into 4 sections.
Pinch seams together and roll dough into desired thickness.
Spread the cheese mixture on dough and roll up, jelly roll style.
Slice and bake on lightly greased baking sheet at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until done.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Place pecans in a bowl.
Sprinkle with salt and add water to cover pecans.
Soak for 30 minutes, stirring twice.
Drain on paper towels for 2 hours.
Place on large cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for about 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes and watching carefully to keep from burning.

title: spicy rice
directions: Cook bacon until crisp, drain, crumble and set aside.
Cook rice in water according to package directions and set aside. Saute onion, celery and carrots in margarine until tender but firm.
Add peas and saute two additional minutes.
Add rice, bacon and seasonings and stir over medium heat two to three minutes. Add small amount of water if needed to moisten.
Serves 4.

title: hollywood chicken
directions: In a large skillet, cook hamburger with onion until hamburger is brown; drain. Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Pour into casserole and heat in a 350° oven until bubbly.

title: artichokes "iced" with caviar
directions: Cut drained artichokes into small pieces.
Drain again.
Mound artichokes in the center of large serving platter.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, sour cream and onion.
Beat until smooth. "Ice" (spread) artichoke mound with cream cheese mix.
Sprinkle caviar on top.
Garnish with chopped parsley.
Serve with butter flavored crackers.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together sugar, shortening and eggs.
Stir in milk or buttermilk and bananas.
In separate bowl, combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Combine with sugar mixture.
Stir in nuts. Let stand 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli about 5 minutes and drain.
Mix together soup, egg, cheese and mayonnaise.
Fold in broccoli.
Spread in baking dish sprayed with vegetable spray.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Make up dough.
Divide into parts.
Place on wax paper with little flour.
Roll in log shape.
Roll in wax paper.
Chill. Slice size of Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes on baking sheet.

title: fish casserole
directions: Precook fish 10 minutes in water, salt, pepper and onion flakes or celery seed.
Mix Ritz crackers, crumbled, with margarine and cheese.

title: pineapple no-cook pie
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese together.
Fold in topping, pineapple and nuts.
Put in graham cracker crust and chill.

title: sparkling juice with fruit kabobs
directions: In 2-quart pitcher, combine juice and soda.
On each of 6 wooden skewers, place assorted pieces of fruit.
For each serving, place 1 fruit kabob in each glass.
Pour juice over fruit kabob; serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: baby food pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in tube pan.
While hot, glaze cake with the following.

title: cauliflower with cheese
directions: Pull cauliflower apart and cook with just enough water to cover.
Cook about 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Brown flour in butter, add milk and cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Place cauliflower in shallow serving bowl and pour cheese sauce over it.
Serve hot.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: In small saucepan, combine pineapple with juice, sugar, cider vinegar, flour and egg.
Stir over medium flame until thickened. Refrigerate until cooled.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars well.
Add remaining ingredients. Drop by
rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and pepper.
Add soups and drained noodles. Mix and pour into casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: best corn bread
directions: Melt the butter in a pan.
Mix the eggs, corn, corn bread mix and sour cream or plain yogurt.
Pour in pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until brown.

title: sour cream banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add beaten eggs.
Thoroughly mash bananas and add to butter-sugar mixture.
Sift flour with soda, baking powder and salt; add to banana mixture.
Fold in sour cream, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Combine wheat germ, bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Mix egg and milk.
Peel eggplant and slice into 1/2-inch slices.
Dip eggplant slices in egg mixture, then in bread crumb mixture. Place in a single layer on oiled baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Turn and bake 10 more minutes.
Layer eggplant in casserole; top with sauce, then cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, covered.
Bake for 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: lemon-lime congealed salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with water and pineapple juice.
Let it barely thicken, then add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Place in refrigerator until just before serving time.
(I use Dream Whip or Cool Whip sometimes.)

title: sizzling pinwheels
directions: Trim crusts from bread.
Flatten each slice by rolling lightly with rolling pin.
Beat together cream cheese and mustard; stir in Cheddar cheese and salami.
Spread on bread.
Roll up each slice, starting with one of the corners; cut in half.
Roll half slice bacon around each pinwheel and fasten with a toothpick.
Place on broiler pan and bake in 425° oven for 20 to 25 minutes until bacon is crisp.
Makes 40 to 60 pinwheels.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Add salt and maybe a bay leaf to the water. Use just enough water to cover pieces.
Boil until tender and remove chicken from bones.
Reserve liquid.
This is what you will use as chicken broth.
Put broth in refrigerator so that the grease will come to the top.
Let stand in refrigerator for awhile.
Combine both cans of soup (undiluted), 2 cups chicken broth (scrape grease off first) and macaroni.
Put in a long casserole dish.
Top with cheese slices.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Thaw and squeeze spinach; dry.
Mix all ingredients and form small balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: shrimp mousse appetizer
directions: Soften
gelatin in water.
Bring soup to boiling point, but do not
boil.
Melt
cream cheese and gelatin in hot soup and whip with
a
wire
whip.
Add mayonnaise, celery, onion, green pepper, salt, pepper and shrimp.
Pour into Jell-O mold. Chill overnight. Turn out onto a serving plate and serve with your favorite crackers.

title: deviled-ham reubens
directions: *For a sweeter taste, use Bavarian sauerkraut.

title: sweet-n-sour chicken wings
directions: Cut wings apart; throw away tips.
Mix together all ingredients in bowl without wings.
Use a foil pan (lasagna size) for easy clean up.
Place chicken wings in pan; pour mixture over. Toss together; marinate for 1 hour.
Cook at 375° for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours, or until browned.
Chicken will be sweet and sticky.

title: quiche muffins
directions: Put cottage cheese in food processor; beat well. Put in a large bowl. Put egg white in food processor; beat until foamy. Add to cottage cheese; mix. Add the next 5 ingredients; mix well. Stir in cheese, onions and bacon. Preheat oven to 400°; pour in greased mini muffin pans. Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: 5-hour baked stew
directions: Arrange raw meat in bottom of casserole.
Arrange celery, carrots and onions on top of meat.
Mix last 4 ingredients and pour over top.
Bake, covered, for 5 hours at 250°.
You can pop in potatoes for last 2 hours or serve with rice, or boiled or mashed potatoes.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Combine cake mix, 1 cup coconut, water and egg whites; beat 2 minutes at highest speed of electric mixer.
Reduce speed to low; beat 1 minute.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in one cup boiling water.
Add can of drained, crushed pineapple, then add frozen strawberries, 4 mashed bananas and one cup walnuts, chopped.
Mix.
Pour half of the mixture into a bowl and refrigerate until it thickens.
Then add sour cream and the rest of the dessert.
Place in the refrigerator until chilled.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and add strawberries.
Let set up slightly in refrigerator and pour on top of cream cheese mixture.
Can be made the day before serving.
Keeps very well.

title: mr. mcgill's chicken
directions: Grease a shallow baking dish and then line the bottom with 2 layers of the dried beef.
Wrap each breast with 1 strip of bacon and lay in the pan.
Mix the sour cream and soup together.
Cover the chicken with this mixture.
Cover and cook for 2 1/2 hours at 300°.
Uncover and bake for another 1/2 hour.
Serve warm.

title: wheat, corn or other rolls
directions: Mix dry ingredients cut in shortening then add buttermilk and yeast. Mix well. At this time you may 1. make them out like biscuits and bake 2. place in bowl and let rise until double punch down and make out in to rolls let rise then bake. 3. Refrigerate in covered bowl for up to 2 weeks.

title: garlic roasted chicken and potatoes
directions: About 1 1/4 hours before serving:
Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large roasting pan (about 17 1/4 x 11 1/4-inch), melt butter. Remove pan from oven.

title: hamburger zucchini
directions: Mix together and put in baking dish.
Bake
at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: In large mixing bowl, thoroughly stir together the flour and baking soda; stir in sugars and oatmeal.
Add peanut butter, butter and egg; mix with fingers if need be (with a spoon if can) until all crumbly.
Press in prepared 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Place on wire rack until cool.
Cover top with Peanut Butter Frosting.
Refrigerate until frosting is set; cut in bars.
Remove with small metal spatula.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Grind the Oreo cookies.
Mix in butter until crumbly, put 3/4 of this into regular cake pan.
Whip Dream Whip, add marshmallows and nuts.
Put over crumbs in pan.
Sprinkle rest of crumbs over this.
Chill and serve.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs; add milk and sugar.
Add butter and corn.
Pour into a greased loaf pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: Peel the shrimp, leaving only the tails attached. Reserve the shells and set aside. Sprinkle the shrimp with 1 tablespoon seasoning and 1/4 teaspoon black pepper. Use your hands to coat the shrimp with the seasoning. Refrigerate the shrimp. Heat 1 tablespoon of the oil in a large pot over high heat. When oil is hot, add the onions and garlic; saute for 1 minute. Add the reserved shrimp shells, the remaining Creole seasoning, the bay leaves, lemons, water, Worcestershire sauce, wine, salt and remaining black pepper. Stir well and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes. Remove from heat and allow to cool for about 15 minutes. Strain into a small saucepan. There should be about 1 1/2 cups. Place over high heat; bring to boil and cook until thick, syrupy and dark brown, for about 15 minutes. Makes about 4 or 5 tablespoons of barbecue sauce base. Heat the remaining 1 tablespoon of oil in a large skillet over high heat. When the oil is hot, add the seasoned shrimp and saute them, occasionally shaking the skillet, for 2 minutes. Add the cream and the entire barbecue base. Stir and simmer for 3 minutes. Remove the shrimp to a warm platter with tongs and whisk the butter into the sauce. Remove from the heat. Mound the shrimp in the center of a platter and spoon the sauce over the shrimp and around the plate. Garnish with chopped chives.

title: date balls
directions: Combine dates, butter and sugar. Heat on medium fire until melted. Add pecans and Rice Krispies. Let cool and roll into balls. Roll balls in powdered sugar.

title: caramels
directions: Mix all ingredients together into saucepan.
Boil until candy thermometer reaches 248°.
Pour into a buttered jelly roll pan; cool.
Cut into squares and wrap.
This will scorch very easily. Be sure to cook on low heat and stir continuously.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Beat the first 5 ingredients thoroughly until smooth.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Sift flour mixture into butter and sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Sprinkle salted peanuts over top and press in lightly.
Bake approximately 20 minutes in a 350° oven until golden brown.
Cut in narrow strips or squares, whichever you prefer.

title: fish with sour cream and mushrooms
directions: Cook mushrooms and onions about 3 minutes.
Spoon over fish. Mix sour cream or yogurt with Parmesan cheese; spread over mushrooms.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: date nut loaf
directions: Bake at 250° for 2 hours.
Bake over water.
Cover the first hour.
Bake in a tube pan.

title: coconut chess pie
directions: Using
electric
mixer,
mix
all ingredients in order: sugar, flour,
eggs,
oleo,
vanilla,
milk and coconut.	Mix well. Stir
coconut
in
by
hand.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour (approximately) or until a knife inserted in middle comes out clean.
This pie will make its own crust.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Crush crackers; mix with softened butter.
Spread on bottom of 8-inch round or square pan.
Cream cheese, sugar, eggs and 2 teaspoons of vanilla together until smooth.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool 10 minutes.

title: donna's meat loaf
directions: Mix and form into loaf shape.
Place in Pyrex baking dish, leaving space around meat loaf.
Pour remaining tomato sauce on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Pour melted butter over the cracker crumbs (stir well).
Spread 1/3 of the cracker crumbs on the bottom of the buttered casserole. Cover with 1/2 of the oysters (can either be cut up or whole, if you prefer the whole oyster).
Then add another 1/3 of the cracker mix and the remaining 1/2 of the oysters.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Cover all this with last 1/3 of the cracker mix. Pour the 2 cups of cream over this entire casserole.
Bake in a moderate 350° oven for about 40 minutes or until browned on top and around the edges.

title: pancakes(doug's favorite)
directions: Mix in order given.
Fry on both sides until brown.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, sugars, eggs, flour, butter, spices, milk, salt and evaporated milk.
Pour into pie shells and bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 pies.

title: candy bar cookies
directions: Cream butter; gradually add powdered sugar.
Add evaporated milk, vanilla and salt; mix well.
Blend in flour.
Roll out dough half at a time on floured surface to 12 x 8-inch rectangle.
Cut into 3 x 1 1/2-inch rectangles or 2-inch squares.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 16 minutes until lightly browned; cool.
Spread 1 teaspoon filling on each.
Top with 1/2 teaspoon icing.
Decorate with pecan half, if desired.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, salt, pepper and egg.
Shape into 4 oval patties, each about 3/4-inch thick.
Cook patties in 10-inch skillet over medium heat, turning occasionally, until brown, about 10 minutes.
Drain.
Add onion, broth and mushrooms. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until beef is done, about 10 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: In an oblong 13 1/2 x 9-inch cake pan, dump and spread cherries, then pineapple, then dry cake mix.
On top, sprinkle coconut, then pecans.
Cut margarine into pieces; place around on top.
Bake at 350° until light brown on top, about 45 minutes.

title: creative chef salad
directions: Arrange your selections attractively on the romaine and use 1 to 2 tablespoons dressing.

title: chocolate roll
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate.
Cool slightly. Stir in powdered sugar and beaten egg.
Cool. Fold in marshmallows and nuts. Stir until coated with chocolate.
Form into 2 rolls. Roll in coconut. Wrap in wax paper or foil and freeze. Slice to serve.
Keeps well in freezer for 6 months or more. Very good.

title: roasted pepper spread
directions: Place sweet peppers and jalapeno pepper on an aluminum foil-lined baking sheet.
Bake at 500° for 5 to 10 minutes or until skins look blistered, turning once.
Add onion and garlic and bake 10 minutes.
Set onion and garlic aside.
Place peppers immediately into a heavy-duty, Ziploc plastic bag.
Seal and let stand 10 minutes to loosen skins.
Peel peppers and remove and discard seeds.
Peel onion and garlic; cut onion into quarters.
Place onion, garlic and peppers into container of an electric blender. Process until smooth.
Stop once to scrape down sides.

title: chicken "crumblies"
directions: Put chicken breasts in bottom of 9 x 13 pan.
Top each breast with a slice of cheese.
Mix soup and milk and pour over chicken. Top with crumbled dressing mix, then pats of butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: skillet peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and evaporated milk in an electric skillet.
Set heat control to 280°; bring to boil.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Turn off heat.
Add marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until marshmallows and peanut butter are melted and blended.
Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Yield:
2 pounds.

title: 5-layer salad
directions: In a 9 x 9-inch Tupperware container, layer ingredients in order.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Do not mix.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Brown sausage in pan; pour off grease and add cheese to sausage until melted.
Pour into bowl.
Add Bisquick and stir. Roll into 1-inch balls, place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: nacho chip dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and spread evenly on pan or plate.
Top with remaining ingredients.

title: pineapple upside-down dessert
directions: Melt 1 stick butter in oblong cake pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar over melted butter.
Top with pineapple (drained).
Prepare white cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over mixture in cake pan.
Bake for 30 to 38 minutes or until knife stuck in middle comes out clean.
Invert on cake sheet and serve.

title: blueberry muffins(yields 12 servings)
directions: Grease bottom of 12 muffin cups.
Beat egg.
Stir in milk, blueberries and oil or applesauce.
Stir in remaining ingredients until moist.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: seasons dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: tasty taco pie
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Stir in tomato sauce and seasoning mix.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Press dough into bottom and sides of ungreased 12 inch pizza pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cover with meat mixture; top with process cheese.
Continue baking until cheese begins to melt.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Serve with sour cream, if desired.

title: oven "fried" salmon cakes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray cookie sheet with vegetable cooking spray.
Beat egg with a fork in a medium-size bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix until well blended.
Shape in eight 1/2-inch thick patties.
Place on prepared cookie sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes, turning once, until golden on both sides.

title: butterfinger cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt.
Cream margarine and egg together. Stir in candy chips and dry ingredients.
Add vanilla and blend well.
Chill dough for 30 minutes.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: beef "n" tater bake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and pat mixture into 8-inch square baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; drain.

title: swift chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill and serve on lettuce beds. Makes 2 quarts of chicken salad.

title: lo-cal broccoli quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine eggs, milk, onion, salt and thyme.
Layer broccoli and cheeses in crust.
Pour egg mixture over broccoli and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: debra's "best yet" meat loaf
directions: Measurements may vary according to personal taste.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand in refrigerator until firm.
Roll into a ball.
Keep refrigerated.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken and onion until tender.
Mix 1/2 cup of each cheese and sour cream together.
Heat tortillas, one at a time, just enough to make them flexible.
Dip heated tortilla in salsa, coating both sides.
Place 1 tablespoon mixture in each tortilla. Add chicken and onion. Roll up and place seam side down in casserole dish.
Pour remaining salsa and cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: never-fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt.
Combine egg, water and vinegar.
Pour liquid into flour mixture all at once.
Blend with a spoon just until flour is moistened.

title: south of the border meat loaf
directions: Blend together first 8 ingredients.
Press in bottom of 9-inch square baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Drain fat.

title: el dorado casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground beef, onion and garlic salt.
Add tomato sauce, black olives and taco seasoning.
Mix separately sour cream, cottage cheese, green chiles, tortilla chips and grated cheese.

title: all american chicken & vegetable dinner
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place bag in 1 inch deep pan.
Mix water and flour, add to bag.
Mix cheese and spices sprinkle half over chicken.
Place in bag in an even layer.
Mix vegetables with remaining spice mixture; arrange on top of chicken.
To seal double fold open end of bag.
Place pan in oven.
Cook 55 to 65 minutes.
Make sure chicken is done.
Use oven mitts and a knife to cut bag open.
Fold back top for steam to escape.

title: whole wheat prune muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add prunes. Combine milk, egg and melted shortening.
Stir in dry ingredients. Fill muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: joyce's homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla; beat well.
Mix in evaporated milk.
Pour into freezer can.
Fill to fill line with milk.
Freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: easy jello salad
directions: Sprinkle Jell-O over cottage cheese slowly, stirring constantly.
Add pineapple, then Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: e z fudge
directions: In large pot, mix sugar and milk.
Bring to a rolling boil; boil for 6 minutes.
Put rest of ingredients in large bowl.
Pour milk mixture over chips and nut mixture; mix thoroughly and pour into a greased pan.
Cool; cut into squares.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: walnut cheese log
directions: Beat cheeses, margarine and salt together until smooth.
Stir in half the walnuts; all the pimiento and olives.
Chill mixture for easy handling; shape into log or ball.
Roll in remaining walnuts; chill until firm.
Serve with crackers.
Makes about 1 1/2 pounds of spread.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix together and press in a large cake pan.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Place bread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with sausage and sprinkle with cheese.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Pour over items in pan.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: stained glass salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Fold bananas in last.
Chill. This is a very good hurry up salad.

title: squaw bread
directions: To every cup of flour (unsifted flour), add 1 level soup spoon baking powder. Sprinkle with salt and let stand 30 minutes. Roll out on floured board. Let stand 30 minutes. Cut and cook in deep fat.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend cream cheese, marshmallow cream, orange juice and orange extract.
Put into a bowl and chill.
Great for strawberries.

title: marshmallow bars
directions: Melt butterscotch bits and butter in saucepan, stirring constantly.
Cool and add flour, brown sugar, baking powder, salt, flavorings and egg.
Fold in marshmallows, chocolate bits and nuts. Spread into 9-inch square pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.
The center will be jiggly, but becomes firm with cooling.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Set aside to cool.
Combine graham crackers with butter or margarine and powdered sugar.
Mix this together until it gets like corn meal.
Line the bottom only of 1 large pan (9 x 13-inch cake pan) with this mixture.

title: homemade butter
directions: Mix ingredients (at room temperature) in mixer.
Blend until well mixed.
Pour into bowls.
Place in freezer until firm.
Keep in refrigerator until used.

title: greek pizza
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil over medium heat. Add onion and garlic. Saut for 5 minutes. Add spinach and saut until all excess moisture has evaporated. Add basil, oregano, lemon juice and pepper. Mix well. Cool. Place length of fillo across width of buttered 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking dish. Use 10 sheets of fillo dough, brushing every two with melted butter or margarine. Overlap each set of fillo sheets at the center. At the edges of the baking dish, roll fillo onto itself to form "pizza crust." Brush top layer with melted butter or olive oil. Spread spinach mixture on prepared fillo sheets. Top spinach with 1/2 of the Mozzarella. Dredge tomatoes in bread crumbs and arrange on top of Mozzarella. Top with remaining Mozzarella and Feta cheese. Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Heat butter, cocoa and cola to boiling point.
Pour over confectioners sugar and nuts.
Beat together.
Frost cake while still warm.

title: superbowl dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on the bottom of a baking pan.
Layer can of chili and top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Peel and slice apples, simmer 5 minutes in apple juice.
Add cinnamon and cornstarch moistened with water, cook until thickened.
Put in pie shell and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix together milk and lemon juice.
Mix in fruit (be sure you drain all liquid from fruit).
Add nuts; then fold in whipped cream.
Pour into pie crusts and refrigerate.
Serve cold.

title: hot and tangy garlic chicken
directions: Cut chicken into thin strips, coat with mixture of 1 tablespoon of cornstarch, sherry and garlic.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all and pour into buttered Pyrex deep casserole dish.

title: baked peaches
directions: Peel and slice peaches into baking dish.
Sprinkle with sugar. Mix flour, brown sugar and butter and sprinkle over peaches. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, cocoa and milk in medium saucepan over medium-high heat.
Cook at full boil for 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Stir well. Spoon by tablespoons onto wax paper.
Cool.

title: corn soup
directions: Combine chicken, onion and spices.
Boil until chicken is fully cooked; drain.
Discard onion and spices.
Break the chicken into small pieces and add to corn mixed with 1 can water in saucepan.
Dissolve cornstarch in water and stir into soup.
Bring to a boil and stir in beaten eggs.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Place sauerkraut in strainer.
Wash with cold water and drain well.
Combine kraut, onion, celery, pepper and pimentos in large bowl.
Mix well.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time. Add milk, vanilla, orange flavoring, alternating with flour.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: cream sickle cake(bundt style is the prettiest. serves 8 to 10.)
directions: Follow directions on the box.

title: tyler pie
directions: Mix sugars and cornstarch.
Add milk and cook a little.
Add butter and egg yolks.
Bring to a good boil.
Remove from fire and add beaten egg whites, vanilla and nutmeg.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° until firm and brown, about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: christmas rainbow cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) round cake pans.
Prepare white cake mix according to package directions and bake.
Cool 15 minutes.
Make holes in cake at 1/2-inch intervals.
Dissolve raspberry Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water and pour over 1 cake. Dissolve lime Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water and pour over second cake.
Chill these 4 hours.
Stack cakes and frost with Cool Whip. Decorate with Christmas candy, if desired. Store in refrigerator until serving.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix well in saucepan.
Cook until it forms a soft ball.
Add peanut butter, marshmallow cream and 7 ounce package chocolate chips.
Stir until all is mixed together.
Pour in greased pans. Cool and cut into squares.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate 24 hours in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: turkey bake and cheese swirls
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Cook and stir green pepper and onion in shortening in 2-quart saucepan until tender.
Stir in 1/4 cup baking mix.
Add soup, gradually stir in milk.
Heat to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute. Stir in turkey and peas.
Pour into oblong baking dish (12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inches).

title: spiced tea
directions: In saucepan combine sugar, water, lemon rind, cinnamon, orange rind and cloves.
Bring to boil and hold for 10 minutes.
Remove cinnamon sticks.
Stir in fruit juice.
Bring remaining water to boil.
Pour over tea and let stand 10 minutes.
Strain or remove tea bags and add to fruit juices, chill.
Serve over ice.

title: microwave pork chops
directions: In microwave dish, place paper towel.
Cover pork chops with other ingredients (shake in the bag); place in dish fat side out. Cover with Saran Wrap.
For each chop, allow 3 minutes cooking time.
Example:
For 4 chops, allow 12 minutes.
Remove and put in pan for oven.
Remove paper towel and replace with new for each set of chops fixed.
Put water in pan and place in regular oven to steam for as long as you like, covered.

title: dump cake
directions: In an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan, dump the fruit and stir. Sprinkle in the dry cake mix over the top of the fruit.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Slice margarine and arrange on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until top is light brown and crumbly.

title: pound cake
directions: Coat bottom and sides of an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan with cooking spray and dust with 1 teaspoon flour.
Cream sugar and margarine at medium speed in an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add egg whites; beat 4 minutes at medium speed or until well blended.
Add vanilla and lemon extracts; beat at low speed until well blended.

title: popcorn crumble
directions: Mix popcorn and nuts in large bowl and set aside.
Combine sugar, margarine and corn syrup in heavy saucepan.
Bring to boil; stir constantly and cook to 300° on candy thermometer.
Add vanilla and quickly pour over popcorn mixture.
Stir to coat well and spread on buttered cookie sheet to harden.

title: broccoli-walnut casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; place in casserole.
Melt 1/2 cup margarine and 4 chicken bouillon cubes.
Stir flour and add milk; cook
until thickened.
Pour over broccoli.
Melt 1/4 cup margarine and stir in walnuts and 2 cups seasoned dressing.
Place on broccoli. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken bits
directions: Soak chicken pieces in a mixture of the egg and milk for a few hours.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter an 8 x 8-inch baking dish. In skillet, melt butter.
Drain chicken and dredge in bread crumbs. Saute in butter. When all is browned, place in baking dish. Sprinkle with mushrooms and cheese.
Pour bouillon over and bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix ingredients; pour in a gallon jug.
Finish filling jug with water.
Shake.
Make one gallon or 30 punch cups.

title: coffee crumb cake
directions: Mix together the sugar, flour, margarine and cinnamon until it lumps like pastry.
Remove 1 cup of crumbs for topping.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Season beef and brown with onion.
Mix soups and milk with chili peppers and taco sauce.
Heat in saucepan.
Mix with meat. Quarter tortillas.
Dip in hot bacon fat, barely long enough to soften.
Layer tortillas, meat sauce and cheese alternately, ending with cheese.
Bake at 300° for one hour, in a 4-quart dish.

title: icebox pickles
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Combine rest of ingredients and pour over cucumber mixture.
Do not heat.
Put all ingredients in glass jars or containers.
Cover and store in refrigerator.
Best when cucumbers are in season and good for weeks.
Makes 18 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados in medium bowl with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco mix in a bowl.

title: cinnamon oatmeal rolls
directions: Cook oatmeal in water.
Add brown sugar, butter and salt. Cool.
Dissolve white sugar and yeast in 1/3 cup water.
Add to oatmeal mixture.
Add the slightly beaten eggs and the flour and cinnamon.
Knead.
Let rise, then form into rolls.
Let rise again. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 1/2 to 3 dozen rolls.

title: english muffin loaf(one-rise microwave recipe)
directions: In large bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour, undissolved yeast, chives, sugar, salt and baking soda.
Heat water and sour cream until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add to dry ingredients; beat well. Stir in remaining flour to make soft dough.
Grease 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch microwave safe loaf pan; sprinkle with cornmeal.
Turn dough into prepared pan; top with additional cornmeal.
To rise; microcook uncovered on Medium (50% power) for 1 minute.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Repeat cooking and resting 1 to 2 times until dough doubles in size.
To bake, microcook on High (100% power) for 4 to 6 minutes or until top is no longer moist.
(Crust will be pale.) Let rest 5 minutes in pan.
Remove from pan.
Cool on wire rack. Slice and toast to serve.
Tested in a 600 to 700 watt microwave oven.

title: bair's delight
directions: Combine all ingredients and let stand several hours.
Serve over fresh salad.

title: seethed potatoes of 1916
directions: Place in cast-iron pot with small amount of water.
Cook over low heat 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: sweet-sour bean salad
directions: Cook the frozen lima beans until fork-tender.
Combine drained beans with chopped celery, onion, green pepper and pimentos. Combine sugar, vinegar and oil in a saucepan; bring to boil.
Add salt and seasoned salt; set aside to cool.
Pour dressing over salad.
Refrigerate and stir occasionally.
Prepare this salad the day before using.
Serve with slotted spoon.

title: orange glazed cheesecake
directions: In a small bowl, combine zwieback crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar, cinnamon and melted butter.
Press on bottom and 1.5 inches up side of an 8-inch spring-form pan.
Refrigerate.

title: 3 minute dumplings
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Beat egg and add chicken broth and add to dry ingredients.
Drop batter the size of a walnut into boiling liquid.
Cover and cook 1 1/2 minutes; turn carefully with fork and cook 1 1/2 minutes longer.

title: frozen cheese salad
directions: Mix cheese with salt, mayonnaise and lemon juice, then add pineapple, sliced bananas, nut meats and cherries.
Fold in whipped cream and pour into freezing tray.
When frozen, serve in slices on crisp lettuce leaves.
Garnish with fresh fruit, preferably strawberries.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend all ingredients. Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; pick off from bones.
Cut in small to medium pieces. Mix in rest of ingredients.
Pour in greased pan, 2-inches deep. Bake 45 minutes or 1 hour at 375°.

title: classic banana pie
directions: Slice and cover bananas with lemon juice in bowl.

title: gina's sugar cookies
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla; set aside. Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend into sugar and egg mixture.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Roll dough out into 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into desired shapes.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes or until golden brown. Drizzle colored powdered sugar over for icing.
Makes 4 dozen 3-inch cookies.

title: sour cream noodles
directions: Cook noodles in broth and bouillon cubes until done; drain. Do not rinse.
Add to sour cream, oleo and poppy seed in a greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tex-mex cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease 8-inch square baking pan. Combine all ingredients in order listed; blend well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place one crust in glass pie plate.

title: frosted salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water; add Upper 10 When it begins to thicken,
add
bananas,
marshmallows
and pineapple; congeal. Sift
flour
and
sugar; add egg and pineapple juice.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Cool and add whipped cream.
Frost salad.
Sprinkle with cheese on top.

title: apple pie spices
directions: Put all ingredients in a spice grinder or blender.
Process until finely ground.
Store in airtight container.

title: cheese hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix parsley and onion; set aside.
Stir remaining ingredients to soft dough.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and roll in parsley mixture.
Bake on greased baking sheet about 7 minutes at 350°. Makes about 24.
Tender cheese balls wrapped in a coat of parsley and onion.
Good hot or cold.

title: lime fruit salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; mix thoroughly and cool (not in refrigerator).
Drain cherries and cut in half.
Mix all ingredients; pour into 8-inch square glass dish and chill.
Cut into 9 pieces to serve.
(I like this at Christmas because of the colors.)

title: brussels sprouts and celery in cheese sauce
directions: Saute the celery in 3 tablespoons butter.
Cook and drain the Brussels sprouts.
Make a sauce of the milk, flour and salt and pepper to taste.
Stir in the celery and sprouts.
Place all in buttered casserole.
Sprinkle top with buttered bread crumbs and paprika.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except chopped pecans.
Form into a ball.
Chill.
Roll in nuts.
Serve with various crackers.

title: cool lemon chicken salad
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, basil, juice
and peel.
Let sit 10 minutes. Add remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce lined platter.

title: shirley's biscuits
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients together.
Cut in Crisco.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix in buttermilk.
Add milk and yeast mixture to flour mixture and mix.
Store in refrigerator overnight.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef with onions and drain.
Drain beans and rinse.
Add all ingredients to cooked hamburger and simmer for 30 minutes.
You can sprinkle top each serving with crushed tortillas and grated cheese!

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Follow
directions on pudding mix to make pudding.
Add 1 cup of Cool Whip;
mix and stir well.
Using a 1 quart bowl, starting with
pudding mix, layer pudding, vanilla wafers and sliced bananas,
ending with pudding on top.
Refrigerate for several hours
before
serving.
Could
be
made
day
before serving. Dish up and top with Cool Whip.

title: hearty-hamburger soup
directions: Brown beef (drain grease).
Combine and cook ingredients until rice and barley are done.
Add any vegetables or fresh cabbage on hand.
Peppercorn and bay leaf are optional.

title: great old-fashioned peanut brittle
directions: Butter 2 large baking sheets and set aside. Butter sides of heavy 3-quart saucepan. Combine sugar, syrup, water and butter. Cook over medium heat until boiling. Stir constantly with wooden spoon and avoid splashing on sides of pan. Carefully clip candy thermometer to side of pan. Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until thermometer reaches 275° about 30 to 35 minutes. Boil mixture at moderate steady rate. Stir in nuts; continue cooking, stirring frequently, until it reaches 295° (hard-crack stage) about 15 to 20 minutes. Remove from heat and quickly sprinkle baking soda over mixture, stirring constantly. Immediately pour onto baking sheet. Candy may be stretched as it cools. Cool completely. Break into pieces. Store, tightly covered. Makes about 2/3 pound.

title: tuna salad in tomato cups
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients well and chill.
Cut a thin slice from stem end of the tomatoes.
Scoop out pulp.
Turn tomato shells upside-down to drain.
Spoon in tuna mixture.
Top with 1 thin cucumber slice and 1 stuffed olive.
Serve on lettuce.

title: broccoli-cheese salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; crumble.
Mix broccoli, bacon and cheese together.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and milk to taste.
Add bacon drippings.
Mix with broccoli, bacon and cheese. Refrigerate.

title: kima sauce(chopped meat sauce)
directions: Fry meat and onions with butter until golden brown.
Add tomato paste diluted in one cup of water.
If you use canned tomato, cut into small pieces.
Add other ingredients.
Cover and simmer until sauce thickens, about 30 minutes.
If you use beef, allow more time for cooking.
Serve this sauce over macaroni, spaghetti, rice or pilaf.

title: spicy mexican cheese dip
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Add cream cheese and Ro-Tel sausage mixture.
Cook over low heat.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Over low heat bring to a boil and let boil 10 minutes.
You must stir constantly!!
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla. Beat with a mixer for 10 minutes.
(You can beat by hand, but a mixer is easier.)
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Allow to cool.
Cut into desired size pieces.

title: steamed white rice
directions: Wash rice thoroughly.
Bring water to a boil in a large saucepan set over medium-high heat and add rice.
Bring water back to a boil, then cover, reduce heat to low and simmer for about 20 minutes or until water is absorbed.
Fluff with a fork and serve.

title: homemade "barbecue"
directions: If dry, add more broth.
If too moist, cook longer.
Eat on buns.

title: salmon divan provencale
directions: Drain salmon juice into measuring cup.
Add milk to make a total of 1 1/2 cups.
Flake salmon into large chunks and set it aside.
Cook broccoli half as long as the package directs; drain thoroughly.
Arrange the broccoli in an 8-inch diameter baking dish.
Spread salmon over broccoli.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add garlic and flour.
Cook and stir until it bubbles.
Add salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in salmon-milk mixture; cook and stir until thick.
Add cheese and tomato chunks to sauce.
Pour sauce over salmon and broccoli.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until crumbs are light brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: oatmeal refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream fat; add sugar and continue creaming.
Add eggs; sift flour, soda and salt together, then add to creamed mixture.
Add oats and vanilla.
Shape into long rolls, 1-inch in diameter. Chill; cut into slices with sharp knife.
Place on ungreased pan. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: hawaiian chicken shish kabobs
directions: Mix juice from pineapple and cherries with next 4 ingredients. Simmer and stir (marinade).
Make shish kabobs from maraschino cherries, 1-inch squared pineapple pieces, chicken, mushrooms, onion and peppers.
Grill until desired doneness, basting constantly with marinade.

title: cinnamon nut syrup
directions: Heat all ingredients, except nuts, in a 9-inch heavy skillet over medium heat to boiling, without stirring (approximately 15 minutes).
Be sure to watch carefully as this burns easily.
Stir in nuts.
Cool slightly and pour over ice cream.

title: creamy bacon pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions. Cook bacon to a crispy texture, drain, and crush. Add butter and cheese to drained pasta and toss. Add cream and bacon stirring until thickened over low heat (just a minute or two). Stir in basil. Salt and pepper to taste. Top individual servings with additional grated cheese. Serve with warm French bread.

title: soft caramel
directions: Butter 9 x 9-inch pan.
Melt butter in pan.
Add sugar and salt.
Stir thoroughly.
Stir in corn syrup.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Use a candy thermometer; heat to 245° (12 to 15 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour in pan and freeze.
Cut at room temperature.
Wrap in waxed paper.

title: 4 flavored pound cake
directions: Spray Bundt pan; dust with flour and set aside.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt, sugar, oil, applesauce and milk; beat with mixer until batter is smooth.
Add extracts; fold in 1/3 of beaten egg whites.
Gently fold in remaining beaten egg whites. Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake in 325° (preheated) oven 45 to 60 minutes.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Slice and serve with strawberries and whipped cream if desired.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: onion ring chicken
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry. Pound chicken to tenderize.
Put onion rings in bowl and crush. Add Parmesan cheese and salt.
In a separate bowl, put beaten egg and milk. Dip chicken pieces in egg, then in onion ring mixture.
Place chicken in baking dish. Pour melted margarine over all pieces and top with any remaining onion ring mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 4.

title: sixty minute rolls
directions: Put yeast into 1/4 cup warm water until dissolved.
Mix all ingredients; set in a warm place (add enough flour to make soft dough).
Cover for 15 to 20 minutes.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in pan to bake in.
Roll out dough 1/2-inch thick; cut with biscuit cutter.
Dip in melted butter and fold over half.
Let rise until light.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.
Makes 20 rolls.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown steak in shortening.
Add celery, onion, soy sauce, molasses and water.
Cook 45 minutes.
Stir in soup, flour, salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve on rice; top with noodles. Yields 10 servings.

title: butter tarts
directions: Mix all ingredients, except currants.
Simmer, stirring quite often.
Roll pie dough and cut in circles (large) to fit either cup cake or muffin tins.
Put in 1 heaping teaspoon of currant into each and 1 spoon liquid over currants until 2/3 full.
Cook 25 minutes at 350°.

title: special k cookies
directions: Cook sugar and Karo (with lid on) until comes to a boil. Remove from heat.
Add 1 cup of the cereal.
Add peanut butter; stir until smooth, then add remaining cereal.
Stir until well mixed.
Form into small balls on wax paper; flatten out.
Make indention in top of each cookie for Chocolate Mixture.

title: marshmallow marble top fudge
directions: Cover bottom of square pan with foil.
Set aside.
In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate chips and 2 tablespoons butter with sweetened condensed milk, vanilla and salt.
Remove from heat, stir in nuts.
Spread evenly in prepared pan.

title: bar-b-que sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat to blend well.
For Chicken and pork chops: dip meat pieces into the sauce.
Place on baking pan and cover with aluminum foil.
Cook for 45-minutes to 1-hour or until juices run clear.
Uncover and return to oven for 15 minutes to reduce liquid in pan.
For pork roast, partially cook meat, drain off fat, then cover with sauce and complete cooking. For cooked chopped meat: stir sauce into meat and heat.

title: eye-talian chicken
directions: Bread chicken breasts, fry thoroughly; set aside.
Start the tomato sauce (low or medium heat).
Start the angel hair pasta (boil the water).
Saute the olive oil, chopped garlic, tomato and spinach; set aside.
When tomato sauce is heated, turn heat to low; slowly stir in heavy cream.
Broil chicken breasts with Mozzarella cheese on top until cheese melts.
Drain oil off of sauteed vegetables.
Drain pasta.
On plate:
Put angel hair pasta 1st, sauteed vegetables 2nd, chicken breasts with Mozzarella 3rd and cover with the pink sauce.

title: lush
directions: Press together in a 9 x 13 pan. Bake 12 minutes at 350°; cool.

title: sweet potato pone pie
directions: Combine first seven ingredients; beat until just smooth.
Pour filling into pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 325° and bake another 30 minutes or until set.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in bottom of dish. Cover with soup, then slice eggs and pour over broth. Mix flour, sweet milk, baking soda, salt and oleo. Pour this mixture over the soup and eggs. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: diet malt
directions: Mix all in blender and you have a delicious malt made with half the calories.

title: christmas morning
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate for 12 hours.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cherry cake
directions: Mix all in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Cut in bite-size pieces, cook broccoli in chicken broth until tender.
Arrange in greased dish as follows:
broccoli, then chicken (mix soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice together).
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Use a little milk to make mixture pour better.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with Ritz crackers and butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb crumb tart
directions: For crust, mix flour, baking powder and powdered sugar in a medium bowl.
Cut in oleo until it forms coarse crumbs.
Add egg and milk; stir until a ball forms.
Pat into a greased 11 x 7-inch baking pan.
Place rhubarb in crust; sprinkle with Jell-O.
In small bowl, mix the 1/2 cup flour, 1 cup sugar and 1/3 cup oleo together until crumbly.
Sprinkle over rhubarb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Allow to cool until firm.

title: peanut butter logs
directions: Core apple without piercing through the bottom.
Pour some cinnamon red hots into the core.
Place in a small cup or dish. Cook on High for 2 minutes or until apple is almost tender.
Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: cranberry waldorf salad
directions: Grind the cranberries; combine with sugar and marshmallows overnight.
Add apples, grapes, walnuts and salt.
Fold in whipping cream.

title: homemade cracker jacks
directions: Mix popcorn and peanuts in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Keep warm in a 250° oven.
Melt butter, sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Cook 5 minutes without stirring. Remove from heat. Stir in baking soda and vanilla.
Quickly pour over popcorn and peanuts. Toss until well coated. Spread in shallow pan and bake at 250° for 45 minutes. Break into pieces and put in covered container.

title: blueberry muffin squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease well a 9 x 9 x 1 3/4-inch baking pan.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt and set aside.
In medium bowl, with mixer at high speed, beat shortening, sugar, egg and vanilla until well blended.
Add milk; blend at low speed until combined.
Add flour mixture and beat one minute longer.
With rubber scraper, gently fold in blueberries.
Turn batter into pan. Bake 30 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Good warm or cold.
(If you use an 8 x 8-inch pan, bake a little longer.)

title: a friendly recipe
directions: Blend together and serve generous portions to everyone you meet.

title: harlequin ham
directions: Make sauce of first 3 ingredients (add salt and pepper to taste).
Stir in mayonnaise and remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake at 350° until hot through.
Then add bread crumbs dotted with butter and brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fiesta stack-ups
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients, except beans, and simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add beans and heat thoroughly.

title: butterscotch cheese cake bars
directions: Melt butter and morsels in medium pan over low heat.
Stir in crumbs and nuts.
Press half of mixture into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in egg, milk and vanilla.
Pour into crumb mixture.
Top with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes (325° for glass).
Cool at room temperature and chill.
Make a day ahead or earlier and freeze.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1 cup of pecans, making sure the pineapple is drained well.
You will not use the juice.
Roll and shape into a ball, then roll the ball over the remaining 1 cup of pecans to cover the ball.
Refrigerate.
Great on crackers.

title: carrot lyonnaise
directions: Cook carrots in broth 10 minutes.
Melt 1/4 cup butter.
Add onions and saute 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and water.
Bring to boiling.
Add carrots and stock.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: easy stromboli
directions: Unroll dough; place on greased cookie sheet.
Press dough into 12 x 8-inch rectangle.
Spread sauce on dough within 2-inches of long sides and 1/2-inch of short sides.
Top with ham, cheese, peppers and Italian seasoning.
Fold long sides of dough over filling; pinch to seal.
Pinch short sides to seal.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: frozen slaw
directions: Chop cabbage.
Add salt; let stand 1 hour.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Break spaghetti into 3 or 4 pieces.
Cook as directed.
Drain and rinse well.
Mix all together.
Best to set a day.

title: haystacks
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Let boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat, add 1/2 cup peanut butter, 3 cups oatmeal and 1/2 cup coconut (if desired).
Stir well. Spoon onto cookie sheet and chill.

title: good potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water, when soft rub through a strainer. There should be 2 1/2 c.

Scald milk with onion, remove the onion and slowly whisk milk into potatoes. Melt half of the butter and add flour, salt, celery, salt and pepper. Stir until well mixed in seperate pan, then stir into the hot soup. Boil for 1 min. then add remaining butter.
Serves 4-6

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix butter, 2 cups flour and powdered sugar.
