Pat into greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes. Beat eggs, sugar, 4 tablespoons flour, lemon juice and salt together; pour over hot crust. Bake 25 minutes (do not overbake; it should just be firm). When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water and set aside.
In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in milk until well blended.
Gently stir in gelatin.
Add pineapple and mix well. Chill.
When mixture begins to thicken, fold in whipped topping. Pour into 2 1/2-quart mold.
Allow to set, then serve 8 to 10 loved ones and friends.

title: sugar-free banana bread(everyone eats it and enjoys it.)
directions: Combine oil, butter, milk, dates, bananas and egg in blender; blend and set aside. Sift together remaining ingredients. Mix wet and dry, then stir in 1/2 cup raisins and some chopped nuts. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes and cool 10 minutes in pan before removing.

title: baked cheese grits
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Prepare grits according to directions on package.
Add to beaten eggs, slowly.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until top is set and light and fluffy.
Let stand about 5 minutes before serving. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: jo-ann's apple cake
directions: Gradually add 2 cups sugar to oil and cream well.
Add 3 eggs and beat.
Mix flour and remaining dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture and beat to combine.
Add apples and nuts.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: stove top barbecue chicken
directions: Heat oil in a skillet.
Saute onion until tender.
Stir in catsup, water, vinegar, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, chili powder and celery seed.
Bring sauce to a boil.
Add chicken to skillet.
Spoon sauce over the pieces.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Turn chicken pieces and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes longer.
Can cool and freeze for a quick meal.

title: fudge icing
directions: Cook to soft ball stage.
Add vanilla and butter.
Beat until nice to spread.

title: fruit pops
directions: Will also need toothpicks, foil and ice trays.
Fill up ice tray with your favorite juice.
Cover with foil and stick toothpicks in each slot.
Let freeze and you'll have your snack.

title: sour cream fruit salad
directions: Mix together and let blend overnight.

title: cherry nut fudge
directions: Combine powdered sugar and cocoa, stir well.
Set aside and combine butter and milk in a saucepan.
Cook over low heat until butter milts.
Remove from heat and stir in cocoa mixture until smooth.
Add vanilla, cherries and pecans.
Stir well and pour mixture into a lightly greased 8 inch square pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except broccoli.
Thaw broccoli and mix together with other ingredients.
Pour into ungreased casserole dish.
Bake at 300° until bubbly, approximately 30 to 35 minutes. Can sprinkle top with extra shredded cheese.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: p-nut butter apples
directions: Core the apple and stuff with peanut butter.
Cut into circles or eat whole.

title: butter balls
directions: Cream the cheese and butter together.
Add sugar and vanilla. Mix well until smooth.
Store in refrigerator until firm.
Roll into balls and coat with chocolate.

title: blue-ribbon chicken
directions: To form a pocket, cut each chicken breast in half horizontally, almost but not all the way through.
Cut each ham and cheese slice lengthwise in half.
Place a slice of ham and cheese in each pocket.
Combine bread crumbs and paprika.
Brush chicken with melted butter, then coat with crumbs.

title: luscious lemon pie
directions: Add dry ingredients after milk, eggs, lemon juice, margarine, lemon rind and eggs are almost boiling. After filling has thickened, remove from heat.
Add sour cream.
Pour into 9-inch baked pie shell.
Cool 2 hours, then top with Cool Whip.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine 1
1/2	cups sugar,
cornstarch
and salt in a 2 quart saucepan.	Add
lime
juice, water and egg yolks;	blend well. Add
butter
and
gradually
add
boiling
water.
Bring mixture to a boil over medium heat and cook 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in lime peel and green food coloring.
Remove from heat and cool 20 minutes.
Put in shell.

title: kielbasa casserole
directions: Mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with American or Velveeta cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: oven-fried apple rings
directions: Slice apples into rings and place half in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Dot with 1/4 cup butter.
Combine sugars and spices. Sprinkle half over apples.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: sweet and sour bacon dressing
directions: Heat canola oil, fry bacon and onions.
Remove bacon, crumble, then return to pan, whisking in all remaining ingredients.

title: eid milk drink
directions: Finely sliver the dried dates.
Break vermicelli in small pieces.
Put milk to boil with vermicelli and slivered dried dates and simmer over low heat until vermicelli is cooked.
Add coconut, nuts, sugar and cardamom powder and serve in porridge bowls.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix the persimmon pulp and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, milk and vanilla flavoring.
Sift dry ingredients and add grated potato. Add to liquid mixture.
Pour in greased baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 1 hour.
Eat it hot or cold.
M-mmm good!

title: monkey bread
directions: Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cut biscuits into 4 pieces.
Roll them into the sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Drop them into a buttered Bundt pan.
Bring to a boil the sugar, brown sugar and margarine.
Pour over biscuits in pan.
When done baking, dump onto a dish right away.

title: country cornbread
directions: Combine flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt in a large bowl; mix well.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well. Add wet mix to dry mix and stir until moistened.
Pour into a well-greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 425° for 35 minutes or until tester comes clean.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip, milk and dry Jell-O. Add mandarin oranges and chill.

title: parsley potatoes(microwave)
directions: Place potatoes and water in 2-quart casserole; cover. Microwave on High (100%) until fork-tender, 12 to 15 minutes, stirring after half the time.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Drain and set aside.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths.
Put in bag with a cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Shake to coat.
Place pieces in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bring margarine and sugars to boil over low flame.
Pour over biscuit pieces.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lime punch
directions: Make Kool-Aid using 1/2 amount of water, but full amount of sugar.
Mix all ingredients except sherbet.
Put in refrigerator until almost time to serve.
Add 1 pint lime sherbet to 1 quart of punch.

title: fluffy dumplings
directions: Bring butter and milk to a boil.
Then add flour; separate eggs and add egg yolks one at a time.
Beat egg whites and add to the above.
Drop by spoonfuls onto stew, soups, etc.
Cook, uncovered, for about 20 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini until tender, drain.
Melt butter and mix with herb dressing mix.
Mix zucchini, carrots, onions, soup and salt and pepper.
Place 1/2 of dressing mix in bottom of deep casserole dish.
Pour zucchini and carrot mixture over herb mix.
Cover with rest of herb mix.
bake 1 hour at 350°. (Can cover with foil for 30 minutes, then uncover.)

title: tutti-frutti chocolate log
directions: Line a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan with aluminum foil; grease foil.
Melt chocolate chips in double boiler over hot, not boiling, water.
Beat egg yolks on high speed of mixer for 2 minutes; blend in sugar, melted chips, water and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff peaks form.
Stir 1/4 beaten egg whites into chocolate mixture; gradually fold in remaining egg whites.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 16 to 18 minutes, or until cake springs back when touched lightly in center.
Sprinkle cake with confectioners sugar.
Cover cake in pan with a towel; place baking sheet over towel and invert.
Remove pan and aluminum foil.
Starting with the 10-inch side, roll towel and cake; cool about 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, prepare Tutti-Frutti Filling.

title: meat balls in wine sauce
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk 5 to 10 minutes in a bowl.
Add beef, egg, onion, spices and 1 1/2 teaspoons salt.
Shape into balls the size of a walnut.
Heat butter in large pan and brown meat on all sides.
Add flour to drippings and stir.
Add soup, wine, evaporated milk and remaining 1 teaspoon salt.

title: egg rolls
directions: Precook chicken and cool while chopping vegetables.
Cook sausage until done and crumbly.
Drain fat.
Drain and chop water chestnuts, bean sprouts, cleaned scallions, peeled carrots and cabbage until minced fine.
Cook bacon until done and remove bacon and use bacon drippings.
Add vegetables and meat to bacon drippings and stir on low heat for 10 minutes.
While cooking, add 1/4 cup soy sauce, 3 tablespoons sugar, 1 teaspoon salt and a few shakes of pepper.
Put in refrigerator to cool enough to handle, about 1/2 hour.
Remove from refrigerator and tilt pan so juices won't stick to mixture (juice will cause egg roll skins to be soggy).
Fill skins with about 2 teaspoons filling and roll skins (put 1 beaten egg in bowl and dampen edges of skins before wrapping to seal edges).
After all skins are wrapped, deep fry in hot oil just until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
To eat, dip in soy sauce.

title: sweet potato custard(by:  eva naylor)
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until soft.
Mash up.
Add all ingredients and beat well.
Pour into pie shells and bake at 350° until pie shells are done.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Boil vinegar, sugar, salt and spices together.
Pour over zucchini and onions.
Let stand 1 hour; bring to boil and cook 3 minutes.
Pack in hot sterilized jars.
Makes 6 to 7 pints.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Make meatballs and brown in oven at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: golden graham smores
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Heat syrup, margarine and morsels to boiling, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla. Pour over cereal in bowl, toss until coated.
Fold in marshmallows, 1 cup at a time.
Press in pan with greased spoon.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Store at room temperature.
Makes 24.

title: roast turkey
directions: Cover with aluminum foil.
Cook at 400° until meat is tender, about 6 hours.

title: chicken-n-rice
directions: Melt butter in electric skillet.
Remove skin from chicken. Fry chicken in butter; salt to taste.
Remove chicken when done. Add rice and water to butter mixture.
Cook until done.
Replace chicken on top of rice.
Pour cream of chicken over all.
Simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve.

title: christmas cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries in water 10 minutes. Stir and add sugar and jello. Stir well. Cool slightly. Add remaining ingredients. Pour into bowl and refrigerate.

title: chicken creole
directions: Split chicken breasts in half lengthwise; cut into 1/2-inch cubes and set aside.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Saute onion until transparent.
Add mushrooms and cook over medium heat until liquid evaporates; then add garlic, celery and spices and cook for 1 minute.
Add pepper and cook for 2 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes and cook for about 5 minutes.
Add wine, lemon juice and hot pepper and mix.
Set aside.

title: bernie and pat's anise cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; put aside.
Next, mix eggs, oil, milk and anise together.
Add dry ingredients in as mixing.
Add extra flour if cookie dough is sticky, add milk if too dry.
Dough is very easy to work with.
Great for kids shaping into different shapes.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes until bottoms are golden. Cool on cookie rack.
Mix powdered sugar, milk and few drops of food coloring to decorate.
Recipe may be cut in half (use 1/4 cup of milk in ingredients).

title: clam dip
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Mix well and let sit overnight.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: turkey pot pie
directions: Toss turkey with flour in plastic bag.
Set aside.
In frying pan, cook onions and celery with thyme and pepper in margarine until tender.
Add carrots, water, soup, green beans and turkey. Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Split biscuits in half and place on top.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Yield: 5 servings.
Exchanges: 1 cup = 2 Meat, 1 Bread and 1 Vegetable.

title: penny's mexican lasagna
directions: Combine beef, beans, chili powder, cumin and garlic powder. Place 4 of the uncooked noodles in the bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Spread 1/2 of the beef mixture over the noodles.
Top with 4 more noodles and the remaining beef mixture.
Cover with remaining noodles.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Melt shortening and unsweetened chocolate, cool slightly. Add sugar, milk and eggs; beat well.
Combine dry ingredients, stir into mixture.
Add vanilla, nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop teaspoons onto cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°. Frost if desired.

title: easy hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into balls and deep fry in hot oil until golden brown.

title: sausage balls
directions: For spicy sausage balls, you can add ground red pepper to taste.

title: miracle whip chocolate cake
directions: Put all ingredients together in a bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 minutes in two 9-inch pans or a 9 x 12-inch pan that have been greased and floured.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt 1/2 stick margarine in casserole dish. Combine flour, milk and sugar.
Pour into dish.
Place peaches on top of mixture. Sprinkle cinnamon over top. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: easy refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in sugar, salt, shortening and egg.
Mix in flour until dough is easy to handle.
Do not knead.
Place dough in a greased bowl; turn once to grease surface.
Cover and place in refrigerator.
Will keep up to 2 weeks.
Two hours before needed, shape dough into rolls or cinnamon buns.
Cover; let rise until double (1 1/2 to 2 hours). Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: green beans sorrento(makes 6 servings)
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces.
In medium skillet with tightly fitting cover, saute bacon until lightly browned.
Add onion, garlic and green pepper.
Saute until golden.
Stir in tomatoes, green beans, oregano, salt, pepper and water; cover and simmer 13 minutes or until beans are tender-crisp.

title: barbecued meatloaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Cook beef; drain well.
Combine with other ingredients in large Dutch oven or cooking pot.
Simmer for 2 hours and serve. Will freeze well for future serving.

title: holiday cranberry fruit salad
directions: Mix Jell-O in the 1 cup boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate until set.
Keeps well for one week or more.

title: cheesy hash browns
directions: Combine soup and sour cream; fold into potatoes along with onion, cheese, salt and pepper.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle cornflake crumbs over top.
Drizzle with melted butter or margarine.
Return to oven 15 minutes.
Can use potatoes O'Brien, then omit onions.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: easy steak and gravy
directions: Fry floured cubed steak in frying pan.
Then take out and fry some onions in same pan.
Remove and drain grease.
Put steak back in pan and pour one
can of cream of celery soup and one can of cream of mushroom soup over steak.
Then put onion on top.
Put lid on and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in refrigerator for 2 hours before serving.

title: chinese-style pasta salad
directions: Prepare rotini pasta, following package directions. Meanwhile, in large nonstick skillet, heat margarine and oil over medium heat.
Add peas and cook, stirring, until brightly colored and tender.
Stir in walnuts and five spice powder.
Cook until walnuts are lightly toasted, about 2 minutes.
Toss sugar-snap pea mixture with drained cooked pasta.
Serve immediately.

title: microwave bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients and microwave for 7 minutes on High.
Place in pint jar and seal.

title: hermit cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat butter with an electric mixer on medium to high for 30 seconds.
Add about half of the flour, brown sugar, egg, milk, vanilla, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Beat till thoroughly combined.
Beat in remaining flour. Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoons 2 inches apart onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375 F for 10 minutes or till edges are lightly browned.
Cool cookies on a rack.
Makes 36.

title: giant snickerdoodles
directions: Mix 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon.
In a large bowl, mix at medium speed, oleo, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs until light and fluffy.
In separate bowl, mix flour, salt, cream of tartar and soda.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture until well blended. Refrigerate for 30 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Scald milk; stir in sugar, salt and 1/2 cup oleo.
Cool. Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in milk mixture, eggs and half of the flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add remainder of flour. Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: london broil
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add flank steak.
Marinate 8 to 12 hours.
Broil to your taste.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Line baked cooled pie shell with 2 cups of large, uncooked berries.
Make a sauce of the other 2 cups of berries, cut up and cook until thick with sugar, water, cornstarch, and salt mixed together.
Remove from heat; add butter and stir well.
Cool and pour over berries in the pastry shell.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Spread with a thick coating of whipped cream or whipped topping.
Serves 6.

title: neiman-marcus brownies
directions: Mix cake, eggs and nuts by hand and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine cream cheese, eggs and sugar and spread over cake.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: two tone crispy cereal treats
directions: In a small saucepan, combine corn syrup and butter.
Heat and stir until melted.
Divide mixture in half; transfer to 2 bowls. Quickly stir butterscotch pieces into one bowl and chocolate pieces into the other bowl until melted.
Working quickly, stir 2 cups of cereal into each mixture.
Press chocolate cereal mixture evenly into tray of Tupperware Animal Wigglers set.
Top with butterscotch mixture.
Spray cutter with nonstick coating.
Press cutter into mixture in tray.
Chill for 15 minutes.
Remove cutter from tray. Carefully remove shapes and decorate.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and milk.
Melt butter in baking dish or pan.
Pour fruit into melted butter.
Add nutmeg. Pour flour and milk mixture over fruit.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: barbecue lamb riblets
directions: Season ribs with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Place on cooking grill directly over a drip pan and cook for 50 minutes. Baste with barbecue sauce during the last 20 minutes of cooking time. Serve with additional sauce.

title: onion dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill and serve with chips.

title: play dough
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add food coloring to oil and water. Stir oil and water into dry mixture over medium heat until mixture forms a ball.
Let cool.
Knead until smooth.
Store in an airtight container.

title: instant potato sourdough bread starter
directions: Mix ingredients in glass jar or container of choice.
Cover loosely and let stand 24 hours at room temperature.
Keep in refrigerator 3 to 5 days.
The starter is now ready for making bread.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: First mix apples and sugar and set aside for 20 minutes.
Mix flour and all dry ingredients, then sift.
Add egg, oil and nuts to apple mixture.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: cauliflower pie
directions: In a large bowl, whisk buttermilk baking mix, milk, eggs and salt until blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a lightly greased 9-inch pie dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until puffed and golden. Cut in wedges and serve.
Very good, if you like quiche.

title: rhubarb crunch ala mode
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
Mix oats, flour and sugar (with 2 knives, scissor fashion).
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Place rhubarb combination in pan and top with oat mixture.
Bake 45 minutes.
Serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into casserole dish. Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: choco-peanut butter bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Mix shortening, peanut	butter,
sugars and egg.
Stir in water, flour, soda, baking powder, salt and 6 ounces chocolate morsels. Spread
in pan.
Bake about 20 minutes.
Remove from oven; immediately sprinkle remaining chocolate morsels evenly over baked
layer.
Place
baking sheet over pan so contained heat will
soften morsels.
Spread softened chocolate evenly; sprinkle with peanuts.
Cut into bars, about 3 x 1-inch.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix all preceding ingredients with a mixer on low until thick. Mix 1/2 cup of preceding mix with 1 (8 ounce) package cream cheese in blender (low speed).
Mix this with pudding mixture by hand.
Pour into already prepared pie shell; sprinkle with walnuts.
Let chill before serving.

title: cream cheese pinwheels
directions: Blend the cream cheese with milk.
Stir in salt, pepper and Tabasco.
Spread cheese mixture over slices.
Roll tightly; wrap and chill.
Before serving, cut each roll into slices.

title: merry berry holiday punch
directions: Mix together and freeze until slushy.
Add 3 cups of ginger ale just before serving.

title: quick bread
directions: Grease a 9-inch cake pan with butter or shortening.
Mix flour with milk until mixture is consistency of thick pancake batter. Pour into pan.
Set on stove burner on very low heat until puffy, then place in preheated oven at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat first 6 ingredients together.
Add others one at a time in order and beat well.
Bake 1 hour at 350° oven in well-greased and floured loaf pan.
Makes 2.

title: strawberry-banana salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except sour cream.
Put 1/2 of mixture in a 12 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Chill until firm.
Spread sour cream on first half, then spoon the remainder of mixture over the sour cream.
Chill to set.

title: cheese ball
directions: Set cream cheese out overnight.
Then combine with 2 packages of chopped beef, chopped onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Set up in a mold until good and firm.
Then roll in the remaining package of chopped beef and sprinkle with Accent.
Put Cling Wrap in container first.

title: candy turtles
directions: Arrange pecans in clusters of 3 or 4 halves, two-inches apart on a greased baking sheet.	Top each cluster with one caramel, slightly flattened.
Bake at 300° for 7 minutes or until caramels soften.
Flatten caramels and top each with 1 chocolate square while still warm.
Spread chocolate when melted.
Refrigerate until chocolate hardens.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: cranberry fruit salad
directions: Combine chopped cranberries with sugar, stirring well.
Place mixture in colander and allow to drain overnight.
Combine cranberry mixture with pineapple chunks and nuts.
Fold in whipping cream.
Chill.
Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Top with chow mein noodles.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese straws
directions: Pour melted margarine over grated cheese while margarine is still hot and stir in.
Combine other ingredients and mix into cheese.
Push through pastry tube or cookie press (star tip is suggested).
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until barely brown.
There is no need to grease baking sheet.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Beat butter and sugar until fluffy. Mixture will still be gritty at this point. Combine half and half, vanilla and salt. Heat in microwave until warm, not hot. Very gradually add the liquid to the butter, sugar mixture, beating on high. Scrape bowl in between each addition of liquid. When all the liquid has been combined, you will have the lightest buttercream frosting ever. Spread on cake and refrigerate a couple of hours before eating. It's not good until it is cold.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle pecans and coconut in bottom of pan.
Mix cake according to directions; add coconut and pecans.
Blend margarine, sugar and cream cheese; smooth over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: gulliver's corn (restaurant in l.a.)
directions: Cut corn from cob and place in saucepan with cream.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in salt and sugar. Melt butter in another pan and stir in flour (do not burn).
Stir butter and flour; pour into corn until slightly thickened.
Place into oven-proof dish.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and dot with butter.
Melt under broiler.
Makes 4 servings.

title: overnight linguine salad
directions: Cook linguine as directed on box.
Prepare other ingredients. Combine with linguine and toss.
Let stand refrigerated overnight.

title: squash patties
directions: Mix all 6 ingredients well. Drop by tablespoons into hot oleo in iron skillet in patty shape.
Fry until golden.

title: butterfinger cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg.
Stir in Butterfinger pieces and flour mixture.
Add vanilla and blend well.
Chill dough for 30 minutes.

title: pennsylvania dutch funnel cake
directions: Beat milk with egg.

Blend dry ingredients and gradually add the milk mixture, beating constantly, until batter is smooth. Holding your finger over bottom of a funnel having a 3/8 to 1/2-inch hole, fill funnel with batter.

Holding funnel as near surface of fat as possible, remove finger and drop batter into deep fat heated to 375°, using circular movement from center outward to form a spiral cake about 3-inches in diameter. Immediately replace finger on bottom of funnel and then form other cakes (as many as will float uncrowded, 2 to 2 1/2 dozen cakes). Fry until cakes are puffy and golden brown, turning once.
Remove cakes with a slotted spoon to absorbent paper to drain.
Sift confectioners sugar lightly over cakes and drizzle with molasses and serve at once.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini, celery and onion in 1 1/2 cups water until tender.
Do not drain.
Add oleo.
Cool.
Add cheese, cracker crumbs, eggs, salt and pepper.
Bake, uncovered, in greased casserole for 1 hour at 350°.

title: skillet beef and macaroni
directions: Put small amount of oil in skillet.
Brown meat.
Add all other ingredients, including noodles and let simmer for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes, covered.

title: hopping john pork chops
directions: Cook bacon in skillet until crisp; remove and crumble bacon. Add pork chops, onion and garlic to drippings in skillet.
Cook until pork chops are brown and onion is tender.
Stir in gravy and peas.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in rice.
Cook for 25 minutes or until pork chops and rice are tender, stirring occasionally.
Cook, uncovered, to desired consistency.
Top with bacon and green pepper.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: corn fritters
directions: Cut off tips of kernels, then scrape cobs to make 1 cup cut corn.
Drain fresh (or canned) corn, reserving liquid.
Add enough milk to liquid to measure 1 cup.
Sift together dry ingredients. Combine egg, milk mixture and corn. Add to dry ingredients.
Mix just until moistened. Drop batter from tablespoon into deep, hot fat (375°). Fry until golden brown, 3 to 4 minutes.
Drain on paper towels. Serve with warm maple syrup.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add milk and extract and blend.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well after each egg.
Beat entire mixture well before pouring into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hominy bake
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into buttered dish.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: red cake
directions: Make paste and set aside red food coloring, water and Nestle Quik.

title: cheezy potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes or until golden brown. Serves about 8.

title: creamy fudge
directions: Mix the sugar, evaporated milk and the butter and boil and stir constantly to a soft ball stage, about 5 minutes.
Next, add the chocolate chips and the marshmallow cream.
Stir until dissolved.
Do not beat.
Add nuts and pour into a buttered dish.

title: mildred's christmas salad
directions: Dissolve gelatine in water.
Combine with pineapple, sugar and lemon juice.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add cream cheese and pineapple cheese spreads.
Stir until dissolved and blended.
Add whipping cream.
Pour into 13 x 19-inch dish and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
May garnish with red or green maraschino cherries if making for Christmas.

title: chocolate macaroons
directions: Melt together shortening and chocolate.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add sugar to chocolate, stirring until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Add flour mixture; blend thoroughly. Chill dough 2 to 3 hours.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Mix sugar and vinegar until sugar dissolves. Add mayonnaise and stir until creamy.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Pour sauce over macaroni and mix well.
Let set for a while and keep refrigerated.

title: heavenly hash candy
directions: Mix together sugar and chocolate.
Add milk, Karo and salt. Stir well and cook until a soft ball can be formed when dropped into water.
Remove from heat and add butter, vanilla, pecans and Marshmallow Creme.
Divide this into 2 pans.
Beat one pan until creamy and glossy into buttered pan.
Cut marshmallows into small pieces and drop onto chocolate.
Beat the other half of candy until creamy and pour on top of marshmallows.

title: catalina fish fillets
directions: Mix first 6 items together.
Coat fish and pour any remaining over fish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: lasagna
directions: Simmer the beef, onion, sauce mix, tomato sauce, tomatoes, oregano, parsley flakes and garlic for 15 minutes.
Cook lasagna noodles in water.
Place noodles on bottom of pan.
Layer sauce, Mozzarella cheese, noodles, sauce, cheese, then sauce on cheese. Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt together margarine, peanut butter and chocolate pieces over low heat.
In a large bowl, pour mixture over Crispix cereal and mix thoroughly or until well coated.
Put powdered sugar in clean paper grocery bag.
Add Crispix mixture.
Shake well.
Put in freezer until set, then break apart and put in containers.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Mix together.
Serve with red and/or green apples.
Dip apples into caramel apple dip and enjoy.
Great Christmas idea!

title: favorite sloppy joes
directions: In a large skillet, cook beef and onion over medium heat until meat is no longer pink; drain. Stir in chili sauce, water, mustard and chili powder. Transfer to a slow cooker. Cover and cook on low for 4 to 6 hours or until flavors are blended. Spoon 1/2 cup onto each bun; top with cheese. Yield: 12 servings.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix crab meat, egg and juice of lemon.
Mix rest of ingredients with crab meat.
Toss lightly.
Form crab cakes.
Roll in cracker crumbs and fry.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together and pour into greased baking dish.
Melt last 1/3 stick of margarine and last three ingredients to make topping.
Sprinkle over sweet potato mixture.
Bake in 400 degree oven for 35 minutes.

title: chinese-style spareribs
directions: Cut ribs into 3 or 4 rib sections.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Combine salts.
Mix and sprinkle evenly over ribs.
Cover ribs with aluminum foil, crimping foil firmly to edges of pan. Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat slowly.
Add oregano, salt and Ragu sauce.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Cook noodles.
Beat eggs.
Add sour cream, Parmesan cheese, parsley flakes and pepper.
Lay noodles in baking pan.
Add sour cream mixture.
Add half of Mozzarella cheese.
Add sauce and repeat.
Add noodles on top.
Bake for 30 minutes in 375° oven.

title: crunchy potato chip salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and vinegar.
Add cabbage, peppers, carrots and onions.
Cover and chill.
Add tuna and add chips immediately before serving.
Toss lightly.
Serves 6.

title: little meat loaf
directions: Break eggs in bowl, beat slightly.
Add all ingredients, except corn flakes.
Stir quickly with a fork.
Divide meat into six parts.
Shape each into an oblong loaf.
Roll each loaf in corn flakes.
Place in greased pan. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Place in glass bowl.
Add green pepper, onion, salt and pepper.
Pour over bean mixture.
Toss.
Refrigerate, covered, for 24 hours.
Makes 20 servings.

title: no sugar apple bars(sugar-free)
directions: In saucepan, mix water, raisins, shortening, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bring to a boil and simmer 3 minutes; cool.
In mixing bowl, beat egg and vanilla.
Add to raisin mixture.
Mix flour, salt, soda and nuts and add to mixture.
Spread into 6 x 6-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into bars and serve warm.

title: salad dressing
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add part of water and vinegar to dissolve.
Save some water to rinse beaten egg dish.
Cook in double boiler or heavy pan.
Stir while cooking at medium heat. Store in covered jar in refrigerator.
Keeps and keeps.

title: my own famous chicken salad(formerly a secret recipe)
directions: Chop chicken in bite size pieces.
Toast almonds and pecans separately in 1 teaspoon margarine each.

(I do mine in the microwave, stirring at 1 minute intervals until lightly toasted.) Toss all ingredients with just enough mayonnaise to hold together. Better if made a day ahead (before adding mayonnaise) to allow flavors to blend.
Green grapes may be substituted, but the salad will be more tart.
Serve with crackers for a meal or make into sandwiches.
Will make 8 to 10 large sandwiches or 12 to 20 dainty tea sandwiches.
Recipe may easily be halved or doubled.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Mix applesauce, sugar and vinegar.
Heat in microwave until hot.
Place in crock-pot.
Cook on high for 8 to 10 hours.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream together cheeses, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce. Place in fridge to chill.
Add remaining ingredients, except nuts and paprika.
Chill 30 minutes.
Roll into ball and roll in paprika and nuts.

title: hungarian goulash soup
directions: In a Dutch oven over medium heat, brown beef in 1 teaspoon oil. Remove beef; drain drippings. Heat remaining oil in the same pan; saute onions and garlic for 8 to 10 minutes over medium heat or until lightly browned. Add paprika, caraway, pepper, cayenne and salt, if desired. Cook and stir 1 minute. Return beef to pan. Add broth, potatoes, carrots and rutabagas; bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until vegetables are tender and meat is almost tender. Add tomatoes and red pepper; return to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes or until meat and vegetables are tender. Serve with sour cream, if desired. Makes 15 servings.

title: chicken divan on rice(serves 6)
directions: Cook rice until tender in 6 cups water and 1 tablespoon butter.
Cook broccoli per package directions.
Drain.
Melt butter in skillet.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add chicken broth.
Cook until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Stir in cream. Place rice in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place broccoli on top of rice.
Pour 1/2 of sauce over.
Top with chicken.
Add Parmesan cheese to remainder of sauce and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese if desired.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: mexican corn casserole
directions: Combine corn, Bisquick, eggs, butter, sugar and milk.
Mix. Turn half of batter into greased 16 x 11-inch glass dish.
Cover with chilies, onion and cheese slices.
Spread remaining batter. Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 400° until brown.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Cook ground beef and drain.
Then mix all ingredients and bake.

title: church window cookies
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate chips in double boiler.
Cool. Add nuts and marshmallows.
Put coconut on wax paper; pour chocolate mixture on this and form 1 or 2 rolls.
Cover with coconut.
Refrigerate.
Makes about 3 dozen slices.

title: swamp bottom brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 8-inch square baking pan.
In large bowl with electric mixer on medium speed, combine 3/4 cup granulated sugar, flour, 1 1/2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Slowly add milk, butter and vanilla.
Beat until smooth. Pour into greased pan.
In 1-quart saucepan, heat remaining 1/2 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa powder, brown sugar and water over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, until thin syrup forms, about 7 minutes.
Pour over batter in pan.
Bake 40 minutes until brownies are firm in center.
Cool on wire rack for 5 minutes.
Cut into 12 rectangles and invert onto serving platter.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together Sweet 'N Low and shortening.
Add eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Combine milk, vanilla and almond extract.
Alternate 1/2 of milk mixture to rest of ingredients and mix well.
Use 1/2 dough at a time and roll out on floured surface.
Use floured cutters to cut out.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: chicken and stuffing
directions: Wash, dry and skin chicken.
Mix soup, sour cream and chicken. Place in Pyrex dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and place over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cover loosely with foil for first 15 minutes.

title: carol's egg casserole
directions: Place bread in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with meat and shredded cheese.
Mix and beat eggs, milk, mustard and salt.
Pour carefully over contents of casserole.
Cover and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Next morning, mix can soup and 1/2 cup milk.
Pour gently over casserole and bake uncovered at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 12 servings heartily.
Warms over well in microwave.
Serve with toast and fruit.

title: microwave sloppy joes
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, crumble beef.
Add onion, celery and green pepper.
Cover.
Microwave on High for 6 minutes.
Stir after 3 minutes.
Drain meat well.
Add to cooked mixture, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Cover.
Microwave at High 5 to 6 minutes.
Stir after 3 minutes or until hot.
To serve, spoon on buns.

title: beef and macaroni
directions: Cook onions in shortening until soft, not brown.
Add ground beef and brown.
Add salt, pepper, tomato soup, water and macaroni.
Put in a casserole and bake 30 minutes in a moderate oven.

title: bird's nest pie
directions: Divide apples evenly between 2 greased 9-inch pie plates and set aside.
In a mixing bowl combine flour, sugar, baking soda, cream of tartar, some milk and egg.
Mix well.
Divide batter and pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until pies are lightly browned and test done.
Invert onto serving plates so that apples are on the top.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage until tender. Drain well and set aside.
Saute onions in margarine until tender. Add soup and 1/4 cup water. Stir until smooth. Add cheese. Stir more.
Mix this with cabbage. Place in buttered casserole dish.
Top with crushed crackers and a little melted margarine. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together; add beaten eggs.
Sift flour; add to spices and salt.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk; add this and flour mixture alternately to egg-sugar mixture.
Add jam and nuts. Bake in 325° oven for about 2 hours if in tube pan; about 40 minutes if in layer pans.

title: hot and spicy beef burgers
directions: Combine ground beef, jalapeno peppers, cumin, salt and pepper. Mix lightly, but thoroughly.
Divide beef mixture into 4 equal portions.
Shape into 1/2-inch thick patties, 4-inches in diameter.
Place patties on grid over medium coals.
Grill 7 to 9 minutes, turning once.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon cheese on each burger 1 minute before end of cooking time.
Place tomato slice on bun bottom.
Top each with grilled burger and cover with roll top.

title: vincent's pie
directions: Mix yogurt, whip cream, frozen fruit and chocolate chips. Pour into pie crust and freeze.

title: judy's brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350°
for 35 - 40 minutes.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: buckeyes
directions: Cream the peanut butter with softened margarine and vanilla. Beat in powdered sugar.
Form balls.
Place on a sheet until chilled in the refrigerator.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin over hot water.
Dip balls in chocolate using a toothpick.
Let cool on wax paper.
Can freeze.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Place crumbs, coconut, chips, pecans and milk in order given in pan forming layers.
Do not stir. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix in order given the eggs, sugar, evaporated milk, cinnamon and pumpkin.
Grease and flour a 10 x 14-inch pan.
Pour in mixture and sprinkle cake mix on top.
Dribble with margarine. Bake 1 hour at 350° or until knife comes out clean.
Serve as is or with Cool Whip.
Good warm or cold.

title: microwave carrots
directions: Thinly slice carrots and mix with white wine or champagne. Add butter, dill, pepper and (if desired) salt.
Cover tightly and microwave until crisp-tender.
Season with additional pepper and garnish with parsley.

title: italian chicken stew
directions: Cook chicken in 2 cups of water until done.
Remove chicken from water and add spices and pasta.
Cook 5 minutes.
Slice squash.
Dice onion and green pepper.
Add to water.
Cook 5 minutes more or until pasta is done.
Remove from heat.
Add boneless chicken meat and cheese.

title: marinade mix
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Marinate meat overnight. Will keep in the refrigerator for several weeks.
Great for steaks, chicken and shish kabobs.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions.
Cut both layers in half when cooled.
Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut. Chill; reserve 1 cup of mixture.
Divide rest between flour layers. To reserved cup of mixture, add whipped topping.
Spread over cake. Place in airtight container and let stand and set for 3 days.

title: congo squares(bar cookies)
directions: Melt shortening in large pot.
Remove from burner.
Add brown sugar
and
stir
until
shortening melts.
Add eggs and mix.
Add baking
powder and salt and mix.
Add flour and mix. Add nuts and chocolate chips and mix.
Spread on greased 10 x 15 x 1-inch jellyroll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cut into 2-inch squares when cool.

title: peanut butter cup cookies
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and both sugars.
Add egg and vanilla and beat until creamy.
Stir in dry ingredients until blended.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Put into greased and floured
1 1/2-inch muffin tins.
Bake at 325° for 12 minutes. Remove from oven and immediately press 1 peanut butter cup into each hot cookie crust.
Allow to cool.
Remove cookies gently from pan with sharp knife.
They pop right out.
Makes 48.

title: jumbo shells seafood fancies(8 servings)
directions: Add shells gradually to 6 quarts of boiling salted water; cook until tender, yet firm.
Drain; rinse with cold water, then drain again.
Invert on paper towel-lined plate to cool.
Combine crabmeat, shrimp, cheese, salad dressing, celery, onion and pimento in medium size bowl.
If mixture seems too dry, add more salad dressing.
Spoon mixture into cooled shells; cover and refrigerate until chilled.
Garnish with celery leaves.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Mix ingredients all together and put in greased casserole dish.
Add grated cheese and bread crumbs on top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: creamy mac 'n' cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Drain.
In separate bowl, combine flour and 1 cup of milk.
Blend well.
Pour into saucepan; add remaining milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add cheese; continue cooking until cheese is melted.
Stir constantly.
Add cooked macaroni, salt and pepper.
Yields 8 servings.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Wash and pare firm potatoes.
Cut in eighths, lengthwise. Cover with cold water.
Let stand at least 30 minutes.
Drain.
Dry thoroughly with a paper towel.

title: easy mexican meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Have a shallow baking dish ready.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl until well blended.
In baking dish, shape mixture into an 8 x 4-inch loaf.
Bake 1 hour or until cooked through.
Serves 4.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Put the rice in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay pieces of raw chicken on rice.
Salt and pepper, if desired.
Mix the soups and broth; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle the dry onion soup over this.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
While baking, chicken and rice should be covered with foil.
The last 1/2 hour, remove foil and allow chicken to brown.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: In saucepan, bring potatoes, onion, water and salt to boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer until potatoes are tender.
Do not drain!
Mash slightly.
Stir in milk.
In a small bowl, blend margarine, flour, parsley and pepper.
Stir into the potato mixture.
Cook and stir constantly over a medium heat until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat; add cheese and stir until almost melted.
Yields 6 servings (1 1/2 quarts).

title: pizza crust
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water; add oil, salt and sugar. Add flour; let rise about 1/2 hour.
Spread pizza dough on pizza pan; add desired toppings.
Bake at 425° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: german pancake
directions: Mix together, batter will be lumpy. Use a 10 inch iron skillet. Spray with pam. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes in a pre-heated oven at 450°.

title: lemonade syrup base
directions: Measure sugar, water and lemon peel into large saucepan. While stirring constantly with wooden spoon, bring the mixture to a boil. Boil for 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add lemon juice to cooled sugar mixture.
Pour this lemonade syrup into a quart jar and cover it tightly with a lid.
It can be stored in refrigerator for 2 to 3 weeks.

title: pumpkin cheesecake i
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat cream cheese and sugars until fluffy.
Add eggs gradually.
Mix in remaining ingredients. Butter a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Coat with graham cracker crumbs. Fill with batter.
Bake cheesecake for 80 minutes or until it is firm around the edges.
Turn off oven and let cheesecake stand in cooling oven for 30 minutes.
Remove and cool completely on rack. Good served with whipped topping.

title: spinach and bean minestra
directions: Heat the oil in a heavy pot over medium heat.
Cook the bacon until it is done, but not crisp.
Pour off all but about 6 tablespoons of the fat.
Add the garlic.
Cook, stirring, until golden.
Add the spinach and its cooking water, salt, pepper, oregano, ditalini, cannellini (undrained) and tomatoes.
Stir over low heat for 5 minutes.
Stir in the Romano cheese and serve. Minestra is a very thick soup, almost a stew.

title: whopper pie
directions: Combine softened ice cream and whipped topping.
Mix 1 cup crushed candy into mixture.
Spoon into pie crust.
Sprinkle remaining crushed candy on top.
Freeze 4 hours.
Garnish with whipped topping and whole Whoppers.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken soup
directions: Bring broth to a boil.
Add rice; cook 30 minutes or until rice is soft.
Turn off heat.
Beat egg yolks together with lemon juice, then add to it 1 cup of rice mixture and blend.
Pour this back into pot of rice mixture.
Makes 6 to 7 servings.

title: supreme green casserole
directions: Thaw, drain vegetables.

Layer bottom of casserole with 1/2 onions (crushed), then lay out spinach, top with 1/2 can of soup, 1/2 shredded Mozzarella, 1/2 mushrooms; lay out asparagus spears (cut off ends that may be too tough), top with remaining soup, Mozzarella, and mushrooms.
Lay out broccoli spears, top with remaining onions, Cheddar (shredded) and almonds.
Cover and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover and crispen top under broiler, if desired, or keep covered for another 5 minutes at 400°.
Yields approximately 12 servings.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Layer Doritos in bottom of pan.
Put in a layer of chicken, then onions, then bell pepper.
Repeat another layer of everything.
Pour soup mixture over this.
Top with grated cheese and bake 40 minutes at 350° to 400° or until real bubbly.

title: gourmet holiday casserole
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Stir in flour and seasonings. Cook until smooth, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Gradually stir in milk.
Bring to a boil, over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir one minute.
Add Cheddar cheese; stir until melted.
Set aside.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix soups, sour cream, almonds and chicken.
Put in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Crush crackers.
Melt butter and mix together.
Add poppy seed and pour on top of casserole.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Even those not fond of carrots will
like them prepared with these ingredients.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Microwave butter and chocolate until melted.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Then add flour and salt.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° until brownies are pulling away from edges of pan, approximately 45 minutes.

title: easy pineapple upside down cake
directions: Mix butter with brown sugar and spread over the bottom of a well greased springform pan.
Arrange pineapple slices over brown sugar mixture; reserve pineapple juice.
Place a cherry half in the center of each pineapple slice.
Add enough water to the pineapple juice to make 1 1/3 c. liquid.
Mix this with the cake mix, eggs, and vegetable oil.
Pour this over pineapples and bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes.
Let cake cool completely, then remove springform pan and serve cake slices with cool whip.

title: black walnut cream pie
directions: Cook to boiling, stirring constantly the granulated sugar, flour, salt, egg yolks, butter and milk.
Add vanilla, maple flavoring and black walnuts.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Grease a shallow pan.
In a large heavy pot, melt butter and add water, molasses and sugar.
Stir well to dissolve.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Boil without stirring until a little becomes brittle in cold water.
Add peanuts and pour on greased pan.

title: layered bean dip
directions: In
medium
bowl,
mix beans, chiles and taco seasoning mix. Spread
on	12-inch
round serving dish.
Blend avocado, juice and sauce until smooth.
Spread on top of bean mixture. Spread sour cream
on
top of avocado mixture.	Top with lettuce,
then cheese,
taco sauce and olive slices.
Serve with chips.

title: pumpkin angel squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix flour, butter and pecans with pastry blender until crumbly.
Pack into 9-inch square pan.
Bake in oven 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and whipped topping with electric mixer.
Spread on cooled crust and chill in refrigerator.
Soften gelatin in water.
Combine gelatin mixture with pumpkin, egg yolks, brown sugar, milk, pumpkin pie spice and salt in large saucepan.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring until mixture begins to bubble.
Cover and cool.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Slowly add remaining sugar and continue beating until stiff and glossy. Fold into pumpkin mixture.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Chill until set.
Cut into squares.

title: angel crisps
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Form into balls size of walnuts.
Dip in water, then in sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Press down in center with finger.
Bake in 425° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: christmas gingerbread men
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar together.
Add molasses and egg yolk.
Blend well.
Add salt, soda, baking powder and spices. Slowly add sifted flour.
Roll out dough and cut with gingerbread man cookie cutter.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Decorate. Yields 2 to 3 dozen, depending on size of cutter.

title: spaghetti salad supreme
directions: Cook spaghetti; rinse in cold water twice.
Mix in onion, Salad Supreme and dressing.
Refrigerate in covered bowl overnight.
Before serving, add cucumber and tomato.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in salted water; drain and add half of oleo. Cream together; add remaining ingredients.
Hold half of stuffing mix and half of oleo.
Line casserole with reserved stuffing mix, which has been mixed with melted 1/2 stick of oleo.
Pour in squash mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
If desired, save a small amount of stuffing mix and crumble on top.

title: yum-a-setta casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with salt, pepper, brown sugar and onion.
Add tomato soup (undiluted).
Cook egg noodles; drain.
Add cream of chicken soup (undiluted).
Layer hamburger mixture and noodle mixture in casserole dish with cheese in between each layer.
Top with grated cheese, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. This makes a very large casserole; good for a crowd.
I sometimes split it into two dishes and freeze one for a later date.
(Feeds a family of four nicely.)

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Place French-cut beans in the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Place on beans the chicken, boiled until tender for approximately 1/2 hour.
Mix together cream of chicken and celery soups, onion soup mix and sour cream.
Place the mixture on top of the chicken. Sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Bake until bubbly for approximately 1/2 hour at 350°.
Serve with rice.
Will serve 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Blend in egg, soda, vanilla, 1/3 cup peanut butter and salt.
Stir in flour and oatmeal.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Let stand 5 minutes, spread. Combine powdered sugar, 1/4 cup peanut butter and evaporated milk. Mix well.
Drizzle this mixture over melted chocolate.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: muffins
directions: Cut shortening into flour mixture.
Add egg and milk all at once.
Stir only until dampened.
Spoon into greased muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° about 25 minutes.
Yields 10 muffins.

title: jerry's crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into cakes.
Fry quickly until browned.
Serve hot or may be warmed over.
Can be made into cakes and frozen to use later.

title: taco dip
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl; mix well until blended.
Stir in salsa.
Line 10-inch platter with lettuce. Spread mixture on lettuce leaves.
Top with cheeses, tomatoes, green onions and olives.
Serve with chips.
Makes 10 servings.

title: glorified rice
directions: To cold rice,
add
pineapple, sugar, apple and pecans. Mix all the ingredients
together.
Fold
in
tub of Cool Whip and mix very well.	Put
in
refrigerator for about 30 minutes or until chilled.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cook all ingredients, except rice, for 3 hours on low heat. Serve over rice.

title: spanish barley
directions: Wash barley.
Add water and boil about 45 minutes or until done; drain.
Brown bacon.
Add onions, green pepper and seasonings.
When onions are tender, add tomatoes and cook 10 minutes.
Add to drained barley and simmer 5 minutes.

title: chicken andouille gumbo
directions: Cut up chicken and season with salt and pepper.
Heat 1 cup oil in heavy
skillet and fry chicken until brown.
Remove chicken and put aside.

title: mailable cookies
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Melt oleo in a large saucepan (2 1/2 to 3 quarts).
Stir in brown sugar and allow to cool slightly.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour mixture, chopped nuts and semi-sweet chocolate; blend well.
Turn into greased pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 25 to 30 minutes.
When almost cool cut into strips, 1 x 2 1/4 inches.
Makes 48 strips.

title: tuna spread
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth.
Serve with crackers. This can be rolled into a log and used for all types of festive entertaining.

title: lefse
directions: Peel the potatoes; cook and mash with butter, cream and salt. Let them get cold.
Mix in the flour and roll out rounds of dough paper thin on lightly floured board.
Bake the rounds on a grill, turning to lightly brown on both sides.

title: peach cobbler in a hurry(georgia peach growers association)
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Mix together the milk, flour and sugar and add this mixture to the melted margarine.
Add peaches to baking dish; do not stir.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Top with ice cream.

title: chocolate snowballs
directions: Cream butter thoroughly; add sugar gradually and keep beating until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add vanilla; combine flour with salt and cocoa.
Add gradually to the creamed mixture; blend thoroughly.
Add pecans and mix well.
Form dough into balls about the size of a marble between the palms of the hand.
Bake in moderate oven, 350°, for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and roll in confectioners sugar.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: granny's tomato bisque
directions: In a saucepan or Dutch oven melt butter.
Stir in flour and cook until thick.
Meanwhile, heat tomato juice and milk in separate pans.
When all is hot, stir tomatoes into butter/flour mixture and add soda mixed with a bit of water.
Then add hot milk last.

title: chicken caruso and rice
directions: Season chicken with garlic salt and pepper.
Saute in oleo about 2 minutes.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and seasoning.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add celery; continue cooking until celery is tender and crisp.
Serve over cooked rice or noodles.

title: sliced baked potatoes(4 servings)
directions: Peel potatoes if skins are tough, otherwise, scrub and rinse. Cut into thin slices, not all the way through.
Put in baking dish; fan them slightly.
Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with herbs.

title: grandma's chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in a well-oiled, shallow roasting pan. Put potato halves in the same pan, arranged along with the chicken.
Spread garlic and onion evenly over the pan.
Sprinkle all other herbs and spices evenly over the chicken.

title: lemon glaze cake
directions: Mix cake package, flour, water, oil, pudding and eggs together.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let cool for 10 minutes.
Boil juice and powdered sugar together for 1 minute.
Poke small holes in top of cake.
Pour glaze over cake while warm.
Let cool before serving.

title: world's greatest peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together the first 5 ingredients; add peanut butter. Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix together creamed and dry ingredients.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Crisscross with a fork. Bake at 350° no longer than 10 minutes.

title: cornbread muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Beat egg and milk; add to dry ingredients.
Blend oil or bacon drippings into this and pour into greased muffin pans.
Fill the muffin cups half full.
Bake in a 400° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until edges and tops are brown.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Beat eggs, oil, butter, vanilla and about half of dry cake mix until smooth.
Stir in remaining cake mix.
(If dough is dry, mix in 1 to 1 1/2 teaspoons water.)
Shape dough into 1 1/4 inch balls.
Place about 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly, before removing from baking sheet.
Cool thoroughly.
You can frost cookies with frosting mix.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: mexican cake
directions: Mix all together and bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: olive-nut spread sandwich
directions: Mash the cream cheese with a fork, then add the mayonnaise. Blend well. Stir in the pecans and salad olives. (Notice the recipe calls for the salad olives.
Since they are to be chopped up anyway, don't spend extra money for the more expensive whole ones.)
Now add the olive juice and a dash of pepper, but no salt. Stir well.
This mixture will be slightly mushy, but it's supposed to be that way.
Put it into a covered container and refrigerate for several hours and it will become firm.
This mixture may be served on white or wheat bread. Top with a slice of olive or a pecan half.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Bake 2 pie crusts in hot oven 10 minutes before filling, then set oven back to 325°.
Mix and blend all other ingredients and pour into crusts.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Drain and mash beans; set aside.
Combine sugar and margarine; mix well.
Add the beans, coconut and vanilla.
Add beaten eggs to mixture.
Pour in 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. This makes one pie, but one can of pinto beans and one can of coconut makes three pies.
All you do is double the mixture.

title: pork roast in wine
directions: Line 9	x
13-inch
pan with heavy duty foil (enough to close at	the
top).
Place
pork
roast	in
center
of foil. Sprinkle dry
onion	soup
mix
and mushrooms over meat.
Pour over 1 cup red
wine
with the water.	Close foil at the top. Bake at 275° for 4 to 5 hours.
(You can increase or decrease the ingredients according to size of roast.)

title: oyster nut loaf
directions: Combine and mix well.
Roll in 1 cup chopped walnuts. Refrigerate until time to serve.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Crumble cornbread and toast.
Mix in onion, broth, egg, margarine and pepper.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until it will form a soft ball in water.
Add peanut butter and stir until thick; then pour in greased plate.
Let cool and cut.

title: daffodil dip
directions: Warm cream cheese to room temperature and add mayonnaise; mix well.
Add the rest of the ingredients; mix well and refrigerate. This dip is tastier if made a day before serving.

title: old time chicken dumplings
directions: Sift
the
flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add margarine
and
enough
boiling
water
to	make a stiff dough (dough should
be
stiff,
not soft).
Let cool and mix in the egg.
Roll thin and cut in squares.
Drop into boiling chicken stock and cook 5 minutes.
These dumplings are never heavy and they are as good or better when warmed over.

title: cream puffs
directions: Mix water, oleo and salt and bring to a boil.
Add flour (all at once).
Beat hard until forms a ball.
Add eggs one at a time. Beat until smooth.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet or cupcake tin 1 tablespoon first, then 1 tablespoon on top of first.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: strawberry banana salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except the sour cream.
Pour 1/2 of the mixture in a large Pyrex dish and let gel.
Spread sour cream over gelled mixture.
Pour remaining half of jello mixture over sour cream and let gel.
Cover.
Refrigerate until serving. Serves 12.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Combine all ingredients and cook about 30 minutes.

title: grits souffle(this is great for southern-styled brunch; serve with ham)
directions: *To prepare grits, boil 4 cups water to 1 cup grits or follow box directions.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all at once; grease and flour 3 (1 pound) coffee cans. Fill 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes.
Slides from can easily.

title: pink lemonade
directions: In a one gallon pitcher, mix lemonade, grape juice and 7 1/2 cans of water (11 1/4 cups or 90 ounces).

title: zucchini soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil until tender in large saucepan. Add chicken broth and uncooked rice and simmer 10 minutes covered. Add zucchini and salt and pepper to taste and simmer uncovered 15 minutes.
Beat together egg, Parmesan cheese and chopped parsley and whisk into soup and serve.

title: best ever cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on box in 13 x 9-inch pan. Meanwhile, simmer pineapple and sugar.
Remove cake from oven. Punch holes in it and cover with pineapple.
Mix instant pudding as directed on box.
Add coconut.
Spread over pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip and nuts.

title: diabetic peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all together in a large bowl.
Shape into balls and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes. (You may add a little more flour, if desired.)

title: chocolate icing
directions: In small saucepan, add butter, milk and cocoa.
Stir to blend. Cook over medium heat, stirring until butter melts.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and powdered sugar. Mix well until spreading consistency.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and butter.
Beat all ingredients together.
Serve with strawberries or fruit salad.

title: pork chops
directions: In casserole dish, put layer of beans, then a layer of chops, another layer of beans and more chops on top.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.
After 45 minutes, turn chops over.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat tomato soup (no water added). Add cream cheese and beat until smooth. Add water, gelatin, celery, onion, shrimp and mayo. Salt, pepper and Tabasco to taste. Put into oiled mold and refrigerate overnight. Serve with crackers.

title: escalloped pineapple
directions: Place cubed bread in a buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Add sugar and melted butter.
Combine eggs and milk; add to bread. Add pineapple; mix slightly.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Drain.
Mash squash and add 1/2 cup bread crumbs, sugar, salt, pepper, eggs and butter. Pour 1/2 into casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and Cheddar cheese.
Repeat.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: tangy dip
directions: In a pan beat eggs.
Add vinegar and sugar.
Cook until thick.
Add cream cheese and diced pepper. Add onion, if desired.

title: egg casserole
directions: Put crumbs on bottom of buttered dish.
Layer sauce, cheese then pimento.
Then add eggs and top with buttered cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: peggy's pasta salad
directions: Cook the vermicelli 6 minutes, drain, but do not rinse. Marinate cooked vermicelli overnight in the oil, lemon juice and Accent.
Add the mayonnaise, celery, onion, stuffed olives, ripe or black olives, pimentos and salt and pepper to taste the next morning.
Let the salad sit for awhile as to allow the flavors time to blend. This salad tends to improve the longer it stays in the refrigerator.
Serves about 30 people.

title: mexican fried rice
directions: In kettle place ingredients.
Boil and simmer for at least 1 hour.
Fry 1 quart rice in heavy pan with small amount of oil. When turning color is apparent, put rice in kettle and cook until done.
(May have to add water.)

title: eggplant rollatini
directions: Peel eggplants and slice lengthwise.
Dredge in flour.
Dip in eggs and fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Place a slice of Mozzarella in the middle of each slice of eggplant. Add parsley and Romano to Ricotta.
Add a scoop of the Ricotta mixture and roll up the eggplant.
Spoon marinara or your favorite sauce into a baking pan.
Place eggplant rolls seam side down over sauce.
Top with additional sauce and sprinkle with grated Romano cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve pasta on the side.

title: sugared walnuts
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cinnamon together in a pot.
Add water and bring to a soft boil and boil about 15 minutes to a temperature of 375°.
DO NOT STIR. Remove from heat and add vanilla and nuts. Stir until creamy and coated. Turn out on wax paper.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook green beans in pan until hot; drain and set aside.
In a saucepan at very low heat, melt butter.
Add flour and garlic salt.
After mixed, add sour cream and Velveeta cheese.
Fold mixture into green beans; pour into buttered dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: homemade buns
directions: Let raise 1 hour.
Work down; let raise 1 hour again.
Then put them in pans.
Let raise hour and a half.
Then bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and onion together; drain. Add remaining ingredients to meat and simmer for 30 minutes. Before serving, shred Cheddar cheese on top and serve with tortilla chips.

title: caramel apple pie
directions: Combine caramel pieces and flour; add apples, topping and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into 9-inch unbaked pie crust.
Top with pecans.
Bake on preheated baking sheet at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes, until crust has browned.
Cool.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add fruit cocktail, beaten eggs and oil.
Pour into large 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle with 1/4 cup brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost with Fruit Cocktail Icing.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Melt sugar and Karo in large pan.
Add peanut butter.
Add Rice Krispies into mixture and stir well.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Melt chips in double boiler and pour over mixture.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Bake cake.
Poke holes in cake with a wooden spoon handle. Pour milk over warm cake.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Stir coconut cream.
Pour over chilled cake.
Frost with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with coconut flakes.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Combine all but Cool Whip; blend well.
Fold in Cool Whip. Chill.

title: nut rolls
directions: Mix these ingredients.
Add yeast mixture and knead.
(If sticky, add flour.)
Let rise about 15 minutes.
Separate dough into four balls.
Roll each ball out flat, about 1/2 inch thick.

title: britzel bars
directions: Line a cookie sheet with foil and spray lightly with Pam. Line with one layer of crackers.
In saucepan, bring butter and sugar to a rolling boil.
Pour over crackers and spread evenly. Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes.
Let stand a couple of minutes, then cover with chocolate chips, spreading evenly as they melt.
Sprinkle with walnuts; gently pressing walnuts into chocolate.
Place entire pan in refrigerator for a couple hours to harden.
Cut into bars.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Crush pretzels (saving 3 tablespoons crumbs for top).
Add 3 tablespoons sugar and the butter or margarine.
Stir with fork until well blended.
Pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: iced almonds
directions: In a heavy skillet, heat almonds, sugar and butter over medium heat.
Stir constantly until almonds are toasted and sugar is golden brown, about 15 minutes.
Stir in vanilla.
Drop in clusters on baking sheet or foil.
Sprinkle with a little salt. Cool.
Makes 1 pound candy.

title: custard rice pudding
directions: Mix rice, evaporated milk, eggs, sugar and salt in a large glass baking dish.
Stirring, add vanilla and 1 can of water.
Top with butter and sprinkle with nutmeg before baking.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: refreshing treat
directions: Mix all together and serve.
Surprising flavor, very good.

title: sausage spaghetti
directions: In a large skillet, fry sausage until almost brown.
Add all except spaghetti.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Prepare spaghetti and drain.
Place on large platter and pour sauce on top.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl and place in refrigerator overnight before serving.

title: leftover ham or other meat
directions: Fry onion in margarine; add rest of ingredients.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Serve over cooked noodles.
Serves 4.

title: 1-2-3 baskets
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop in greased muffin pans. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: easy care pot roast
directions: Place 2 pieces of aluminum foil (18 x 24-inch) crisscross over a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle half of the soup mix over the foil.
Place meat on top; spoon soup and the remainder of mix over meat.
Bring opposite edges of foil together.
Fold and seal. Bake at 350° for 3 hours.
Pour off gravy and slice meat to serve.

title: mint brownies
directions: Melt chocolate with butter in a medium pan.
Remove from heat and add eggs, sugar, extract, flour, salt and nuts.
Blend well by hand.
Pour into a well-greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Spread with frosting and refrigerate.
Spread with glaze and refrigerate.
When glaze is set, cut into squares.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; mix well. Add sugar and oil; mix. Add buttermilk.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugar.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together; add to sugar and egg mixture. Mix well.
Stir in M&M's.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: robin's nests
directions: Cream butter with sugar; beat in egg yolks and vanilla.
Stir in flour.
Beat egg whites in shallow bowl; sprinkle nuts on waxed paper.
Roll dough, one teaspoonful at a time, into balls.
Roll in egg whites, then nuts.
Place on cookie sheet.
Press a hollow in center with finger.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until firm and lightly golden.
Cool.
Place a fondant egg in each "nest".

title: rio grande valley grapefruit and avocado salad
directions: Peel; seed avocados; cut each half into 3 or 4 thick vertical slices.
Bathe all in lime juice.
With your very sharpest knife, peel whole grapefruit thickly enough to cut off all white "rag." Then cut toward core along segment line; nice sections will fall out.
Sprinkle lightly with garlic powder or garlic salt.
On lettuce leaf put together alternating sections to form a rounded mound, red and green.
Serve with dressing, if desired.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Add spaghetti sauce and simmer. Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix cheese with sour cream and spread over meat mix.
Top with rolls. Brush with melted butter. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: french silk pie
directions: Bake pie crust according to directions and allow to cool.
In a small bowl, cream sugar and butter until light.
Blend in cooled chocolate and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat on medium speed of electric mixer for 2 minutes.
After each egg, scrape sides of bowl constantly.
Turn mixture into baked/cooled pie shell.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Cook and drain broccoli (no salt).
Mix first 3 ingredients. Add milk, mayonnaise and egg.
Pour in sprayed casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with toasted bread crumbs.

title: christmas punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin.
Add lemonade, cold water and cranberry juice.
Place 2 trays of ice cubes in large bowl; pour over. Slowly add ginger ale.
Also may add raspberry sherbet.
Float green cherries for color effect.

title: marinated veggies
directions: In large pot, heat broccoli, cauliflower, and carrots to a boil, reduce to simmer for 10 minutes & drain. To the cooked vegetables, add tomatoes, onion, mushrooms, green pepper, & celery.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat oil and sugar together. Add eggs and bananas and beat well. Sift the flour, soda, baking powder and salt together and add to oil mixture alternately with milk and vanilla. Beat well and stir in nuts. Pour in 9 x 5-inch greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour. Cool and store in airtight container.

title: chocolate delight
directions: In medium casserole dish, place the butter and flour for the crust.
Bake until brown.
Mix the cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 1 cup of Cool Whip; place on top of the crust for the first layer.
Mix the pudding and milk; place on top of first layer.
Top with Cool Whip.
Place in refrigerator to chill.

title: cherry pineapple cobbler
directions: Generously grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer the cherry pie filling and crushed pineapple on bottom of dish.
Pour dry cake mix right out of box over the fruit filling.
Melt butter and pour over the cake mix.
Sprinkle pecans over the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bunny's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together; drop onto cookie sheet by teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pie crusts.
Let stand overnight.
If desired, save a few pieces of pineapple for top.

title: mud balls
directions: Mix all together real good all ingredients except the package of chocolate bits and the melted paraffin wax.
Form into balls the size of quarter.
Refrigerate until ready to dip (overnight). Melt chocolate bits and paraffin.
Mix and then dip each ball into chocolate.
Place on cookie sheet and refrigerate until hard.

title: crunchy baked chicken(makes 1 serving)
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; set aside.
Brush chicken with skim milk.
Coat with cereal mixture and place on nonstick baking pan.
Dot cutlet with 2 teaspoons reduced calorie margarine and bake for 15 minutes at 400° or until done.

title: baked chicken
directions: Spread chicken on both sides with mustard, dip in sour cream and roll in croutons.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and place chicken in dish; dot with butter.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 400° for 30 minutes, then uncover and bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: hamburger soup
directions: In a large saucepan or kettle, brown meat and drain fat.
Add salt, pepper, oregano, basil, seasoned salt and onion soup mix. Stir in boiling water, tomato sauce and soy sauce.
Cover and simmer for about 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, prepare celery, leaves and carrots, then add to simmering mixture with split peas and continue to cook for 30 minutes.
Add macaroni and simmer for 30 minutes longer adding more water if necessary.
Serve with Parmesan cheese if desired.

title: banana fritters
directions: Mash bananas, then add remaining ingredients.
Fry in hot oil, 1 tablespoon batter.
Makes 12 fritters.

title: sweet and spicy salsa
directions: In medium bowl, combine pineapple, red and yellow peppers, onion, cilantro, jalapeno pepper, lime juice, brown sugar, salt and black pepper.
Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes before serving. Makes 8 appetizer servings.

title: mahi-mahi creole
directions: Roll fish in creole seasoning.
In large iron skillet, saute fish in butter and sherry wine for 3 minutes.
Then put in oven for 10 minutes at 350 degrees.
