Remove from oven and take fish out of skillet and set aside.
In same skillet, add green peppers, onions, parsley, mushrooms, dill, garlic salt, tomato sauce and 1 tablespoon of sherry wine.
Last, add the 1/2 lemon, squeezed, and return fish to skillet.
Saute for another 2 to 3 minutes.
Then serve and enjoy.

title: chewy coconut-raisin nut cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugars, margarine, vanilla and eggs in a large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Shape by teaspoonfuls into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.
Cool 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet.
Yields 4 1/2 dozen.

title: hamburger ro-tel cheese dip
directions: Brown meat in skillet. Drain. Add taco mix and water. Bring to boil, reduce heat and let simmer for about 15-20 minutes. Add nacho cheese dip and Ro-Tel tomatoes. Heat and empty into bowl or pour into crockpot on low heat.

title: fish or shrimp creole(adapted from better homes and garden new cookbook.)
directions: Brown onion, green pepper, garlic, celery and ginger root in a little oil in 10-inch skillet.
Add undrained tomatoes, parsley flakes, bouillon and hot pepper sauce.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add cornstarch moistened by 1 tablespoon cold water.
Cook until thickened and bubbly.
Cut fish into 1 inch or smaller pieces; add to sauce.
Simmer 5 minutes more until fish flakes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Boil milk, sugar and 1 package of coconut for 5 to 7 minutes. While cake is hot, prick with fork and pour boiled mixture over cake.
Allow to cool.
Mix Cool Whip and other package of coconut. Spread over cooled cake.
Keep refrigerated.

title: pineapple chicken and rice
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat until hot.
Add chicken and cook 2 to 3 minutes on each side or until browned. Remove chicken from skillet.
Add chicken broth, sweet/sour sauce, pineapple liquid and rice to skillet; blend well.
Bring to a boil. Add chicken, meaty side down.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 25 to 30 minutes or until most of the liquid is absorbed, chicken is fork-tender and juices run clear.
Remove chicken and keep warm. Add bell peppers, onions and pineapple tidbits to rice mix.
Cook an additional 5 minutes or until peppers are crisp-tender.
Spoon rice mixture onto platter; top with chicken breasts.

title: cream cheese salad
directions: Put cheese in Jell-O while still warm.
Beat until smooth. Add other ingredients and mold.

title: breakfast cocoa
directions: In a saucepan stir together sugar, cocoa and salt.
Stir in water.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in milk.
Heat just to boiling point.
Stir in vanilla.
Makes 4 (8 ounce) servings.

title: ham red eye gravy
directions: Fry ham slowly and be careful not to overcook.
Remove ham from pan.
Mix flour in ham grease and brown good.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add coffee right from the pot.
Add water and cook until thick enough.
Real good on biscuits.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Drain cooked carrots; add melted butter (1/4 stick) to Velveeta and melt.
Crush crackers and toss with remaining 1/4 stick butter.
Mix cheese with carrots and pour into casserole. Sprinkle with crumbled cracker-butter mixture on top and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown beef with onions, celery and seasonings.
Add soup and simmer to blend flavors.

title: hush puppies
directions: Beat egg in a bowl.
Add corn and mix.
Add sugar, onion and flour; mix well.
Add enough corn meal to thicken, not as thick as regular corn meal hush puppies.
Stir lightly with a fork.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: green tomato jam
directions: Cook tomatoes and sugar until sugar is melted and it comes to a full boil. Add jello.
Heat until jello is dissolved.
Put in jars and seal with paraffin.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix ingredients in one bowl.
Bake at 350° in a greased tube pan for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pecan brittle
directions: Boil sugar, Karo and water until thread spins; then add pecans.
Stir continuously after pecans are added.
Cook until brownish gold.
Take from heat.
Add butter, salt and soda. Quickly pour onto buttered board or pan.
Let cool.
Break into pieces.

title: better 'n sex pineapple cream cake
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook pineapple and sugar in saucepan until syrupy (20 minutes).
Pierce cake at 1-inch intervals.
Spread mixture over cake.
Cool.
Blend pudding mix with milk until thick.
Spread over cake.
Beat cream and confectioners sugar until stiff.
Cover cake.
Sprinkle with toasted coconut.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Serves 16.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Stir and drop on pan.
Cook at 350° until lightly browned.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Bake dough on greased and floured pizza pan 15 minutes at 350°.
Mix cream cheese and sugar and spread on top of cooled crust.
Start layers of fruit on the outside.
Combine juice from mandarin oranges and cornstarch.
Let cool. Glaze on top.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Soften cream cheese with lemon juice.
Add shrimp, cut up, and chopped onion.
Serve with any kind of crackers or party rye.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Saute chopped onion in small amount of cooking oil.
Drain. Brown meat.
Add other ingredients and simmer at least 1 hour. Makes 8 to 10 servings.
Serve spooned over toasted buns.

title: marilyn's vegetable lasagna
directions: Cook Lasagna. Heat vegetable oil in a sauce pan. Add Onions, Carrots, and Garlic. Saute until Carrots are tender. Add Spaghetti Sauce, Water and Spices. Bring to a simmer. Beat Eggs and blend in the Cottage Cheese, Parmesan Cheese, and vegetables. Spread thin layer of Sauce in 9 x 13 inch pan. Cover with layer of Noodles, spoon 1/2 Cheese mixture over Noodles. Cover with 1/2 Sauce over the Cheese. Repeat. Cover with foil and bake at 350 for 35 minutes. Remove foil. Sprinkle with Mozzarella Cheese and bake uncovered for 15 minutes.

title: roasted onions(cipolle arrostiti)
directions: Place onions on a baking sheet
and
bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, or until tender but not mushy.
They should be crunchy to the bite.
When they
are done, cool and peel.
Cut into wedges and separate.
Arrange
in a large flat bowl.
Add oil and vinegar and
toss
lightly.
Sprinkle
with
salt
and pepper.
Serve with roasted
meats.
Leftovers
are
great and can last for several days.

title: beans-beans-beans
directions: Brown meat in skillet; add onions, green peppers and mushrooms.
Cook until vegetables are lightly browned.
Place meat mixture in a large pot and add tomatoes, soup, beans, Worcestershire sauce, seasoned salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add cheese and simmer 10 minutes more.

title: chocolate mint sauce
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water. Add sugar, water and salt. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar and chocolate thickens and melts. Boil 3 minutes at 230° or until small amount forms a ball in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and peppermint.
If you are going to store and use later, omit butter. Seal in a jar and chill.
Before using, reheat and add butter. Makes 2 cups sauce.

title: four layer torte
directions: Combine flour, butter and pecans.
Press into 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Allow to cool completely. Cream the cream cheese with powdered sugar and one cup of Cool Whip.
Pour over crust.
Mix pudding with milk until it begins to congeal.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Spread 3 cups Cool Whip over pudding.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Serves 15.

title: kirsch's fresh apple cobbler
directions: Place apples in a 9-inch baking dish and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Boil 1 cup sugar and water to a syrup, about 5 minutes, then pour over apples.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Mix pineapple and pudding until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over cake.
Refrigerate.

title: banana slush punch
directions: Mix well and freeze.
Let slush before serving.
"Great hit."

title: salmon cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into a ball.
Chill 2 to 3 hours. Serve with crackers.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Boil broccoli and onion in chicken broth for about 10 minutes in covered pot. Melt butter and add flour. Add to broccoli mixture. Add half and half and white pepper to taste. Simmer low until hot. Do not boil. Top with cheese and bacon. Serves 2.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour over 4 pound or larger brisket, fat side up.
Cook brisket with sauce, covered, in 350° oven for 3 to 5 hours (depending on size of brisket).
Turn after one hour if possible; baste.

title: siberian meat dumplings
directions: Break egg into the flour and add salt; mix with water, a little at a time.
Knead into a stiff dough and leave in a cool place while you prepare the filling.
Fry the minced onion in butter until light.
Add meat and seasoning and break with a fork.
Roll out the dough into 1/8th-inch thickness.
Cut into small circles about 2 inches across.

Put 1 scant teaspoon of filling into the center of each circle and then dip your finger into cold water and wet the edge of each circle of dough completely around so edges will seal securely, then gently press edges again with tips of a fork's prongs.
To seal, bring the 2 corners together to form a pouch-like shape, and pinch edges together.
Drop into salted boiling water and cook, uncovered, for about 5 minutes until they rise to top.
Do not boil too vigorously or they might cook apart. Serve either in a clear soup (consomme) or as a separate course served with a side dish of sour cream and buttered.

title: pumpkin custard
directions: Combine milk, eggs, honey, vanilla, cinnamon, ginger and salt. Add pumpkin, blend well.
Pour into 6-ounce custard cups and bake in oven at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: michele's corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; bake in a large, oiled covered casserole dish for 1 hour at 350°.
Then sprinkle with about 1 cup of grated Cheddar or American cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: herbed-cheese omelet
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; add next 5 ingredients.
Mix well.
Combine eggs, water and 1/2 teaspoon white pepper; stir with a whisk until blended.
Heat a 10-inch heavy skillet over medium heat until hot.
Add olive oil and butter.
Pour egg mixture into skillet.
As mixture starts to cook, gently lift edges of omelet with a spatula and tilt pan so uncooked egg flows underneath.
Spoon cheese mixture in center and fold sides over filling.
Sprinkle with green onion.

title: french pork pie
directions: Put pork, onion and spices in pan with water to cover ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Drain liquid and save. Add mashed potato and liquid until moist.
Cool; put in pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until crust is brown.
Check at 30 minutes.

title: frank 'n chili manicotti ole
directions: Cook manicotti in boiling salted water according to package until just tender.
Drain; set aside.
Shred 2/3 of cheese; set aside.
Cut remaining cheese into 4-inch strips.
Slit frankfurters lengthwise; insert strip of cheese.
Place 1 cheese stuffed frank into each cooked manicotti.
Combine chili, tomatoes and jalapenos; spoon about 2 cups of mixture into bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange the 10 filled manicotti shells atop sauce in dish. Pour remaining chili mixture over.
Cover; bake in 350° for 25 minutes.
Uncover.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top.
Bake 10 minutes more.

title: low calorie jelly
directions: Add sweetener to equal 3 cups sugar; mix.
Let ingredients set
for five minutes to allow tapioca to soften.
Bring to
a boil and boil one minute.
Skim foam and pour into jars. Use any fruit juice.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 12-inch pan and mix in graham cracker crumbs, patting evenly in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, coconut and chopped nuts, layered in that order, pouring Eagle Brand milk over all.
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 35 minutes.

title: taco soup(low-fat)
directions: Mix cooked beef and remaining ingredients in a large pan. Simmer about 30 minutes.

title: cheese omelette
directions: 1. Put butter in pan over medium heat.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and drain well. While still hot, stir in dry taco seasoning mix.
Chop lettuce and tomatoes.
Toss together with ground beef mixture, cheese and taco sauce.
When ready to serve, crush corn chips over top and pour bottle of Ranch dressing over all.

title: chris' chicken
directions: Line baking dish with chipped beef.
Roll chicken breasts up and wrap with bacon slices; secure with toothpick.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken breasts.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 2 hours.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except potato chips and cheese. Toss lightly and heap into casserole dish.*
Sprinkle cheese on top and cover with potato chips. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes. Let cool and serve!

title: beef ragout
directions: In Dutch oven, melt butter.
Add celery and onion; cook and stir over medium heat until tender.
Add beef.
Brown over medium-high heat.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, wine vinegar, brown sugar, parsley flakes, paprika, oregano, garlic salt, caraway seed, cayenne and bay leaf.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until beef is tender, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve over rice or egg noodles. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: thalhimer's chicken salad
directions: Put chicken, celery, lemon juice and mayonnaise in a large bowl.
Stir to blend.
Add pepper and salt and mix thoroughly. Chill before serving.
Makes 8 (1/2 cup) servings.
Each serving contains about 165 calories, 13 grams fat (68% of calories from fat), 38 milligrams cholesterol and 264 milligrams sodium.

title: apple crisp oven pancakes(cholesterol-free)
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch).
Mix 1/4 cup baking mix, brown sugar, margarine and cinnamon; reserve.
Beat remaining ingredients with spoon.
Spread into pan.
Sprinkle with reserved brown sugar mixture.
Bake 14 to 16 minutes, until golden brown.
Cut into 6 pieces.
Serve immediately.

title: dirty rice
directions: Chop peppers and onions.
Add to hamburger and sausage.
Sear until gray.
Add broth and rice.
Cook slowly until rice is done. You will need a large pot.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Fry the ground chuck until brown. Add cooked macaroni, pizza sauce and ground chuck together in a large flat casserole dish. Spread Mozzarella cheese over top. Place sliced pepperoni on top of cheese. Bake in oven at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: chew bread
directions: Bake in long flat pan at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: date balls
directions: Melt oleo first.
Cook melted oleo and dates for 10 minutes (slowly).
Mix in other ingredients.
Roll into balls then roll in powdered sugar.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Cut up margarine and line bottom of baking dish.
Mix other ingredients except fruit and juice, pour over margarine.
Spoon fruit and juice over mixture.
Bake at 375° about 45 minutes. Serve hot.

title: brunch eggs
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch greased pan with bread.
Sprinkle grated cheese over this; add sausage.
Add 1 slice cheese over each bread slice.
Pour Egg Mix over cheese and meat.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Take out 1 hour before baking.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix flour, sugar and milk together.
Pour over margarine in pan.
Do not stir.
Spoon fruit over batter.
Do not stir.
Bake in 350° oven until solid, about 50 to 60 minutes until browned.
If using canned fruit, the juice may be substituted for milk.

title: strawberry shortcut cake
directions: Generously grease bottom only of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle marshmallows evenly over bottom of pan.
Thoroughly combine thawed strawberries and syrup with dry gelatin and set aside.
In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Blend at low speed until moistened.
Beat 3 minutes at medium.
Pour batter evenly over marshmallows and spoon strawberry mixture over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden.

title: lemon gooey
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine
and
1 egg.
Spread in pan (it will be like dough).
Mix
eggs,
cream
cheese
and sugar. Spread on top of dough
mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Let get completely
cold
before cutting in squares.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cut fruit into medium-sized pieces.
Sprinkle lightly with flour and toss to coat fruit.
Add pecans and mix well.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, measure, sift again with soda and spices.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk and orange juice.
Stir in fruits and pecans, mixing well.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased and floured baking sheet.
For more colorful cookies, you may want to top with half a red or green cherry.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Makes about 9 dozen cookies.

title: cranberry relish mold
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve syrup; add water to make 1/2 cup. Dissolve gelatin and sugar in 1 cup of hot water.
Add syrup and lemon juice.
Chill until partially set.
Add fruits, celery and nuts.
Chill in a 5-cup ring overnight.

title: pea salad
directions: Cook peas; season as usual.
Add small amount of butter to peas.
Add all other ingredients to peas when they are done.

title: bill's pumpkin bread
directions: I use a little more cinnamon and a little vanilla (1 teaspoon).
Also
I use white raisins instead of dates.

title: chutney
directions: In a pot, combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cook for 1/2 hour.
Let stand to cool.
Chill.
Store in refrigerator.
Yields 1 cup.

title: dilly potato salad
directions: Put potatoes in pot; cover with water. Cover pot and bring to boil.
Cook until tender. Drain and cool.
Put potatoes in large bowl; add eggs.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients. Pour over potatoes and toss to coat. Cover and refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: miracle whipped pound cake
directions: Cream the margarine and Crisco. Add sugar and cream well.
Add the eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Put in cold oven.
Turn to 325° and bake 1 hour. Turn to 350° and bake for 1/2 hour.

title: easy chicken and dumplings
directions: In a large pot, boil chicken pieces in water (enough to cover).
Remove water when chicken is tender and pulls away from the bone easily.
Set aside.
Add canned chicken broth to the water.
Bring to a boil.
Cut flour tortillas into strips.
Break the tortilla strips and drop them into the boiling liquid.
Cook for 18 minutes.
Stir gently.
Add margarine.
Take chicken from the bone and return chicken to the liquid.
Salt and pepper to taste.
You may increase this recipe according to number of people to be served.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine oil, eggs, sugar, zucchini and vanilla in a large mixing bowl; blend well.
Sift together dry ingredients and stir into zucchini mixture.
Do not beat.
Stir in nuts.
Spoon batter into two well-greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: fabulous banana dessert
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix instant pudding, condensed milk and sweet milk together for 2 minutes or until well blended. Refrigerate for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add the Cool Whip and the sour cream to the chilled milk and pudding mixture.
In a large dish, place a layer of vanilla wafers, a layer of sliced bananas and half of mixture.
Stream a little chocolate syrup on top.
Repeat each layer and garnish top with the chocolate syrup.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Keep popcorn hot and crisp in slow oven.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Mix and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Add milk.
Cook; stir until thick enough to spread, 20 minutes.
Then add butter.
Done in order written.

title: crab loaf
directions: Simmer pepper and onion in one tablespoon of butter until brown.
Make a sauce by adding flour, milk, pepper and salt.
Put crabmeat in bowl.
Add beaten eggs, mayonnaise, mustard, parsley and sauce.
Mold into a loaf and put in buttered loaf dish. Sprinkle with bread crumbs; dot with butter.
Bake 30 minutes in a 325° oven.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: carrot bundt cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Mix flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon and salt in large mixing bowl.
In a small bowl beat eggs slightly.
Stir in vanilla and oil.
Next, stir in carrots, applesauce, egg mixture and nuts into flour until moistened.
Spoon into Bundt pan.
Cook 1 hour and 20 minutes. Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Flip onto plate.
Mix powdered sugar with 5 tablespoons water until smooth.
Use this to ice the cake.

title: jambalaya
directions: Saute peppers and onions until onions are yellow.
Add and brown hamburg.
Mix seasonings; add with tomatoes and rice.
Stir well.
Place in greased casserole.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: feathered corn
directions: Soften cream cheese and butter.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Top with grated American cheese and put back in oven and turn oven off.
(Cheese will melt in about 10 minutes).

title: oven barbecue chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large saucepan, heat garlic and onions 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer 5 minutes. Place chicken in casserole dish with onions on top.
Pour sauce over top.
Bake for 1 hour, basting occasionally.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Combine ingredients; fold zucchini in last.
Spread on greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Drizzle with powdered sugar frosting (if desired).

title: shrimply delicious dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl of food processor and process until smooth.
Makes about 3 cups. Refrigerate.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine eggs, raisins and vanilla in bowl; cover and soak for 1 hour.
Cream butter and sugar; add flour, salt, cinnamon and soda.
Blend in egg, raisins and oatmeal.
Makes a stiff dough. Drop on ungreased sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown onion and ground beef.
Mix with soups and milk.
Boil about 3 minutes the egg noodles.
Add noodles to mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Triple recipe for large casserole.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and set aside.
Combine butter, sugar and eggs.
Stir in vanilla, orange peel and zucchini. Gradually stir until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Glaze on top.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients into banana/egg mixture.
Beat.
Bake in loaf pans at 350° for 15 minutes and then at 300° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool before cutting.
Peaches or apricots may be used instead of bananas.

title: corn scallop
directions: In bottom
of a 9 x 12-inch pan, place a little creamed corn. Layer
sliced
potatoes on top (half of potatoes), then layer onions,
then layer creamed corn and layer of potatoes. Season generously with salt and pepper.
Break up very finely the	Ritz crackers and place over the potatoes.
Cut up butter slices
and place over crackers.
Slowly pour the canned milk over entire casserole.	Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: cherry-pineapple angel cake
directions: Bake our angel food cake mix as directed.
Blend sugar, water, crushed pineapple and cherry flavored gelatin in saucepan.
Bring to boil; simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Chill until partially set, about 2 hours.
Whip the whipping cream; fold into gelatin mixture.
Spread generously on top and sides of angel cake.
Fill center of cake, too.
Chill 4 hours or overnight. Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: ground turkey or beef and vegetable fried rice(25 minutes)
directions: In large, nonstick skillet, brown turkey or beef, garlic and ginger over medium heat 8 to 10 minutes or until meat is no longer pink, breaking up into 3/4-inch crumbles.
Remove meat; pour off drippings.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend cream cheese in bowl until smooth.
Add fluff and blend well.
Add cinnamon.
Use over fruit cup or as a dip for fresh fruit chunks.
Refrigerate unused portions.

title: almond strips
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a mixing bowl, beat margarine or butter with an electric mixer on medium to high speed for 30 seconds.
Add about half of the flour, the sugar, egg, baking powder and almond extract.
Beat until thoroughly combined.
Beat in remaining flour.
Divide dough into 4 portions.
Shape each portion into a 12-inch long roll.
Place 2 rolls 4 to 5-inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Using your hand, flatten each to 3-inches wide.
Repeat with remaining rolls.
Brush flattened rolls with milk and sprinkle with almonds.
Bake in a 325° oven for 12 to 14 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Cut warm cookies diagonally into 1-inch strips.
Cool cookies on a wire rack.
Drizzle with icing.
Makes about 48.

title: oven roasted chicken and vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large plastic bag, add all ingredients. Close bag and shake until chicken and vegetables are evenly coated. Empty all into prepared baking dish.
Arrange chicken breast side up and bake, uncovered, basting half way through.
Bake 45 minutes or until chicken and vegetables are done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: danish fruit dessert
directions: Heat to boiling 1 cup liquid.
Combine jello, sugar and cornstarch.
Make a paste of it with remaining 1/2 cup liquid. Stir into boiling juice
until
thick and clear.
Cook about 1 minute.
Pour
this
over
fruit.
This
is
same
as
Danish Dessert.
It equals same as
one
box.
Pour this over a quart of fresh strawberries.
Put
in
jars and process in hot water bath just until boiling.

title: danish pork chops
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes.
Sprinkle lemon juice over apple pieces.

title: banana split cake
directions: Crust:
Mix 1 stick margarine (melted) with 2 1/2 cups graham crackers.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: danish coffee cake
directions: Mix together as for pie crust:
1 cup flour, 1/2 cup margarine and 1 tablespoon water.
Pat in 2 long strips and place on cookie sheet.
Set aside.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Place ingredients in Dutch oven in order given.
Cook 1 pound ground beef and drain well.
Crumble over the top of first 6 ingredients.
Pour over all the tomatoes.
Cover and cook on high until it starts cooking, then turn to low and cook
until rice is done and cabbage is tender.
Do not lift lid except to check rice. It takes usually 30 to 40 minutes for rice to cook.
When casserole is done, stir to blend flavors.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift flour once, then again with soda and salt.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until smooth.
Add peanut butter and stir well.
Add flour mixture and mix with wooden spoon until blended.
Add vanilla.
Form into 1-inch balls and place on cookie sheet.
Press with back of fork to make waffle design. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: potatoes
directions: One cup cheese goes in mix; 1 cup goes on top.
Microwave for 8 minutes.

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Cut squash in half. Scoop out seeds and strings.
Place in baking dish, cut side down.
Add a little water and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender. Remove and scoop out flesh.
Mash with butter and onions. Top with lots of black pepper or drizzle with pure maple syrup.

title: angel food cake dessert
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar; add sour cream, vanilla and almond extract.
Fold Cool Whip into cheese mixture.
Stir in cake pieces.
In another bowl, combine berries and sugar.
Layer berries, cake, berries.

title: bimini key lime pie
directions: Combine milk, cream cheese and lime juice in blender.
Blend on low speed until smooth.
Add vanilla and stir into mixture. Pour into graham cracker pie crust.
Chill in refrigerator until set.
Top with whipped cream before serving.
Serves 8.

title: no-bake chocolate truffle caramel pie
directions: Toast coarsely chopped pecans, then sprinkle over crust.
Put caramels and milk in small saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring frequently until caramels melt and mixture is smooth.
Pour over pecans.
Stir together chocolate chips, cream and butter in a heavy medium-size saucepan over low heat until chocolate melts and mixture is smooth.
Pour over caramel layer and refrigerate about 4 hours or until set.
Garnish with whipped cream, orange slices and fresh raspberries, if in season.
Keep refrigerated and serve cold. Serves 10.

title: spicy pear-carrot salad
directions: In large bowl, combine 2 tablespoons reserved liquid (from pears), vegetable oil, vinegar, sugar, ginger, salt and nutmeg. Add carrots and raisins; toss to blend.
Gently stir in pears. Refrigerate until chilled.
Serve on lettuce lined plates.

title: blueberry salad
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pie filling, pineapple and nuts.
Chill.
When set, top with a mixture of cream cheese, sour cream and sugar.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to direction on box; drain.
Mix broccoli, cheese, rice and soup together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana pie
directions: Slice bananas in round pieces in pie shell and spread evenly. Sprinkle with cinnamon, covering bananas lightly.
Pour sugar evenly over cinnamon and top with butter.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: quick pigs in a blanket
directions: Chop cabbage; spread in bottom of 13 x 9-inch greased baking dish.
Brown meat and onion.
Stir in rice, salt and pepper. Spoon over cabbage.
Heat tomato soup and tomato sauce to boiling with water.
Pour over all ingredients.
Put Mozzarella cheese and oregano on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix.
Put in covered Pyrex or container with top and freeze.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream the brown sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add milk and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and blend into sugar mixture.
Add nuts.
Roll in wax paper in log form.
Chill until very firm.
Slice into bars.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: green bean bundles
directions: Melt the ingredients in a saucepan. Pour over beans. Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.
Can do ahead.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix
together.
Place
in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
While baking, mix topping of 1/4 pound melted
margarine, 1 cup crushed crackers or corn flakes and
1 package
of
sliced
almonds.
After 25 minutes, remove casserole. Add
topping
and
bake another 10 to 15 minutes or until topping is brown.

title: hot mustard potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water, covered, about 25 minutes or until tender. Drain, peel and slice. Cook bacon until crisp.

Drain, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings in skillet. Crumble bacon; set aside. Add onion to skillet and cook until tender. Stir in sugar, flour and mustard. Add water and vinegar. Stir until smooth. Cook and stir until thick and bubbly. Stir in bacon and potatoes; cook about 5 minutes or until hot, tossing lightly.
Remove from heat and toss with parsley. Serve at once.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Add meat, onion and mushrooms. Cook and stir until browned.
Remove from skillet.
Add 2 tablespoons margarine; stir in flour, then add all other ingredients except sour cream.
Return meat to skillet and simmer about 1 hour until meat is tender.
Just before serving, stir in sour cream; heat, but do not boil.
Serve over hot rice or noodles.

title: coconut chews
directions: On waxed paper, stir flour and baking soda; set aside.
In large saucepan, melt butter over very low heat.
Remove from heat, stir in sugar, egg, vanilla and crumbs until smooth.
Gradually stir in flour until a smooth soft dough forms.
Stir in coconut. Cover tight and refrigerate at least 1 hour or up to 3 days.

title: corn chowder
directions: Place corn in 2 cup measuring cup; add milk or cream to 2 cup mark.
Chop potatoes, carrots and onion.
Saute margarine and onion in large kettle.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until potatoes are tender.
If you wish to thicken the chowder, mix together 1 tablespoon flour and 1/2 cup water.
Add to chowder and cook until thickened.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Force baked
potatoes
through	a sieve into the stock. Thicken with
the
yolk
of an egg.
When serving, place cream and parsley in	the
bottom of a warmed soup tureen; pour soup over it.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Serve at once.
Serves 6.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil and peel potatoes. Mash. Add sour cream, cream cheese, garlic salt and onion salt. Right before baking, sprinkle with paprika and grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: lemon cake
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in 1 cup hot water.
Put cake mix, 4 eggs, Wesson oil and cooled jello into bowl.
Mix with fork.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jane and johnny's biscuits
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Cut in shortening.
In separate bowl, mix egg and milk, then add all at once to flour mixture.
Mix and knead.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness and cut biscuits.
Put biscuits on greased baking pan and bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 24 biscuits.

title: hamburger oven meal
directions: Mix hamburger, onion and bell pepper together.
Place on foil and put your carrots and potatoes around it with salt and pepper. Close foil and pinch edges to seal.
Bake about 1 hour at 400°. Serve with tossed salad and rolls, if you like.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and diced onion.
Pour into baking dish.
Mix soup and 1 can water in bowl.
Pour rice over hamburger, then pour soup over hamburger and rice.
Mix.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Chop all vegetables.
Place all ingredients in 6-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil, turn down to low.
Simmer until vegetables are tender, 25 to 35 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: seasoned shrimp and rice
directions: Empty tomatoes in a bowl.
Squeeze in small pieces.
In a saucepan melt 2 tablespoons margarine.
Add rice.
Saute lightly, but do not brown rice.
Melt remaining margarine in heavy 3-quart pot.
Add onion and celery.
Saute until tender.

title: apple iced tea
directions: Pour boiling water over tea bags; steep for 3 minutes and remove the tea bags.
Let stand at room temperature until ready to serve.
Combine the tea, apple juice and lemon juice in a pitcher. Pour into ice filled glasses.
Add sugar to taste.

title: queso
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
May be heated at very low temperature. Serve as a dip for corn chips or raw vegetables. Makes 1 cup.

title: snow ice cream
directions: In a bowl, combine milk and vanilla. Quickly stir in fresh, clean snow, bit by bit, to taste.
You will have ice cream!

title: saucy chicken with artichokes and mushrooms
directions: Cut chicken in bite size pieces.
Place in plastic bag with flour and shake until chicken pieces are well coated.
Melt butter in large skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken and cook 5 minutes on each side until golden brown.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Drain drippings from pan.
Add artichokes and next 5 ingredients.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce is thickened (low heat).
Add cheese and stir for 1 to 2 minutes.
Serve over hot cooked noodles. Spinach noodles make a pretty dish.

title: quesadillas
directions: In a large heavy skillet, saute meat.
Add garlic salt, onion powder and salt.
Mix well.
Set aside.
Clean skillet.
Saute bell pepper; set aside.
Saute onion; set aside.
Clean skillet and melt a pat of oleo in skillet, turning heat to medium-low, lay one tortilla, then add ground meat on one half of tortilla.
Sprinkle bell pepper over meat, then onions and top with grated cheese. Fold tortilla over cheese.
Brown on both sides.
Cut in serving size.
Serve with sour cream if desired.
Serves 4.

title: man pleasing casserole
directions: Cook noodles; brown meat and add tomato sauce.
Blend sour cream, cream cheese and onions.
In casserole dish, alternate 1/2-inch layer of noodles, meat mixture, cheese mixture, ending with noodles.
Top with grated cheese.
Heat in oven at 350° for 20 or 30 minutes.
A full meal with garlic bread, fresh green salad and iced tea.

title: southwest corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Spread evenly in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until deep golden brown and a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes; cut into squares.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Beat egg and sugar.
Add melted butter with other ingredients. Bake in unbaked pie shell for 50 to 60 minutes at 300°.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix together and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken viennoise
directions: Pound chicken fillets with mallet until thin.
Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper.
Beat eggs and pour into flat plate.
Pour flour and bread crumbs onto 2 additional flat plates.
Prepare garnishes before cooking meat and serve in small bowls.
Heat oil. Dredge chicken slices in flour.
Dip in egg, then bread crumbs. Cook until brown on one side.
Flip and repeat.
Arrange on platter.
Heat butter in skillet until it foams and pour over meat.
Serve with rice.

title: cow pies
directions: In a double boiler over simmering water, melt chocolate chips and shortening, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat; stir in raisins and almonds.
Drop by tablespoonful onto waxed paper. Chill until ready to serve.

title: red riding hood soup
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add tomato sauce, stewed tomatoes and brown gravy mix.
Stir.
Add water, dry onion soup mix, beef bouillon, sugar, mixed veggies and barley.
Simmer for 45 minutes. Serves 8.

title: microwave praline candy
directions: Butter 3-quart mixing bowl.
Stir in sugar, baking soda, buttermilk and butter.
Microwave at 50% for 30 to 40 minutes or until a soft ball forms in cold water, stirring 2 or 3 times during cooking.
Add vanilla.
Beat at high speed with mixer until soft peaks form.
Stir in pecans then drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Cool until firm.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: cracked sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven.
Grease cookie sheets.
Sift together flour, baking soda and cream of tartar on wax paper.
Set mixture aside.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In a medium bowl, combine beans, milk, cream of mushroom soup, pepper and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Top with remaining onions; bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes or until onions are golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: berry purple smoothie
directions: In blender container, combine all ingredients; process until smooth.
Serve immediately or cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: fried salmon
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Pat into small patties and fry fast on pretty high heat in little shortening.
Cook on both sides.

title: ethel's molasses cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of loaf pan.
Mix baking mix, flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder, water, molasses and egg until moistened.
Pour into pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes. Serve with Orange Butter Frosting.

title: ann lander's meat loaf
directions: Mix together all except bacon and tomato sauce.
Put in loaf pan.
Cover with bacon strips.
Pour tomato sauce over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Any leftovers make great meat loaf sandwiches. We never have much left over.

title: florentine scalloped potatoes(6 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Butter a 2-quart casserole dish.
In a mixing bowl, stir together all ingredients, except 1/2 cup of cheese and sliced potatoes.
In the prepared casserole dish, layer sauce alternately with potatoes, beginning and ending with sauce. Cover.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Uncover.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake an additional 15 minutes.
Makes a great side dish.

title: hot ryes
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except bread.
Spread on party rye or pumpernickel and bake at 375° for 10 or 15 minutes until browned.

title: sour cream pudding
directions: Combine pudding mix, sugar and water in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Stir in sour cream, blending well.
Pour into bowl or dessert dishes.
Chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vidalia onion casserole #2
directions: Cook
onions
in
margarine
until
clear.
Reserve
3 tablespoons
of
cracker crumbs for top.
Put remaining crumbs in bottom
of a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Add soup and onions alternately.
Combine eggs and milk;
pour over onions. Top
with cheese
and remaining cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: mints
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
If necessary, add more powdered sugar to make mixture firm.
Press into mint forms, then pop out.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine
flour,
baking
soda,	salt, baking powder and cinnamon and set aside.
Mix together oil and sugar well!
Add eggs
one at a time to oil and sugar mixture.
Beat well after each.
Gradually add dry ingredients.
Add carrots.
Mix well. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: oreo ice cream pie
directions: You will need a 12-inch pie carrier (Tupperware) or 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: bonbons
directions: Mix milk and oleo, gradually adding sugar.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Make into small balls and freeze.
Melt chips and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip balls in hot mixture with toothpicks.
Place on wax paper to cool.

title: remarkable fudge
directions: Butter sides of a 3-quart saucepan.
Add the sugar, milk and butter.
Cook over medium heat to soft ball stage (236°), stirring often.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate chips until almost melted. Stir in marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: chocolate snack things
directions: Melt chocolate in microwave.
In large bowl, add chocolate, peanut butter and remaining ingredients.
Stir together well. Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet and cool in refrigerator.

title: party pork chops
directions: Season pork chops with salt and pepper.
Brown on both sides in lightly greased, hot skillet.
Put chops in baking dish.
Top each with a slice of onion, 1 tablespoon rice and cover with whole tomatoes.
Add remaining tomatoes and juice to dish.
Cover.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350° or until tender.
Serves 4.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: In a skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Saute onion until tender.
Stir in potatoes and fry until golden brown.
In a medium bowl, combine soup, milk, and Cheddar cheese; mix well. Put fried potatoes into a casserole dish and pour soup mixture over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until heated through.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix in order given in a large bowl.
Store in a covered container.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix like corn bread the cornmeal, buttermilk, eggs and salt. Add bell pepper, onion and cream-style corn.
Pour 1/2 batter in greased skillet (heated). Spread over skillet with spoon (wet to spread well). Add the cheese evenly over batter.
Add the remaining batter on top of cheese, covering all with remaining cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 40 minutes.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. With pastry blender or mixer, cut in butter until crumbly.
Stir in eggs, cream and vanilla.
Blend well. Refrigerate dough, if desired. Roll out dough on floured surface to 1/8-inch thickness. Cut into desired shapes with cookie cutters.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets. Sprinkle with sugar, if desired. Bake at 400° for 5 to 8 minutes until light brown. Cool.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix well and chill for 4 hours.
Good with pintos or other dried beans. Refrigerate.

title: megan's favorite meal
directions: Put mashed potatoes in a bowl.
Place heated SpaghettiOs on top. Caution:
Not too hot!
May substitute 1/2 cup peas for SpaghettiOs.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; chill before serving.

title: grilled chicken teriyaki
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a small bowl; stir well.

Place chicken in a shallow dish; pour soy sauce mixture over chicken. Cover and marinate in refrigerator 8 hours, turning occasionally. Remove chicken from marinade; place marinade in a small saucepan. Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Coat grill rack with cooking spray; place on grill over medium-hot coals.
Place chicken on rack and cook 20 to 25 minutes, until chicken is tender, turning and basting frequently with reserved marinade.
Yields 6 servings.
Protein 28.7, fat 3.4, carbohydrate 6.4, cholesterol 78, iron 1.0, sodium 589 and calcium 17.

title: cabbage
directions: Put cabbage and potatoes in dish, chip up butter on top.
Add water, salt and pepper.
Microwave 6 to 8 minutes.
Stir and cover 6 to 8 minutes.

title: hank's dip
directions: Dice egg; chop or mince garlic and combine the 2.
Add only enough oil to make it stick together.
You could add 1 tablespoon mayo.

title: cucumber soup
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add broth, water, cucumbers, potatoes and salt to taste.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Serve cold or warm.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix butter and sugar together and simmer slowly for about 5 minutes.
Stir constantly while mixture simmers.
Let mixture cool and add one egg at a time, beating well.
Add vinegar and salt to mixture.
Pour mixture in pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then lower temperature to 350° and continue to cook for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: butterscotch pecan log
directions: Melt over hot (not boiling) water the butterscotch morsels. Remove from water.
Stir in Eagle Brand, vanilla and chopped pecans.
Chill until firm.
Shape into a 12-inch roll.
Mark surface lengthwise with fork.
Brush with slightly beaten egg white.
Press pecan halves into entire surface of roll.
Wrap in wax paper; chill.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices with sharp knife. Yields approximately 2 dozen slices.

title: fruit tea
directions: Boil tea bags with cinnamon sticks in water.
Add sugar.
Pour in gallon container.
Then add orange juice and lemonade.
Add water to fill container.

title: stuffed flank steak teriyaki
directions: Cut pocket in flank steak (pocket opens at short end of steak).
Combine soy sauce, oil, molasses, mustard, ginger and garlic.
Pour marinade inside pocket and over meat.
Let stand at least 1 hour, turning occasionally.

title: sweet and sour bean salad
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
(I use a plastic container with cover to shake occasionally.)
Chill well before serving.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix first five ingredients together and make
well in the center.
Into this pour eggs and oil.
Mix well.
Fold in frozen strawberries (after thawed and drained).
Add lemon extract.
Pour into greased and floured 8 x 4-inch loaf pans.
Makes 2 loaves. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: christmas salad
directions: In a mixing bowl, blend together sour cream, whipped cream, sugar, lemon juice and vanilla.
Fold in fruit and nuts.

title: tortellini pasta salad
directions: Cook tortellini as directed on package and pour over the frozen vegetables in strainer (use pasta and liquid both).
Let cool.
Add green pepper, cheese and meat.
Slice olives and add to mixture.
Mix with enough Hidden Valley Ranch dressing.
Make evening before serving.
Add more dressing if dry.

title: homemade pate(leverpostei)
directions: Cook shallots in 1 tablespoon butter until soft.
Remove shallots from pan.
Add remaining butter and saute chicken livers over a quick fire for 4 or 5 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Pour brandy over livers and ignite.
Remove pan from heat and add shallots, cream, tarragon, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture into a blender and blend until smooth and creamy.
Pour mixture into a jar or bowl and chill 4 hours.

title: crusty baked eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant, if you wish; cut into 1/2-inch slices. Sprinkle salt on both sides of slices.
Let stand for 30 minutes. Rinse with water and pat dry.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Cream margarine until soft.
Add sugar, gradually, continuing to beat until light and fluffy.
Beat eggs, using mix-stir.
Add syrup, honey and vanilla.
Blend thoroughly.
Slowly beat egg mixture into margarine-sugar mixture.
Add 1 cup pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Arrange remaining 1 cup pecans on top.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes at 350°. Cool.
Top with whipped cream if desired. Serves 6 to 8.

title: aunt jo's baked beans
directions: Brown ground chuck.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook on low heat 4 to 6 hours in crock-pot or in oven for about 1 hour at 300°.
Can place bacon strips on top, if oven cooked.
Great meal with green salad and hot bread.

title: calico ham casserole(serves 25)
directions: Day ahead, cook vegetables as per label.
Meanwhile in a large kettle, melt 1/4 cup butter.
Add bread and toss well.
Remove buttered crumbs and set aside.
In bowl mix flour with salt, pepper, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, slowly stir in 2 cups milk. Heat rest of milk in same large kettle used for crumbs.
Then stir in flour mixture and 3/4 cup butter.
Cook over low heat stirring often until smooth and thickened.
Add onion and cheese.
Cook stirring often until cheese is melted.
Add drained vegetables and ham.
Pour into 2 (12 x 8 x 2-inch) baking dishes.
Refrigerate along with crumbs.
About 1 hour before serving, heat oven to 350°. Sprinkle top of each baking dish with buttered crumbs.
Bake uncovered about 40 minutes until hot.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Heat water and bouillon cube to a boil.
Add the broccoli and carrot.
Cook according to the broccoli package directions; then remove from heat. Do not drain. In a separate pan, melt the butter and slowly stir in the flour.
Continue stirring while gradually adding the milk.
Stir in the cheese, onion flakes, Worcestershire sauce, and soup.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add the broccoli and carrot mixture (the chicken if desired) and cook over low heat until reaching the desired degree of thickness.

title: pineapple torte
directions: Beat egg yolks in medium size pan.
Stir in 1/2 cup sugar, salt and syrup off pineapple.
Stir over low heat just to a boil (no longer).
Cool.
Stir in pineapple and lemon juice.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Beat in 2 tablespoons sugar, one tablespoon at a time, until stiff peaks form.
Beat cream until stiff.
Fold cream and egg whites into pineapple mixture.

title: grandma's casserole
directions: In Dutch oven, saute onion and green pepper in butter or margarine for 3 minutes.
Add ground chuck and brown meat, breaking up meat with spoon as it cooks.
Add seasoned salt, monosodium glutamate (optional), pepper and sugar.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce and water.
Heat mixture to boiling, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, layer tomato meat mixture, and noodles.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Make sure noodles are well covered by sauce.
Cover pan with aluminum foil and bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Cut and serve as you would lasagna.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all together.
Put in three 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet sour cabbage
directions: Combine all ingredients; cover tightly and steam over low heat until cabbage is tender.
About 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: wild rice salad
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions omitting fat. Combine rice, corn and next 2 ingredients in a large bowl; set aside.
Combine lemon juice and next 4 ingredients.
Pour over rice mixture, tossing gently.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours.
Before serving, sprinkle with sunflower kernels.
Serve on lettuce leaves. Makes 14 servings.

title: handmade ornaments
directions: Mix the cornstarch and baking soda in a saucepan and add the water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until the mixture is the consistency of wet mashed potatoes.
Turn it out onto a plate, cover it with a damp cloth; let cool.
When cool, knead it until it's smooth.
Seal it in a plastic bag and store in the refrigerator.
Shape ornaments by hand or flatten the dough and use cookie cutters to cut out shapes.
Insert a wire hanger into soft dough, then let the ornaments dry overnight or heat them in a 250° oven for 15 minutes.

title: aunt carrie's chocolate pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa in bowl with a little milk.
Make a paste, then add melted margarine and mix well.
Add milk and vanilla.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then turn to 375° and cook until knife comes out clean.

title: never fail meringue
directions: Mix cornstarch with 2 Tbsp. sugar in small sauce pan. Add water, stir and cook over medium heat stirring constantly until thick and clear. Beat egg whites with salt and vanilla until soft peak forms. Gradually add remaining sugar beating well after each Tbsp. Add hot mixture, continue beating until stiff peaks form. Spoon over your favorite filling. Bake at 350 degrees for 12-15 minutes.

title: chewy chocolates
directions: Place 2 pecan halves and a date half in clusters on a lightly buttered baking sheet.
Melt caramels in saucepan over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Spoon caramel mixture over each cluster, leaving ends of pecans uncovered.
Let stand until set, about 30 minutes.
Spread chocolate over caramel.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix oil, oleo or margarine, sugar and egg.
Mix well, then add flour, soda and salt together.
Add to first mixture, then add vinegar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet until edges are brown.

title: baked dough ornaments
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Knead like bread dough until smooth.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with cookie cutters or fashion ornaments by hand.
(Use small portion of dough at a time.
Cover remaining dough with a damp towel.)
Place ornaments on cookie sheet.
Make a hole at top for hanging.
Bake at 325° about 1 hour.
Color with food coloring before baking or paint ornaments when cool.

title: sweet and sour marinade for chicken, shrimp or steak
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour over chicken, shrimp or steak in a Ziploc baggie or marinade container.
Marinate for at least 2 hours, turning occasionally.

title: dreamsicle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box except replace water with milk and add the orange flavoring.
Bake as directed on box and let cool.
Cut layers in half (dental floss works good for this).

title: banana waffles
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix just until moistened, but still slightly lumpy.
Pour into greased waffle iron.
Close lid quickly and do not open while baking.

title: 24 hour fruit salad
directions: Put eggs, vinegar and sugar in top of a double boiler and cook until thick, then add butter.
Put in a large bowl to cool.
Whip cream and add to dressing.
Be sure dressing is cool.
Add fruit, well drained, then marshmallows.
Mix well.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: Blend eggs, sugar, and milk.
Add cocoa, flour,
butter,
and vanilla.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into 2 unbaked 9 inch pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until firm.
Add nuts or coconut if desired.

title: white enchiladas
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; set aside.
Cut the 2 pound bar of cheese into 8 long bars.
Coat the top of a flour tortilla with some of the soup mixture.
Sprinkle some green onions over it and roll up one bar of cheese at a time, 8 bars rolled up fit into an 8 1/2 x 13-inch pan or Pyrex dish.
Spread the remaining soup mixture over the top and bake at 350° for approximately 30 to 45 minutes. Leftover chicken or beef can be added to this.
Serve with a green salad after soccer practice!!

title: potato supreme
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix all other ingredients plus margarine. Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Put bottom crusts in two pie pans.
Divide the ingredients between the two pies.
Place the top crusts on the pies, crimp the edges and cut 4 slits across the top.
Place in a 350° oven and bake for about 45 minutes or until crust reaches desired brown.

title: seasoned potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes, wash, cut into wedges. Combine next three ingredients in a gallon plastic self sealing bag. Mix together, thoroughly combining butter with seasonings. Add potato wedges, coat well with butter mixture. Place wedges on foil covered cookie sheet. Bake at 350° till potatoes are tender.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: With electric beater, beat together sugar, flour, baking soda, eggs, vanilla, salt and can of fruit cocktail.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan, lightly greased and floured.
Sprinkle brown sugar and chopped nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a 9-inch skillet, heat oil.
Add onions, green peppers, garlic and broth/seasoning mix.
Saute until onions are translucent.
In mixing bowl, combine sauteed vegetables with remaining ingredients.
Shape into a loaf and place in an 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Bake until browned, about 45 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: easy hamburger soup
directions: Brown hamburger, drain.
Add to soup starter and water according to soup directions.
Cook as directed on soup starter package.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling, salted water until tender; drain. Melt butter; blend in flour.
Add milk.
Cook and stir until thick.
Add onion and cheese; stir until cheese is melted.
Mix sauce with macaroni.
Bake in 1 1/2-quart casserole at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly and browned.

title: yogurt fruit dip
directions: Stir together yogurt, preserves and cinnamon.
Slice fruit and serve with dip.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken meal in one
directions: In ungreased 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish combine hash browns, green beans and carrots.
Top with chicken and combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken and veggies.
Cover and bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Uncover and bake 25 to 30 minutes longer.

title: crock pot tropical tea
directions: In a 5-quart crockpot, combine boiling water and tea bags. Cover and let stand for 5 minutes. Discard tea bags. Stir in the remaining ingredients. Cover and cook on low for 2-4 hours, or until heated through. Serve warm. Yields approximately 2-1/2 quarts.

title: graham cracker things
directions: Boil margarine, butter and sugar 2 to 3 minutes.
Put crackers on flat pan.
Place one pecan half on each cracker.
Pour mixture over crackers.
Bake for 10 minutes at 325°.
Take off pan immediately; place on foil to cool.

title: strawberry-rhubarb pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry and set aside.
Put 1/2 of the strawberries and rhubarb into pastry lined pie plate.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of the sugar mixture.
Repeat with remaining strawberries and rhubarb.
Add sugar mixture.
Dot with margarine.
Cover edge of pastry with aluminum foil to prevent excessive browning.
Remove foil during last 15 minutes of baking.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Saute onion, green pepper and celery in butter. Cook broccoli and drain.
Combine with Cheez Whiz, vegetables, undiluted soup and mushrooms.
Fold in cooked rice and put into 3-quart buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly (about 20 to 30 minutes).
(Can be made a day ahead and baked just before serving.)

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown hamburger meat; mix carrots in hamburger meat when done. Prepare gravy mix and add to meat and carrots.
Cook potatoes and mash like creamed potatoes.
Put in a casserole dish.
Spread a layer of potatoes on top of mixture.
Slice cheese and put on top of potatoes.
Bake until cheese is melted and mixture is bubbly.

title: baked eggs
directions: Crumble bacon in bottom of individual baking dishes.
Place grated cheese on top, then another layer of bacon and cheese. Break egg on top.
Place in oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Bake at 375° approximately 45 minutes.
Serve warm with Sauce.

title: hip patter bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine milk, 2 tablespoons butter and chocolate in top of double boiler.
Cook over hot (not boiling) water until chocolate melts.
Add vanilla and cool.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix ingredients except cheese and 1/2 cup of the onion rings. Pour into greased casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining onion rings on top and return to oven until bubbly and cheese is melted.

title: mexican cornbread with ground meat
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and set aside.
Brown ground meat; drain off excess grease and spread cooked meat on paper towels to drain.
Prepare onion, cheese and peppers; place in separate mounds, ready to use.

title: chocolate chip cookies(doubled)
directions: Combine shortening, sugars, vanilla and eggs.
Add flour, soda and salt slowly to mixture.
Mix in chips and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 8 minutes.
Makes about 50 cookies.

title: pineapple treasures
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs and mix well. Gradually add dry ingredients.
Add coconut, nuts and Treasures. Drop onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Allow to stand before removing from sheets.
Bake at 375°.
Yields 36 servings.

title: orange pineapple sherbet
directions: Combine and freeze in ice cream maker until firm.
Let "ripen" for 1 hour before serving.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Mix all ingredients together. Form into 1 inch balls. Bake 15 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet. Makes about 6 dozen.

title: ziti with turkey sauce
directions: In large saucepan, heat oil.
Add onion and carrots.
Cook, stirring, for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add turkey and oregano and cook 3 to 4 minutes or until turkey is no longer pink, stirring to break up meat.
Add wine and cook 2 minutes or until liquid evaporates. Stir in tomatoes, chicken broth, tomato paste and parsley.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chopstick chicken
directions: Cook the chicken breasts in boiling salted water for 30 minutes.
Remove skin and bones and cut chicken in bite sized pieces.
Add the soup, water, celery, cashews, onions and half the noodles.
Place into a 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle remaining noodles in ring around edge of casserole and cover center with mandarin orange slices.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat with onion and drain.
Add tomato paste to meat. Mix well.
Next, add tomato juice, sauce mix packet, butter, cinnamon and sugar.
Simmer on stove for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Grease 2-quart casserole dish. Put broccoli in dish and top with grated cheese.
Add mushroom soup.
Pour milk over top.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven; add French fried onions.
Return to oven for 5 minutes; watch carefully because onions burn very easily.

title: chili bean dip
directions: Place beans, vinegar, water, chili powder and cumin in blender container; blend until smooth.
Pour into a bowl.
Add onion and parsley.
Serve with raw vegetables, if desired.

title: no bake granola bars
directions: In large saucepan melt margarine. Remove from heat.
Stir in brown sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Return to heat. Cook and stir until bubbly.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Press mixture into a buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Chill in the refrigerator for 2 hours or freeze for 1 hour.
Makes 24 bars.
(Keep leftovers in the refrigerator.)

title: refrigerator rolls(foolproof)
directions: Boil 1 cup of water.
Sit off stove.
Add butter and shortening; stir until melted.
Add sugar and salt; cool to lukewarm.
In bowl, add 1 cup warm water; sprinkle yeast and stir to dissolve.
Add sugar, butter and shortening to dissolve yeast. Add 3 cups of self-rising flour; beat until smooth.
Add 3 cups of plain flour slowly to make a thick dough.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Heat milk in a small saucepan just until bubbles appear around edge.
Cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast and sugar over very warm water in a medium bowl.
(Very warm water should feel comfortably warm on wrist.)
Stir to dissolve yeast.
Let stand until bubbly, about 10 minutes.
Stir in cooled milk.
Combine flour, salt and baking powder in a larger bowl.
Cut in butter with a pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.
Make a well in the dry ingredients; pour in milk-yeast mixture.
Stir until soft dough forms.
Turn out onto floured surface.
Knead dough, 15 to 20 minutes, using as little flour as possible.
Invert a bowl over dough; let dough rest for 10 minutes.
Pour enough oil into a heavy kettle or deep fryer to make 2 1/2 to 3-inches depth.
Heat to 400°.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach thoroughly in cold water.
Tear off and discard stems and blemished leaves.
Spread leaves on paper towel to drain and pat completely dry with fresh paper towels.
Tear leaves into 1-inch pieces and place in bowl.
Fry bacon over moderate heat, turning frequently until crisp and brown.
Transfer to paper towel; drain and crumble.
Hard-boil the eggs; cool and slice. Wash grapes; pat dry and slice in half.
Chop walnuts.
Add bacon, grapes, eggs and nuts to spinach; toss.
Add poppy seed dressing; toss gently.

title: breakfast sausage & egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into an 11 x 7 x 2 casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6-8.

title: creamy broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in an 8-inch square baking dish coated with nonstick cooking spray.
Combine soup and lemon juice; pour over broccoli.
Toss stuffing and margarine; sprinkle over soup mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Uncover; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes longer or until cheese is melted. Yield:
7 servings.

title: vegetable squares
directions: Spread crescent rolls out in a cookie sheet and press seams together.
Pinch edge to form a rim.
Bake for 7 to 9 minutes at 350°.
Mix together cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix. Spread on baked crescent rolls.
Cover with vegetables and press into mixture.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Chill and cut into bars.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Crush cranberries in blender; add sugar and pineapple.
Let set in bowl 15 minutes.
Add other ingredients.
Serve cold.
Great for holidays.

title: grandma weiss' chicken and dumplings
directions: Brown chicken in small amount of oil in large pot or pressure cooker.
Drain off oil.
Cover chicken in pot with water; add salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and simmer until tender, about 1 hour. While cooking, mix dumplings.

title: sue's punch
directions: Mix and chill.
Ice may be added.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the cooked bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When done, layer 1/2 pound bacon on top of beans for an appetizing look.

title: meatless lasagna
directions: Cook noodles. Cook spinach and chop finely. Combine with Ricotta cheese and eggs. Place half of noodles in medium baking dish. Cover with half of vegetable mixture, half of Mozzarella and half of spaghetti sauce. Repeat layers. Top with parsley. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 35 minutes. Let stand 15 minutes before cutting.

title: peanut butter dip
directions: Mix until creamy.
Serve with slices of fresh fruit.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine crackers and margarine.
Spread into bottom of dish. Combine in a large skillet, oil, green pepper and onion.
Cook 5 minutes and add flour, salt, sugar and milk.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly; cook 1 minute more.
Remove from heat and add 1 can cream-style corn and 2 eggs, slightly beaten.
Pour into dish; top with cracker crumbs.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: gingerbread pound cake with lemon curd topping
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 3-quart mold or 9-inch tube pan.
Sift flour with spices and set aside.
Beat butter and sugar until fluffy in a large bowl.
Add eggs one at a time, beating until light and fluffy.
Turn into prepared pan.
Cook
1 hour and 10 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.

title: quick potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onion until potatoes are tender.
Add soups. Cook until completely heated, approximately 3 to 5 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except the margarine and crackers.
Put into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix crackers and melted margarine together and spread on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: hershey-almond pie
directions: Melt Hershey bars just until melted (about 2 minutes in the microwave does it).
Allow chocolate to cool so that it can still be stirred but is no longer hot.
Whip the whipping cream until it makes fluffy peaks.
Fold the chocolate into the whipping cream until evenly mixed together. Pile mixture into the pie crust and refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients, add dry jello and strawberries.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until done. Punch holes in cake with large fork. Pour icing over cake while hot.
(Note:
The longer this cake sets the better it tastes.)

title: spaghetti and meatballs
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Make tiny meatballs.
Brown in little grease in Dutch oven.
Remove meatballs and cook chopped onions until done.
Add tomato sauce and enough water to make as thin as you like and add meatballs and cook for 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: lima bean-broccoli casserole
directions: Let lima
beans and broccoli thaw; add rest of ingredients and mix.
Pour
into lightly buttered baking dish.
Melt margarine and
pour
over
cereal.
Spread on top of vegetable mixture. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: baby ruth bars
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil and remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, peanuts and cornflakes.
Mix well.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Melt chocolate bits and butterscotch bits in a double boiler.
Spread over bars.
Cool and cut.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except hash browns.
Stir in potatoes.
Top with 2 cups corn flakes mixed with 1/2 cup melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (uncovered).
Cover and bake additional 15 minutes.
tags: cream of chicken soup or mushroom

title: gary's chicken recipe
directions: Pan-fry chicken, coated in flour mixture (flour, salt, paprika and pepper).
Mix soup, sour cream and mushrooms together well. Place cooked chicken in a casserole dish and pour soup sauce all over.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle on grated cheese and just put back in oven until cheese bubbles.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Mix together all ingredients; store in refrigerator.
Use over cream cheese, with crackers or as a glaze for roasted meats.

title: caraway seed buns
directions: Cut shortening into dry ingredients.
Add caraway seed (or one cup currants).
Mix well.
Make well in center.
Pour sponge into well and mix lightly as for bread.
Use more warm milk if necessary.
Let rise again until doubled in bulk and form into buns.
Let buns double in bulk.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: poppy seed bread(almost like a cake)
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients together.
Blend next 4 ingredients together, then blend both together.
Put in greased loaf pans and bake about 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 large loaves or 5 mini loaves.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat shortening until creamy.
Add sugar, beaten eggs and then dry ingredients.
Add bananas and nuts.
Bake in loaf pan (divide into 2 loaf pans for best results) at 350°.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
Boil for 2 minutes and stir constantly.
Add remaining ingredients; stir in well.
Drop by spoonfuls on paper.
Cool.

title: beef in potato shells
directions: Bake potatoes until soft.
Heat oven to 475°.
Cut each potato lengthwise into halves.
Scoop out potato, leaving 1/4-inch shell.
Brush outsides and insides of potatoes with margarine. Place shells, cut side up, on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake, uncovered, until edges are brown (15 to 20 minutes).

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order.
Beat well.
Bake in greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage wedges in a heavy saucepan in a small amount of boiling, salted water for 10 minutes or until tender; drain. Arrange in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Saute green peppers and onions in butter in saucepan until tender.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk.
Cook until mixture is thick and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Pour over the cabbage.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Combine mayonnaise, cheese and chili sauce in a bowl; mix well.
Spoon over wedges.
Bake for 5 minutes longer.
Serves 8.

title: pink dessert
directions: Mix all together, Cool Whip last. Put in refrigerator. Cool well before serving.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Fry, mash and drain hamburger.
Grind onions and garlic cloves.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, red pepper and salt.
Cook slowly for 3 hours.
Last half hour, add 1 small can mushrooms (optional).
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Makes enough sauce for 1 1/2 pounds of spaghetti.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 2-quart casserole dish.
Combine all ingredients in order given.
Place in dish.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Continue baking for an additional 45 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper together.
Layer 6 slices bread, 1/2 of cheese, 1/2 of sausage, 6 slices of bread and rest of mixture over all.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken au vin
directions: Place chicken pieces in frypan.
Add cherries, wine and marmalade.
Heat to boil.
Turn down and simmer for 1 hour.
Baste occasionally with sauce.

title: strawberry truffle(quick!)
directions: 1990 state award winning pie for the Crisco All-American Pie Bake Off.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until lemon colored.
Beat in sugar and oil.
In large bowl add egg mixture, vanilla and zucchini to dry mix.
Pour batter into 2 well greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done.
Bake at 350°.

title: wyoming whopper cookies
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Blend in sugars, eggs and peanut butter.
Mix until smooth.
Add oats, soda, raisins and chocolate chips. (Mixture will be sticky.)
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: vanilla refrigerator cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and roll into roll and refrigerate until cold.
Slice and bake in greased cookie sheet in 350° oven until done.

title: wild rice and pecan stuffing
directions: Bring 6 1/2 cups stock and bay leaf to boil in large saucepan. Add wild rice.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 30 minutes. Add long grain rice; cover and cook until both rices are tender and stock is absorbed, about 20 minutes more.
Transfer to large bowl.

title: easy icing
directions: Beat butter and shortening in a large bowl until the mix is light and fluffy.
Add powdered sugar, 1 cup at a time, beating the mixture between each cup.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Add 2 tablespoons milk and beat quickly until icing is light, thick and fluffy.
For smoother icing, add more milk.
Add food coloring and mix until desired color.

title: fudge
directions: Place nuts, vanilla, margarine and chocolate chips into large bowl.
Combine
sugar, marshmallows and milk in saucepan and bring to a boil.	Boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Pour hot mixture over
contents of bowl.
Stir until chips are melted. Pour into buttered	pan
or
dish.	To
make
peanut butter fudge, add 2/3 cup peanut butter.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease

long casserole dish. Crumble 1/2 box crackers, add sliced chicken and sliced water chestnuts. Blend soups and sour cream; pour over chicken and chestnuts. Add remaining box of crackers crumbled. Cut oleo over top. Heat at 350° for about 30 min.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease baking sheet with shortening.
Combine shortening, egg, milk, vanilla and brown sugar in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Combine oats, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon into the creamy mixture at a low speed, just until blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts. Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of dough 2 inches apart into a baking sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool 2 minutes on a cooling rack.

title: grandma's sunday salad
directions: Cook sugar, flour, egg yolks and pineapple juice until it becomes a glaze or boils.
Let cool.
Add drained pineapple, marshmallows and whipped cream.
Chill.

title: grandmother brown's vegetable soup
directions: Cook corn and tomatoes separate.
When done, mix together. Cook onions, peppers, lima beans, okra, carrots, green peas and hot pepper together.
When done mix all together.
Add salt and sugar.
Simmer 20 minutes and seal in sterilized jars.
When you decide to eat soup, cook 4 or 5 potatoes and 2 onions until tender.
Add a quart of canned soup and a pint of canned tomatoes. Bring to a boil and then simmer for 20 minutes.
Season as desired.
Bacon or fatback seasoning is very good.

title: coca-cola chicken
directions: Place chicken in large skillet.
Combine in bowl, catsup, Coke and lemon juice.
Stir and pour over chicken.
Cover and simmer one hour or until chicken is tender.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, celery, onion, water and salt in a large Dutch oven.
Simmer covered about 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Mash mixture a few times with a potato masher, but leave some vegetable pieces whole.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Return to heat and cook, stirring constantly, until soup is thoroughly reheated.

title: frogmore stew
directions: Fill large pot 1/3 full of water.
Bring water to boil.
Add crab boil and potatoes and boil 5 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients in order, letting stew boil 5 minutes between each addition.
As soon as shrimp turn pink, it's ready to eat.
Feeds 12.

title: pasta e fagioli
directions: In a saucepan, fry garlic in oil until it is golden brown. Add the tomato sauce and water; cook for about 10 minutes.
Add beans; stir gently and continue to simmer.
Cook ditalini al dente; drain and add to bean mixture.
Stir.
Serve immediately. Serves 4.

title: spanish chicken
directions: Boil chicken; take off bone and cut into pieces.
Add all ingredients together.
Bake for 25 minutes at 450°.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Cook meat and onions until done in skillet.
Mix meat and onions, corn, soup, sour cream, pimento and salt.
