Pour over cooked noodles in baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.
If crumbs brown too fast, cover with foil.

title: apple cake
directions: In a bowl, combine all ingredients and mix by hand.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 375°.

title: crumb topping for pies
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg; cut in the butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over filling and bake in hot 350° oven until brown, about 15 minutes.

title: coconut squares
directions: Put butter in 8-inch square microsafe baking dish.
Cook on High for 1 minute or until melted.
Stir in crumbs and sugar and mix.
Pat mixture firmly and evenly in bottom of dish.
Cook on High for 2 minutes.
Cool partially; mix coconut, milk and nuts. Spoon carefully over graham cracker crust.
Cook on High for 3 minutes; rotate dish one half turn once during cooking.
Sprinkle with chocolate bits.
Cook on High for 1 minute.
Spread melted chocolate over coconut.
Cool then cut.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: In butter, saute onion and carrots until tender over medium heat. Cook potatoes until tender, then add onion and carrots, including butter to cooked potatoes. Over medium heat, add enough milk to cover potatoes and add flour; stir. Cook 30 to 45 minutes, then add cheese and salt and pepper to taste. Cook until cheese is thoroughly melted. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fake steak
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together, then shape in loaf and put in fridge overnight.
Slice and fry.
Put in a casserole dish. Pour over a mixture of the mushroom soup and milk or water. Simmer for 1 hour in oven at 325° to 350°.

title: piglet blankets
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Divide each crescent roll into 3 sections.
Wrap each section around miniature hot dog.
This should make 48.
Bake until golden brown.
Serve with mustard.

title: peanut butter crinkles
directions: In
a
bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat margarine, peanut butter,
sugar,
brown
sugar,
eggs and vanilla until fluffy. At	low
speed,
beat in flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Shape into 1-inch balls; roll in sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in 350° oven for
to 15	minutes
or until browned.
Immediately press kisses
into cookies.
Cool.
Store in an airtight container. Makes 6 dozen.

title: chocolate-peanut butter drops
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and honey in Dutch oven; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter, stirring until blended.
Stir in cereal; drop by tablespoon onto waxed paper.
Let cool.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: docksides peanut butter pie
directions: Blend until smooth all the ingredients.
Pour in 1 (8 ounce) package Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust and freeze until ready to eat.

title: peanut butter surprises
directions: Spread peanut butter evenly on crackers; set aside.
Melt chocolate candy coating slowly in top portion of double boiler. Dip prepared crackers in coating and place on baking sheet lined with waxed paper.
Refrigerate until set.

title: twinkie dessert
directions: Layer the twinkies in a 9 inch square pan. (They just fit so do not eat any.) Peel and slice bananas, arrange slices on top of twinkies. Prepare vanilla pudding, spread over bananas. Spread whipped topping over bananas and pudding. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours or overnight.

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: Place chicken and cheese in a greased pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top with sauerkraut. Pour salad dressing evenly over cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours or until fork-tender.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley to serve.
Makes four servings...Good!

title: scotch-a-roos
directions: Mix and melt Karo syrup, peanut butter and sugar together in pan over low heat until smooth.
Add Rice Krispies and mix together.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan and cool for 30 minutes. Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips together in microwave for 2 minutes.
Stir until smooth and spread over Rice Krispies mix.

title: sour cream cake with orange icing
directions: Mix all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Place iron skillet of water on bottom rack under cake while cooking.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix margarine and crumbs.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with mixture.
Mix butter (melted), eggs and powdered sugar.
Put on top of crumbs.
Put on layer of bananas.
Put on layer of pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together first three ingredients and let set for 1 hour. Stir often.
Add flour, nutmeg, salt, cinnamon and baking soda to apple mixture.
Add oil, vanilla and eggs.
Mix well by hand.
Pour into a greased tube pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: copper pennies(serves 12 to 15)
directions: Slice and cook carrots.
To cooked carrots, add onion and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients.
Allow flavors to blend several hours before serving.
This relish will keep several weeks in refrigerator.

title: sukiyaki don(beef rice bowl)
directions: In a hot pan, pour vegetable oil and stir-fry the leek and shiitake mushroom.
Add beef, and cook until done.
Mix sugar, soy sauce, and butter until well blended.
Pour over beef mixture. Serve cooked rice in a bowl and pour this over the rice.
You can also put 1 tablespoon butter on top too.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Boil the raisins and water for 5 minutes. Cool and stir in the baking soda. Cream the sugar, shortening or oleo, vanilla and eggs.
Add the cooled raisin mixture, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and baking powder.
Nuts can be added. Drop by spoonfuls onto greased pan. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Should be a soft cookie.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the sugars and oleo.
Add oil, peanut butter and egg. Add soda in milk.
Add flour and salt.
Stir in chips.
Roll into balls and bake on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: christmas punch
directions: Prepare Kool-Aid according to package directions, then freeze. Combine orange juice, lemon juice, ginger ale and tea in a bowl. Add the fresh strawberries.
Add the frozen Kool-Aid just before serving.
Add water to taste if too sweet.
Makes 60 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add egg; beat thoroughly. Add banana and buttermilk.
Sift together dry ingredients and add, then add nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes or until well done.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Crumble sausage and brown.
Mix all ingredients together. Pour into buttered Pyrex dish (8 x 11 1/2 x 2-inches).
Bake at 350°, uncovered, about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chuckwagon beans
directions: Cook meat and onion until lightly browned.
Combine all ingredients in casserole.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, or until brown.

title: blueberry imperial pie
directions: Prepare pudding and pie filling mix as directed.
Cool.
Pour into shell.
Chill.
Drain blueberries, saving 1/2 cup syrup.
Mix sugar and cornstarch in quart pan.
Stir in the 1/2 cup syrup gradually until smooth.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick and clear.
Take off heat.
Stir in butter, lemon juice and berries.
Cool.
Spread on pie; chill until firm.
Top with sweetened, whipped cream if desired.

title: chicken elegante
directions: In a large, shallow baking dish, place chicken and set aside. Mix soup, wine and mushrooms and pour over chicken.
Bake in 350° oven about 1 hour or until fork can be inserted with ease.
Remove chicken to heated serving dish.
Add sour cream to liquid in baking dish.
Heat, stirring constantly.
Do not boil.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Beat together with sugars, vanilla, peanut butter and eggs.
In separate bowl, combine flour, bran, oats and baking soda.
Stir mixture into butter mixture.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix soups, rice and water.
Put mixture into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Place chicken breasts on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: michigan beans and sausage
directions: Place beans in a Dutch oven; add water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil; boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; cover and let stand for 1 hour.
Drain and discard liquid.
Return beans to pan and set aside.
In skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain, reserving 2 Tbsp. of drippings; set bacon aside.
Saute onions, and gizzards if desired, in the drippings until onions are tender and the gizzards are browned.
Add water, garlic, salt, marjoram, bay leaf, pepper, bacon, and onion mixture to beans.
Cover and bake at 350° for 3 hours or until beans are tender.
Discard bay leaf.
Stir in sausage and tomato sauce.
Toss bread crumbs and margarine; sprinkle over top.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes longer or until golden.
Yields 10-12 servings.

title: butter pecan cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture; mix well.
Stir in pecans.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° about 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields about 48 cookies.

title: marble cake
directions: In large bowl, combine cake mix, pudding mix, water and oil. Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Pour 2/3 of batter in Bundt pan (well-greased).
Mix remaining 1/3 batter with chocolate syrup and pour evenly over lemon mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
You could use any mixes, yellow, etc.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Layer ingredients.
Take out of refrigerator 1/2 hour before serving and mix up.

title: dirt pie
directions: Mix cookies, cream cheese, powdered sugar and butter until smooth.
Mix pudding and milk, then add Cool Whip.
Add cream cheese mixture.
Layer cookies and pudding.
Add a few gummy worms.
Use flower pot and flower scoop to serve.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients except butter.
Pour into well-greased casserole.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Cube the cake.
Add boiling water to Jell-O; stir until dissolved.
Add strawberries and ice cream; mix well and pour over cubes of angel food cake.
Ice with whipped cream.

title: peanut butter treasures
directions: Heat
oven to 375°.
Combine first 5 ingredients.
Beat at medium
speed until blended.
Add egg and beat until blended. Combine
flour,
salt
and	baking soda and add to creamy mixture. Mix until blended.
Stir in M&M's or butterscotties. Drop heaping
teaspoons	about
2-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: chicken barbecue
directions: Tear chicken into pieces and add other ingredients.
You may add a little water if too thick.
Simmer until onions are soft. Serve over rice.

title: steamed shrimp bubba
directions: Cook all ingredients uncovered in large pot over medium heat without water until shrimp are done (approximately 8 to 10 minutes).
Remove from heat and cover for 5 minutes.
Serve.

title: manly lancaster's buttermilk pie(former forsyth county sheriff)
directions: Cream sugar and butter together well.
Add eggs, buttermilk and flour.
Mix well.
Divide evenly between 3 pie shells.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: freeze-ahead pizza crust
directions: In large mixer bowl, stir together 3 cups of the flour, the yeast and salt; add water and oil.
Beat on low speed of electric mixer 1/2 minute, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes at high.
By hand stir in enough of the remaining flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead on lightly floured surface until smooth and elastic, about 12 minutes (dough should be firm).
Place in lightly greased bowl, turning once.
Cover; let rise until more than double, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Punch down; divide in fourths.
Cover; let rest 10 minutes.
On lightly floured surface, roll each portion to a 12-inch circle.
Place each on greased 12-inch pizza pan, forming edges on crust.
Bake in 425° oven 10 minutes (crust will not be brown).
Remove from oven; cool on pans.
Remove from pans; wrap each in foil.
Label and freeze.
Makes 4.

title: seafood lasagna
directions: Boil noodles according to package directions and drain.
Saute onion in butter, add cream cheese, egg, Ricotta cheese, basil and pepper.
Set aside.

title: pizza rounds(hors d'oeuvre)
directions: Cook beef and sausage together, stirring often until done. Drain grease.
Add broken cheese; stir until melted.
Cool. Spread on party rounds.
Place on a cookie sheet to freeze and then store in a "freezer-type" container.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 48.

title: boiled peanuts
directions: Wash peanuts thoroughly in cool running water to remove any grit from the surface of the shell. Place nuts in a stockpot and cover with a brine solution of 10 ounces salt to 1 gallon of water. Add optional flavors, if desired. Use adequate solution to completely submerge the peanuts. Bring peanuts to a rolling boil and cook for 1 hour. Taste test to determine if the nuts are cooked to a texture you prefer. If done, remove from stove. If still crunchy to your taste, continue boiling and checking every 15 minutes, until desired texture is reached. When cooked, serve immediately or allow to sit in the hot brine to increase the salty taste. The longer they sit, the saltier they get. When a desired level of saltiness is achieved, remove peanuts from the water and serve.

title: shoe peg corn
directions: Bring to boil sugar, oil and vinegar.
Pour over other ingredients.

title: easy pork barbecue
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients in crock-pot until tender.
Remove from pot and shred or chop.
Return to pot and add remaining ingredients.
Serve on hot buns.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients. Add enough water to pineapple juice to make 1 cup. Chill mixture until thick. Whip until fluffy. Add cream cheese. Mix thoroughly. Add celery, nuts and pineapple. Let stand in the refrigerator 1 hour, then whip in 1/2 pint whipping cream.

title: strawberry-banana smoothie
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of electric blender; finish filling with ice.
Process until smooth.
Yields 5 cups.

title: olive-nut party sandwiches
directions: Spread on bread rounds or rusks.
Decorate top with olive slice.

title: not so sweet pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except eggs.
Add eggs, beating in one at a time.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: rice pudding
directions: Separate eggs and add 2 tablespoons milk to the yolks.
Place remainder of milk in a double boiler, add the washed raisins and cook over hot water for 10 minutes.

title: judy's peanut butter pie
directions: Melt chocolate chips and spread over prepared graham cracker pie crust. Cream together powdered sugar and cream cheese. Add vanilla to taste. Add peanut butter; fold in Cool Whip. Spread over cooled chocolate. Chill at least 1/2 hour before serving.

title: imperial crab
directions: Add hot white sauce gradually to beaten egg yolks, stirring constantly.
Add crab meat and heat through.
Add mustard, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, cayenne and mushrooms and put in oiled crab shells.
Sprinkle lightly with buttered crumbs and parsley and brown in 450° oven for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle lemon juice over top and serve.
Serves 6.

title: marinated beans
directions: Drain and rinse beans.
Add chopped onions and peppers.
Mix other ingredients in small bowl.
Pour over beans.
Refrigerate for at least 24 hours before serving, stirring 2 or 3 times daily.

title: ratatouille
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet; add garlic, onion, green pepper and zucchini.
Cook about 3 minutes until onion is tender, stirring frequently.
Add eggplant, basil, oregano and pepper; cover and cook over medium heat for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add tomato wedges; cover and cook 5 minutes or until tomatoes are heated.
May be served warm or chilled.

title: new england boiled dinner
directions: Place brisket in large kettle.
Cover with cold water.
Cover tightly.
Simmer 3 1/2 hours or until tender.
Skim fat from liquid.
Add onions, carrots, potatoes and turnips.
Sprinkle with caraway seed.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove meat to warm platter.
Add cabbage; simmer uncovered 10 to 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 8 servings.

title: spring time lime salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Cool slightly, then stir in evaporated milk.
Chill until as thick as unbeaten egg whites. Fold in pineapple, lemon juice, cheese, nuts, celery, and mayonnaise.
Pour into 8 inch square pan or 5 cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Serves 8.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Saute crushed garlic in oil until lightly browned over low heat.
Add the juice or wine and bring to a boil.
Add shrimp and cook, stirring constantly, until shrimp turn pink, about 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve over linguine or angel hair pasta.
Sprinkle with Romano and bread crumbs.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour, salt and coconut.
Blend in peanut butter.
Spread in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°.
Cut into bars.
Makes about 1 dozen.

title: baked chicken with wine
directions: Dip chicken pieces in melted butter and roll in crushed bran flakes.
Place in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Halve the potatoes and place between chicken pieces.
Pour in a half cup of wine.
Cover and cook 40 minutes in 400° oven.
Uncover and cook 15 minutes more. Sprinkle with parsley.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Crumble crackers over soup mix.
Melt margarine and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(I just use chicken breasts.)

title: world's best play dough
directions: Combine water and alum.
Add to other ingredients.
Knead. Add food coloring.
Keep in covered containers.

title: sweet and sour kielbasa
directions: In large pan, combine juice, sugar, catsup and onion.
Bring to boil; simmer 15 minutes.
Slice kielbasa in 1/4-inch slices. Place in large pan.
Cover with water.
Bring to boil.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Drain.
Add to pineapple mixture; simmer 15 minutes. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Reheat before serving.

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Cream cheese well, then add jello liquid a little at a time and stir until smooth.
Add pineapple, lemon juice and salt.
Pour into molds and put in refrigerator.
Very good and pretty.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Brown hamburger in butter.
Add all the ingredients.
Simmer uncovered for 10 minutes or until onions and celery are tender.

title: fritters
directions: Dry food thoroughly before dipping into batter.
Heat fat or oil (3 to 4 inches) to 375° in deep fat fryer or kettle.
Measure all ingredients into bowl; beat with rotary beater until smooth.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Bake in a jelly roll pan for 15 minutes at 350°.
Frost.

title: enchiladas
directions: Soften tortillas in hot oil over medium heat.
Just dip in oil long enough to get coated.
Stack on plate and set aside.
Combine onion with hamburger.
Heat chili in pan over medium heat.
Add a little water.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Make sauce a day ahead.
Mix flour, sugar, pineapple juice, vinegar and slightly beaten egg in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until thick; chill overnight.
Mix chilled sauce with Cool Whip, crushed pineapple, diced apples and 3/4 cup peanuts.
Mix and top with remaining nuts.

title: baked apples
directions: Cut a circle at the top of each apple.
Take out the core. Sprinkle cinnamon on the inside and cook on High for 2 minutes on a microwave plate.

title: chocolate wonder cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cocoa, salt and soda into 9-inch square ungreased pan.
Make 3 holes in dry ingredients.
Pour vinegar, oil and vanilla in the 3 holes equally.
Pour 1 cup water over the cake.
Stir well with a fork until all lumps are out.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and frost.
Cake stays moist and good for a long time.

title: garlic pork roast
directions: Using the point of a paring knife, make slits all around the roast.
Insert the garlic slivers into the slits.
Rub entire roast with salt and sprinkle top with pepper.
Place in roasting pan with meat thermometer and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes per pound or until thermometer reads 160° to 170°.
Remove roast from pan and let stand.

title: mashed potato dish
directions: Cook potatoes; drain and mash.
Add cream cheese, sour cream, milk and salt and pepper.
Beat at medium speed until smooth. Spoon potato mixture into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Drizzle top with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve hot.

title: frozen bread caramel rolls
directions: Tear or cut 1 loaf in pieces and drop here and there in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt butter.
Add rest of ingredients and beat until smooth.
Pour over torn up loaf.
Cut 2nd loaf and place pieces in empty spots.
Let rise.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Turn out on waxed paper.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Heat until all is melted.
Serve in fondue dish with crackers.

title: hearty golden chowder
directions: Add water to potatoes, carrots, celery, onion, chives, salt and pepper.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes.
Do not drain.

title: spanish rice
directions: Melt butter in pan over medium high heat. Once melted, add onion. Saute onions 1-2 minutes and add rice. Cook rice 5 minutes, stirring 2 or 3 times. Add broth, water and tomato sauce. Bring to a boil. Cover and simmer until all liquid is completely absorbed and rice is dry. Mix in corn, if desired. Serve with green chili and pinto beans.

title: cranberry walnut squares
directions: Prepare and bake cookie crust.
Meanwhile, in large bowl, beat eggs, corn syrup, sugar and butter until well blended.
Stir in cranberries and walnuts.
Immediately pour over hot crust; spread evenly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until set.
Cool completely. Cut into bars.

title: canned pears
directions: Pack the pear halves in jars.
Combine the sugar and water to make a medium syrup; cover pears with boiling syrup and place in hot water bath for 10 minutes.

title: turkey pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large saucepan combine first 6 ingredients.
Heat until frozen vegetables are warm.
Transfer mixture to an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Unroll dough into 4 rectangles, pressing perforations on edges to seal.
Cover turkey mixture with 3 rectangles to form top crust.
Decorate crust with cutouts from remaining rectangle.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until browned.
Serves 6 to 12.

title: meringue cookies
directions: Heat oven to
Blend
all
ingredients
in top of double boiler.
Place over boiling water; beat with rotary (or cordless) mixer, scraping
sides and bottom of pan occasionally, until mixture
forms
stiff peaks.
(Note:
At this point, you can add food
coloring
to make these into pastel colored cookies.)

title: grandma's meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except milk in a large bowl, mixing well.
Add milk and mix.
Place in loaf pan and bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken continental
directions: Roll chicken in flour.
Brown in butter.
Remove chicken. Saute onion and celery in drippings.
Add seasonings, soup and water.
Bring to boil and add rice.
Bake mix for 30 minutes or finish on top of stove.

title: swiss pie
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and
margarine; press into bottom and sides of 8-inch pie plate.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Drain and flake tuna. Combine with bread crumbs, celery and onion in a large bowl; mix well. Stir in mixture of mayonnaise, chili sauce and lemon juice. Shape into 5 patties. Place in lightly oiled skillet. Cook over low to medium heat for 5 minutes or until light brown. Serve plain or on hamburger buns with lettuce and tomato. Yields 5 servings.

title: artichoke pasta casserole
directions: Mix vinegar, oil, mustard, rosemary and pepper.
Add artichoke hearts, salami, carrots and zucchini.
Mix well.
Add cooked and drained vermicelli and combine all ingredients together.
Stir in Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° covered with foil.
After 45 minutes, remove foil and top with the Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 15 additional minutes.

title: grandma marys chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour, soda and salt, set aside.
Cream butter and brown sugar till light, add eggs and vanilla.
Slowly add flour mixture then add chocolate chips, toffee bits and pecans.
Scoop with ice cream scoop to cookie sheet.
Bake 350° for 12-15 minutes; let cool on cookie sheet 5-8 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: three layers of yum
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 12 minutes at 350°.
Combine the next 3 ingredients and spread over crust.
Mix pudding and milk and pour over cheese.
Top with remaining Dream Whip.

title: melt away peanut butter balls
directions: Hand mix together butter, peanut butter, evaporated milk and sugar.
Do not use electric mixer.
Mix together well, using pastry blender or fork.
Form into balls or eggs and chill.
Melt chocolate and dip balls or eggs into melted chocolate.
Chill.

title: chili con carne
directions: In a Pam sprayed Dutch oven, saute first 5 ingredients 8 to 10 minutes. Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Uncover and simmer 15 minutes to thicken.
Serves 6.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Mix ingredients together in a bowl.
Spray a baking dish with Pam.
Dip chicken pieces into mixture and place in baking dish. (Pour leftover mixture over chicken.)
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: crunchy apple raisin salad
directions: Wash, core and dice apples.
Put into a large bowl.
Add raisins, nuts, marshmallows and carrots.
Mix well and stir in the whipped topping.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: mixed fruit soup
directions: Combine juice, pudding and sugar in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Simmer 5 minutes or until slightly thick.
Add orange slices, lemon slices and spices.
Simmer 10 minutes more, stirring occasionally. Discard citrus slices, cinnamon sticks and whole cloves.
Add fresh fruit and simmer 10 minutes longer. Serve hot or cold. Garnish with sour cream and/or ground cinnamon.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar to pineapple and bring to a boil on low heat; cool, then add other ingredients in layers or mixed up.
Top with whipped cream.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together.
Put into a loaf pan.
Bake until done or microwave pan for 6 minutes.

title: bonnie pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into graham cracker pie crust.
Save 1 tablespoon to spoon on top.
Spread fruit pie mix over fruit cream mix.
Put last tablespoon of fruit cream mix on top.
Serve chilled.

title: confetti fish
directions: Preheat broiler to hot.
Place fish in oiled shallow pan in single layer.
In a small bowl combine crumbs, basil, onions, green pepper, carrot, oil and vinegar.
Spread mixture on fish. Broil 6 inches from heat until fish flakes easily.

title: mounds bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients for crust and press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Mix milk and coconut and spread over crust.
Bake for 20 minutes.
When cool, frost with melted chocolate chips and peanut butter mixture.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; drain.
Add seasoning mix and water to meat.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer for 15 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread corn chips on bottom of 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Pour meat sauce evenly over chips. Sprinkle cheese and green pepper over meat.
Bake in oven for 20 minutes to melt cheese and heat through.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: mushroom stuffed tomatoes
directions: Wash tomatoes.
Cut off tops and remove pulp.
Prepare mushroom filling.
Wash fresh mushrooms with water, then scald. Slightly dry them.
Slice, salt and fry until done.
Add sour cream and mix.
Heat.
Spoon mushroom mixture into hollowed tomatoes.

title: tex-mex
directions: Layer in large rectangular pan or dish in the following order: refried beans, sour cream mixed with the taco seasoning, tomatoes, onions, olives and Cheddar cheese.
Chill and serve with nacho or tortilla chips.

title: super shrimp creole
directions: Cook onion, celery and garlic in oil in large skillet until tender, but not brown.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, Pace picante sauce and seasonings.
Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Combine cornstarch and water; add to sauce and stir until smooth and thickened.
Add shrimp and green pepper.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Serve over rice with additional Pace picante sauce. Makes four 1-cup servings.

title: ooy-gooy
directions: Lightly grease a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix cake mix, margarine and 1 egg together.
Press into pan bottom edges up.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and 2 eggs together.
Pour on top and bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Arrange pecan halves in pie crust.
Beat eggs.
Add melted butter, corn syrup and vanilla; stir until well blended.
Combine sugar and flour; blend this with the egg mixture.
Pour over pecans.
Let stand until nuts rise to surface.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa well to avoid lumps.
Mix in other ingredients.
Add nuts, coconut, and/or oatmeal.
Mix well.
Put into 8-inch pie shell.
Place pecan halves on top. Bake at 350° until done, about 30 minutes.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
In a skillet, saute the onions, celery and pepper in butter; pour into a casserole dish and add pimiento, mushrooms, rice, shrimp, crabmeat and mushroom soup; mix thoroughly.
Top with cracker crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter or margarine in a large saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth and bubbly (about 1 minute).
Remove from heat.
Stir in broth and milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly with a wire whisk.
Boil and whisk 1 minute.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into ungreased 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish or 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 40 to 45 minutes.
Garnish with snipped parsley.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sweet and sour hot dogs
directions: Cut pepper into strips and saute in butter until tender.
Add hot dogs and drained pineapple to pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Mix brown sugar and barbecue sauce together and add to hot dogs. Simmer another 10 to 15 minutes until hot.
Serve over rice or alone.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown the hamburger and let cool.
Mix together the cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning until smooth. Spread on cookie sheet.
Put cooled hamburger on top, shredded lettuce on top of hamburger and sprinkle Cheddar cheese.
Garnish with tomatoes.
Use nacho chips to dip with.

title: yummy frosting
directions: Beat all ingredients at high speed until creamy and smooth. Vary by adding food coloring or grated sweet chocolate.
Frosts one two-layer 8-inch or 9 x 13-inch cake.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Cook vegetables and garlic in oil until tender.
Stir in pasta sauce and oregano; simmer 15 minutes.
Combine cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese.
In 13 x 9-inch baking dish, layer 1/2 each of the noodles, sauce, cottage cheese and Mozzarella.
Repeat layering.
Top with chopped parsley.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes.
Let stand 20 minutes and serve.

title: sweet coffee cake
directions: Mix ingredients and set aside.

title: fudge drop cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, nuts and salt in mixer bowl; mix at low speed until thoroughly blended.
Add unbeaten egg whites; mix just to moisten.
Do not overmix.
Line baking sheets with parchment paper.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls, 2 to 3 inches apart, onto parchment paper.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: rice chantilly
directions: Combine rice, sour cream, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup cheese. Spoon into buttered shallow 1-quart baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: no fail cobbler
directions: Heat one large can of cherries or peaches or some other fruit (as you prefer), juice and all.
Melt 1 stick butter or oleo in 2-quart baking dish.
Pour the mixed batter over the top of the melted butter.
Then pour hot fruit over batter and bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: rootin' tootin'
directions: In a large hot skillet brown potato and carrot in granola oil.
When slightly tender, add celery and onion.
When they are slightly tender, add squash, zucchini and green pepper.
When they are slightly tender, add garlic, Italian seasoning, tomato and salt.
Cover and cook on medium heat for 1/2 hour.
The tomato and vegetable juices should form a rich sauce.

title: chocolate dipped strawberries
directions: Melt semi-sweet chips, vanilla chips and oil together.
Stir often until smooth.
Holding by top, dip strawberries into melted chocolate and place on wax paper-lined baking sheet.
Cover loosely and chill until firm, about 1 hour.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Mix and let stand 2 to 3 days.
Stir a couple times a day.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with buttered hands.
Roll into rolls. Place chili powder on wax paper.
Roll the cheese rolls in chili powder; roll in plastic wrap.
Chill.
Slice and serve on crackers.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine with meat and lay meat mixture between 2 pieces of wax paper.
Roll out like a jelly roll.
Sprinkle with about 1 cup grated cheese and 1 large jar of Green Giant mushrooms.
Roll up like jelly roll.
Top roll with barbecue sauce.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: polynesian spareribs
directions: Cut ribs into serving-size pieces, 3 to 4 ribs wide.
Arrange them in a shallow roasting pan. Cover pan with aluminum foil; crimp foil tightly to edge of pan. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: dumplings
directions: Beat together egg
and
milk.
Add dry ingredients, mix with a fork.
Drop
into meat broth or sauerkraut.
Boil about 20 minutes.

title: bagel snack
directions: Cut bagel in half.
Heat both halves.
Spread with butter, cream cheese and sardines.
Serve with thin slices of sharp cheese.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Bake in loaf pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cold pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles, then mix in rest of the ingredients.
Chill in refrigerator for at least 1 hour.

title: fried rice
directions: Pour 1 tablespoon of oil into a large skillet.
Preheat over medium heat.
Add eggs.
Lift and tilt the skillet to form a thin sheet of egg.
Cook, without stirring, about 2 minutes or just until set.
Slide sheet onto a cutting board.
Cut into 2 x 1/2-inch strips.
Pour remaining oil into skillet.
Preheat over medium-high heat.
Add green onions; stir-fry for 30 seconds.
Add the shrimp, ham and mushrooms; stir-fry for 1 minute, adding more oil if necessary.
Stir in rice.
Sprinkle with soy sauce; stir-fry 1 to 2 minutes more.
Stir in egg strips, lettuce and peas; heat through.
Gently toss.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: beef ball (appetizer)
directions: Mix
together	cream	cheese,
Worcestershire
sauce, Accent, onion and beef (chopped
fine).
Make ball or can make 2 small balls.
Take other
package of beef (chopped) and roll ball into it.

title: favorite muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottom of 12 muffin cups.
Beat egg; stir egg and oil.
Mix in remaining ingredients just until it is moistened.
Batter should be lumpy.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: hayride kitchen bean soup
directions: Blend 1 can of each type of bean in blender.
Add 1 soup can water.
Cook in crock-pot all day or simmer on low heat 2 hours or longer.
Stir often.
Serve over rice.

title: apple salad
directions: Cook ingredients except apples over medium heat until thick. Cool completely!
Peel and dice apples.
Mix with cooled sauce and pour into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with Cool Whip. Sprinkle a few chopped pecans and cocktail cherries with stems on top.
Chill.
Serves 12+.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Put in bundt pan which has been floured and greased.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Mix some apricot nectar with powdered sugar and pour over warm cake.

title: raspberry champagne
directions: Puree raspberries.
Mix all together.
Raspberry sherbet may be added, if desired.
Serves 20.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Heat lightly until mixed, sugar, water and cream of tartar. Break crackers in halves and place in an unbaked pie shell.
Pour ingredients over and add top pie crust.
Bake until golden brown. You will be surprised!

title: baked vegetable meat loaf
directions: Spray 5 x 9-inch loaf pan. In large bowl, combine beef, oats, carrots, celery, onion and parsley. Mix well. Combine tomato sauce, egg and seasoning. Combine meat mixture with tomato sauce mixture just until mixed. Lightly spoon into loaf pan. Bake in 375° oven for 50 to 60 minutes. Allow to stand for 5 minutes, then slice into 6 pieces.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Mix ingredients together like you would a pie crust.
Line a greased 9 x 13-inch pan with dough.
Peel and slice the apples. Line on top of dough. Sprinkle with sugar, cinnamon and 1/2 cup melted butter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine the last 3 ingredients and pour over the first 5 ingredients.

title: ruby's peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and butter.
Cook for 12 minutes at a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into lightly buttered 10 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and cut.

title: no bake brownies
directions: In medium pan, combine milk and chocolate chips and cook over low heat, stirring occasionally until chocolate melts and mixture is smooth; pour into electric mixing bowl and add graham cracker crumbs and nuts to mixture on medium speed until smooth.
Spread in greased 8 x 8-inch pan; refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: bonnie's banana bread
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder and soda.
Cream until light the margarine and brown sugar.
Beat in bananas.
Alternate adding the wet mixture to the flour mixture in about 3 parts with the vanilla and water.
Stir until blended.
Transfer to loaf pan (greased).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Place grated zucchini, onion and salt in ice water and refrigerate overnight; drain well.
Add vinegar, sugar, celery seed, cornstarch, dry mustard, pepper, turmeric and peppers.
(You can use all green pepper, if you choose.) Stir well and cook 30 minutes.
Pour in 6 pint jars and process 15 minutes in hot water.

title: miracle soup
directions: Cut up vegetables and cover with water.
Season with dry onion soup mix.
Boil for 10 minutes; cover, lower heat and simmer until vegetables are soft.

title: santa fe souffle
directions: Cook the grits as directed on box.
When they are cooked, add the remaining ingredients. Mix well and pour into a greased casserole and bake at 350° until brown, about 30 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine oil and sugar. Add eggs and salt and mix. Mix together baking soda and buttermilk. Add to egg mixture, alternately with flour. Add bananas. Fold in nuts and pour into a well-greased pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: low-fat hot chocolate
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly in a large container.
Keep in tight container.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers and oleo.
Put in casserole dish or pan.

title: easy italian roast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line roast pan with aluminum foil. Salt roast and place in pan.
Combine soup, mix and water; stir and pour over roast.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 1 hour per pound for a tender and delicious roast.

title: sweet potato pone
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in greased cast-iron skillet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.
You may add grated orange peel if desired.

title: orange salad
directions: Drain fruits.
Mix and make 1 cup.
Pour in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add jello to dissolve; cool.
Add other ingredients. Chill until firm.

title: delicious italian soup
directions: Brown meats.
Add tomatoes, onion soup mix and Italian seasonings.
Cover and simmer 1 hour until beef is tender.
Add consomme, Burgundy, mushrooms, beans and cooked macaroni and cook for 20 minutes more.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Let broccoli thaw and mix soup, milk, 1/2 of margarine and Cheez Whiz over low heat.
Saute onion in 1/2 of margarine. Combine all ingredients together and pour into a large glass baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Do not cover.
I like to use fresh broccoli.

title: mexican meat loaf roll
directions: In a large bowl, combine eggs, oats, Worcestershire sauce and pepper. Add ground beef and mix well. On a piece of waxed paper, pat meat mixture into an 18 x 9-inch rectangle. Combine cream cheese and chilies. Spread over meat to within 1-inch of outer edges. Roll meat mixture, jelly roll style starting at narrow end. Place seam side down in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Drain excess fat. Top with salsa and bake another 10 to 15 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: creamy yogurt cooler(a real kid pleaser!)
directions: Place the yogurt and sherbet in blender container.
Cover; blend about 15 seconds, or until smooth.
Serve immediately as a beverage, or pour mixture into four 3-ounce paper cups.
Insert wooden sticks in mixture.
Freeze about 2 hours, or until firm.

title: pizza twists
directions: Unroll breadsticks.
Place 1 pepperoni on each end.
Cover pepperoni up; give a twist.
Bake at 350°.
Can be served plain or in pizza sauce.

title: peanut butter ripple fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in heavy 2 to 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to full rolling boil, stirring constantly. Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat or until candy thermometer reaches 234°, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter until melted. Add marshmallow and vanilla; beat until blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate bits.
Cut through fudge with knife for marble effect.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to directions.
Combine mayonnaise, celery, cheese and onion in small bowl.
Place vegetables in long cooking dish.
Layer cheese mixture on top of vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, covered with tinfoil.
Remove tinfoil, sprinkle crackers over and drizzle margarine over them.
Return to oven and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer, until golden.
May add water chestnuts if desired.

title: quick beer bread
directions: Combine Bisquick, flour and sugar and mix.
Add eggs and beer. Beat with an electric mixer for about 1 minute, until blended. Turn into a greased loaf/bread pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool in pan for 10 minutes and remove.
This is a great quick bread for the fall season and goes nicely with soups and salads.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into baking dish.
Cook at 350° until done.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix cooked hamburger, lettuce, tomatoes, onion, red kidney beans, cheese and seasoning.
Just before serving, add the remaining ingredients.

title: shredded beef sandwiches
directions: Trim fat from roast.
Cut roast as necessary to fit into a 3 to 4-quart electric slow cooker.
Place meat in cooker.
Combine vinegar, onion, bay leaves, salt, cloves and garlic powder.
Pour over meat.
Cover and cook on low heat setting for 11 to 12 hours or until meat is very tender.
Remove meat and use two forks to shred meat.
Discard bones and fat.
If desired, line split rolls with spinach or lettuce leaves.
Place shredded meat on roll. Strain meat juices; skim off fat from juices.
Serve juices with sandwiches for dipping.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: jumbo stuffed shells (beef)
directions: Break ground beef into small particles and saute in butter or olive oil.	Mix thoroughly meat, egg, Mozzarella, milk, bread, chopped parsley, salt and pepper.
Fill cooked shells.
Cover bottom of baking dish with pasta sauce.
Arrange filled shells side by side in single layer in baking pan.
Pour remaining sauce over filled shells and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes. Sprinkle with grated cheese and serve.
